INSERT INTO verses (book_id, chapter, verse, text, version) VALUES
(44, 24, 43, '"Know this: A homeowner who knew exactly when a burglar was coming would stay alert and not permit the house to be broken into.', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 44, 'You also must be ready all the time. For the Son of Man will come when least expected.', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 45, '"Who is a faithful, sensible servant, to whom the master can give the responsibility of managing his household and feeding his family?', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 46, 'If the master returns and finds that the servant has done a good job, there will be a reward.', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 47, 'I assure you, the master will put that servant in charge of all he owns.', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 48, 'But if the servant is evil and thinks, ''My master won''t be back for a while,''', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 49, 'and begins oppressing the other servants, partying, and getting drunk--', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 50, 'well, the master will return unannounced and unexpected.', 'NLT'),
(44, 24, 51, 'He will tear the servant apart and banish him with the hypocrites. In that place there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 1, '"The Kingdom of Heaven can be illustrated by the story of ten bridesmaids who took their lamps and went to meet the bridegroom.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 2, 'Five of them were foolish, and five were wise.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 3, 'The five who were foolish took no oil for their lamps,', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 4, 'but the other five were wise enough to take along extra oil.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 5, 'When the bridegroom was delayed, they all lay down and slept.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 6, 'At midnight they were roused by the shout, ''Look, the bridegroom is coming! Come out and welcome him!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 7, '"All the bridesmaids got up and prepared their lamps.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 8, 'Then the five foolish ones asked the others, ''Please give us some of your oil because our lamps are going out.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 9, 'But the others replied, ''We don''t have enough for all of us. Go to a shop and buy some for yourselves.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 10, '"But while they were gone to buy oil, the bridegroom came, and those who were ready went in with him to the marriage feast, and the door was locked.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 11, 'Later, when the other five bridesmaids returned, they stood outside, calling, ''Sir, open the door for us!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 12, 'But he called back, ''I don''t know you!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 13, '"So stay awake and be prepared, because you do not know the day or hour of my return.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 14, '"Again, the Kingdom of Heaven can be illustrated by the story of a man going on a trip. He called together his servants and gave them money to invest for him while he was gone.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 15, 'He gave five bags of gold to one, two bags of gold to another, and one bag of gold to the last--dividing it in proportion to their abilities--and then left on his trip.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 16, 'The servant who received the five bags of gold began immediately to invest the money and soon doubled it.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 17, 'The servant with two bags of gold also went right to work and doubled the money.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 18, 'But the servant who received the one bag of gold dug a hole in the ground and hid the master''s money for safekeeping.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 19, '"After a long time their master returned from his trip and called them to give an account of how they had used his money.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 20, 'The servant to whom he had entrusted the five bags of gold said, ''Sir, you gave me five bags of gold to invest, and I have doubled the amount.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 21, 'The master was full of praise. ''Well done, my good and faithful servant. You have been faithful in handling this small amount, so now I will give you many more responsibilities. Let''s celebrate together!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 22, '"Next came the servant who had received the two bags of gold, with the report, ''Sir, you gave me two bags of gold to invest, and I have doubled the amount.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 23, 'The master said, ''Well done, my good and faithful servant. You have been faithful in handling this small amount, so now I will give you many more responsibilities. Let''s celebrate together!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 24, '"Then the servant with the one bag of gold came and said, ''Sir, I know you are a hard man, harvesting crops you didn''t plant and gathering crops you didn''t cultivate.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 25, 'I was afraid I would lose your money, so I hid it in the earth and here it is.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 26, '"But the master replied, ''You wicked and lazy servant! You think I''m a hard man, do you, harvesting crops I didn''t plant and gathering crops I didn''t cultivate?', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 27, 'Well, you should at least have put my money into the bank so I could have some interest.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 28, 'Take the money from this servant and give it to the one with the ten bags of gold.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 29, 'To those who use well what they are given, even more will be given, and they will have an abundance. But from those who are unfaithful, even what little they have will be taken away.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 30, 'Now throw this useless servant into outer darkness, where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 31, '"But when the Son of Man comes in his glory, and all the angels with him, then he will sit upon his glorious throne.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 32, 'All the nations will be gathered in his presence, and he will separate them as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 33, 'He will place the sheep at his right hand and the goats at his left.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 34, 'Then the King will say to those on the right, ''Come, you who are blessed by my Father, inherit the Kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 35, 'For I was hungry, and you fed me. I was thirsty, and you gave me a drink. I was a stranger, and you invited me into your home.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 36, 'I was naked, and you gave me clothing. I was sick, and you cared for me. I was in prison, and you visited me.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 37, '"Then these righteous ones will reply, ''Lord, when did we ever see you hungry and feed you? Or thirsty and give you something to drink?', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 38, 'Or a stranger and show you hospitality? Or naked and give you clothing?', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 39, 'When did we ever see you sick or in prison, and visit you?''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 40, 'And the King will tell them, ''I assure you, when you did it to one of the least of these my brothers and sisters, you were doing it to me!''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 41, '"Then the King will turn to those on the left and say, ''Away with you, you cursed ones, into the eternal fire prepared for the Devil and his demons!', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 42, 'For I was hungry, and you didn''t feed me. I was thirsty, and you didn''t give me anything to drink.', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 43, 'I was a stranger, and you didn''t invite me into your home. I was naked, and you gave me no clothing. I was sick and in prison, and you didn''t visit me.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 44, '"Then they will reply, ''Lord, when did we ever see you hungry or thirsty or a stranger or naked or sick or in prison, and not help you?''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 45, 'And he will answer, ''I assure you, when you refused to help the least of these my brothers and sisters, you were refusing to help me.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 25, 46, 'And they will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous will go into eternal life."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 1, 'When Jesus had finished saying these things, he said to his disciples,', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 2, '"As you know, the Passover celebration begins in two days, and I, the Son of Man, will be betrayed and crucified."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 3, 'At that same time the leading priests and other leaders were meeting at the residence of Caiaphas, the high priest,', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 4, 'to discuss how to capture Jesus secretly and put him to death.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 5, '"But not during the Passover," they agreed, "or there will be a riot."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 6, 'Meanwhile, Jesus was in Bethany at the home of Simon, a man who had leprosy.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 7, 'During supper, a woman came in with a beautiful jar of expensive perfume and poured it over his head.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 8, 'The disciples were indignant when they saw this. "What a waste of money," they said.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 9, '"She could have sold it for a fortune and given the money to the poor."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 10, 'But Jesus replied, "Why berate her for doing such a good thing to me?', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 11, 'You will always have the poor among you, but I will not be here with you much longer.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 12, 'She has poured this perfume on me to prepare my body for burial.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 13, 'I assure you, wherever the Good News is preached throughout the world, this woman''s deed will be talked about in her memory."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 14, 'Then Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve disciples, went to the leading priests', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 15, 'and asked, "How much will you pay me to betray Jesus to you?" And they gave him thirty pieces of silver.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 16, 'From that time on, Judas began looking for the right time and place to betray Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 17, 'On the first day of the Festival of Unleavened Bread, the disciples came to Jesus and asked, "Where do you want us to prepare the Passover supper?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 18, '"As you go into the city," he told them, "you will see a certain man. Tell him, ''The Teacher says, My time has come, and I will eat the Passover meal with my disciples at your house.''"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 19, 'So the disciples did as Jesus told them and prepared the Passover supper there.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 20, 'When it was evening, Jesus sat down at the table with the twelve disciples.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 21, 'While they were eating, he said, "The truth is, one of you will betray me."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 22, 'Greatly distressed, one by one they began to ask him, "I''m not the one, am I, Lord?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 23, 'He replied, "One of you who is eating with me now will betray me.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 24, 'For I, the Son of Man, must die, as the Scriptures declared long ago. But how terrible it will be for my betrayer. Far better for him if he had never been born!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 25, 'Judas, the one who would betray him, also asked, "Teacher, I''m not the one, am I?" And Jesus told him, "You have said it yourself."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 26, 'As they were eating, Jesus took a loaf of bread and asked God''s blessing on it. Then he broke it in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, "Take it and eat it, for this is my body."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 27, 'And he took a cup of wine and gave thanks to God for it. He gave it to them and said, "Each of you drink from it,', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 28, 'for this is my blood, which seals the covenant between God and his people. It is poured out to forgive the sins of many.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 29, 'Mark my words--I will not drink wine again until the day I drink it new with you in my Father''s Kingdom."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 30, 'Then they sang a hymn and went out to the Mount of Olives.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 31, '"Tonight all of you will desert me," Jesus told them. "For the Scriptures say, ''God will strike the Shepherd, and the sheep of the flock will be scattered.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 32, 'But after I have been raised from the dead, I will go ahead of you to Galilee and meet you there."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 33, 'Peter declared, "Even if everyone else deserts you, I never will."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 34, '"Peter," Jesus replied, "the truth is, this very night, before the rooster crows, you will deny me three times."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 35, '"No!" Peter insisted. "Not even if I have to die with you! I will never deny you!" And all the other disciples vowed the same.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 36, 'Then Jesus brought them to an olive grove called Gethsemane, and he said, "Sit here while I go on ahead to pray."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 37, 'He took Peter and Zebedee''s two sons, James and John, and he began to be filled with anguish and deep distress.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 38, 'He told them, "My soul is crushed with grief to the point of death. Stay here and watch with me."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 39, 'He went on a little farther and fell face down on the ground, praying, "My Father! If it is possible, let this cup of suffering be taken away from me. Yet I want your will, not mine."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 40, 'Then he returned to the disciples and found them asleep. He said to Peter, "Couldn''t you stay awake and watch with me even one hour?', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 41, 'Keep alert and pray. Otherwise temptation will overpower you. For though the spirit is willing enough, the body is weak!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 42, 'Again he left them and prayed, "My Father! If this cup cannot be taken away until I drink it, your will be done."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 43, 'He returned to them again and found them sleeping, for they just couldn''t keep their eyes open.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 44, 'So he went back to pray a third time, saying the same things again.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 45, 'Then he came to the disciples and said, "Still sleeping? Still resting? Look, the time has come. I, the Son of Man, am betrayed into the hands of sinners.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 46, 'Up, let''s be going. See, my betrayer is here!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 47, 'And even as he said this, Judas, one of the twelve disciples, arrived with a mob that was armed with swords and clubs. They had been sent out by the leading priests and other leaders of the people.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 48, 'Judas had given them a prearranged signal: "You will know which one to arrest when I go over and give him the kiss of greeting."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 49, 'So Judas came straight to Jesus. "Greetings, Teacher!" he exclaimed and gave him the kiss.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 50, 'Jesus said, "My friend, go ahead and do what you have come for." Then the others grabbed Jesus and arrested him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 51, 'One of the men with Jesus pulled out a sword and slashed off an ear of the high priest''s servant.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 52, '"Put away your sword," Jesus told him. "Those who use the sword will be killed by the sword.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 53, 'Don''t you realize that I could ask my Father for thousands of angels to protect us, and he would send them instantly?', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 54, 'But if I did, how would the Scriptures be fulfilled that describe what must happen now?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 55, 'Then Jesus said to the crowd, "Am I some dangerous criminal, that you have come armed with swords and clubs to arrest me? Why didn''t you arrest me in the Temple? I was there teaching every day.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 56, 'But this is all happening to fulfill the words of the prophets as recorded in the Scriptures." At that point, all the disciples deserted him and fled.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 57, 'Then the people who had arrested Jesus led him to the home of Caiaphas, the high priest, where the teachers of religious law and other leaders had gathered.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 58, 'Meanwhile, Peter was following far behind and eventually came to the courtyard of the high priest''s house. He went in, sat with the guards, and waited to see what was going to happen to Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 59, 'Inside, the leading priests and the entire high council were trying to find witnesses who would lie about Jesus, so they could put him to death.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 60, 'But even though they found many who agreed to give false witness, there was no testimony they could use. Finally, two men were found', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 61, 'who declared, "This man said, ''I am able to destroy the Temple of God and rebuild it in three days.''"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 62, 'Then the high priest stood up and said to Jesus, "Well, aren''t you going to answer these charges? What do you have to say for yourself?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 63, 'But Jesus remained silent. Then the high priest said to him, "I demand in the name of the living God that you tell us whether you are the Messiah, the Son of God."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 64, 'Jesus replied, "Yes, it is as you say. And in the future you will see me, the Son of Man, sitting at God''s right hand in the place of power and coming back on the clouds of heaven."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 65, 'Then the high priest tore his clothing to show his horror, shouting, "Blasphemy! Why do we need other witnesses? You have all heard his blasphemy.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 66, 'What is your verdict?Guilty!" they shouted. "He must die!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 67, 'Then they spit in Jesus'' face and hit him with their fists. And some slapped him,', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 68, 'saying, "Prophesy to us, you Messiah! Who hit you that time?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 69, 'Meanwhile, as Peter was sitting outside in the courtyard, a servant girl came over and said to him, "You were one of those with Jesus the Galilean."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 70, 'But Peter denied it in front of everyone. "I don''t know what you are talking about," he said.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 71, 'Later, out by the gate, another servant girl noticed him and said to those standing around, "This man was with Jesus of Nazareth."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 72, 'Again Peter denied it, this time with an oath. "I don''t even know the man," he said.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 73, 'A little later some other bystanders came over to him and said, "You must be one of them; we can tell by your Galilean accent."', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 74, 'Peter said, "I swear by God, I don''t know the man." And immediately the rooster crowed.', 'NLT'),
(44, 26, 75, 'Suddenly, Jesus'' words flashed through Peter''s mind: "Before the rooster crows, you will deny me three times." And he went away, crying bitterly.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 1, 'Very early in the morning, the leading priests and other leaders met again to discuss how to persuade the Roman government to sentence Jesus to death.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 2, 'Then they bound him and took him to Pilate, the Roman governor.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 3, 'When Judas, who had betrayed him, realized that Jesus had been condemned to die, he was filled with remorse. So he took the thirty pieces of silver back to the leading priests and other leaders.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 4, '"I have sinned," he declared, "for I have betrayed an innocent man.What do we care?" they retorted. "That''s your problem."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 5, 'Then Judas threw the money onto the floor of the Temple and went out and hanged himself.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 6, 'The leading priests picked up the money. "We can''t put it in the Temple treasury," they said, "since it''s against the law to accept money paid for murder."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 7, 'After some discussion they finally decided to buy the potter''s field, and they made it into a cemetery for foreigners.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 8, 'That is why the field is still called the Field of Blood.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 9, 'This fulfilled the prophecy of Jeremiah that says, "They took the thirty pieces of silver--the price at which he was valued by the people of Israel--', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 10, 'and purchased the potter''s field, as the Lord directed. "', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 11, 'Now Jesus was standing before Pilate, the Roman governor. "Are you the King of the Jews?" the governor asked him. Jesus replied, "Yes, it is as you say."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 12, 'But when the leading priests and other leaders made their accusations against him, Jesus remained silent.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 13, '"Don''t you hear their many charges against you?" Pilate demanded.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 14, 'But Jesus said nothing, much to the governor''s great surprise.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 15, 'Now it was the governor''s custom to release one prisoner to the crowd each year during the Passover celebration--anyone they wanted.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 16, 'This year there was a notorious criminal in prison, a man named Barabbas.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 17, 'As the crowds gathered before Pilate''s house that morning, he asked them, "Which one do you want me to release to you--Barabbas, or Jesus who is called the Messiah?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 18, '(He knew very well that the Jewish leaders had arrested Jesus out of envy.)', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 19, 'Just then, as Pilate was sitting on the judgment seat, his wife sent him this message: "Leave that innocent man alone, because I had a terrible nightmare about him last night."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 20, 'Meanwhile, the leading priests and other leaders persuaded the crowds to ask for Barabbas to be released and for Jesus to be put to death.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 21, 'So when the governor asked again, "Which of these two do you want me to release to you?" the crowd shouted back their reply: "Barabbas!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 22, '"But if I release Barabbas," Pilate asked them, "what should I do with Jesus who is called the Messiah?" And they all shouted, "Crucify him!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 23, '"Why?" Pilate demanded. "What crime has he committed?" But the crowd only roared the louder, "Crucify him!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 24, 'Pilate saw that he wasn''t getting anywhere and that a riot was developing. So he sent for a bowl of water and washed his hands before the crowd, saying, "I am innocent of the blood of this man. The responsibility is yours!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 25, 'And all the people yelled back, "We will take responsibility for his death--we and our children!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 26, 'So Pilate released Barabbas to them. He ordered Jesus flogged with a lead-tipped whip, then turned him over to the Roman soldiers to crucify him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 27, 'Some of the governor''s soldiers took Jesus into their headquarters and called out the entire battalion.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 28, 'They stripped him and put a scarlet robe on him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 29, 'They made a crown of long, sharp thorns and put it on his head, and they placed a stick in his right hand as a scepter. Then they knelt before him in mockery, yelling, "Hail! King of the Jews!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 30, 'And they spit on him and grabbed the stick and beat him on the head with it.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 31, 'When they were finally tired of mocking him, they took off the robe and put his own clothes on him again. Then they led him away to be crucified.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 32, 'As they were on the way, they came across a man named Simon, who was from Cyrene, and they forced him to carry Jesus'' cross.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 33, 'Then they went out to a place called Golgotha (which means Skull Hill).', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 34, 'The soldiers gave him wine mixed with bitter gall, but when he had tasted it, he refused to drink it.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 35, 'After they had nailed him to the cross, the soldiers gambled for his clothes by throwing dice.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 36, 'Then they sat around and kept guard as he hung there.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 37, 'A signboard was fastened to the cross above Jesus'' head, announcing the charge against him. It read: "This is Jesus, the King of the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 38, 'Two criminals were crucified with him, their crosses on either side of his.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 39, 'And the people passing by shouted abuse, shaking their heads in mockery.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 40, '"So! You can destroy the Temple and build it again in three days, can you? Well then, if you are the Son of God, save yourself and come down from the cross!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 41, 'The leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the other leaders also mocked Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 42, '"He saved others," they scoffed, "but he can''t save himself! So he is the king of Israel, is he? Let him come down from the cross, and we will believe in him!', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 43, 'He trusted God--let God show his approval by delivering him! For he said, ''I am the Son of God.''"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 44, 'And the criminals who were crucified with him also shouted the same insults at him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 45, 'At noon, darkness fell across the whole land until three o''clock.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 46, 'At about three o''clock, Jesus called out with a loud voice, "Eli, Eli, lema sabachthani?" which means, "My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 47, 'Some of the bystanders misunderstood and thought he was calling for the prophet Elijah.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 48, 'One of them ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, holding it up to him on a stick so he could drink.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 49, 'But the rest said, "Leave him alone. Let''s see whether Elijah will come and save him."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 50, 'Then Jesus shouted out again, and he gave up his spirit.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 51, 'At that moment the curtain in the Temple was torn in two, from top to bottom. The earth shook, rocks split apart,', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 52, 'and tombs opened. The bodies of many godly men and women who had died were raised from the dead', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 53, 'after Jesus'' resurrection. They left the cemetery, went into the holy city of Jerusalem, and appeared to many people.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 54, 'The Roman officer and the other soldiers at the crucifixion were terrified by the earthquake and all that had happened. They said, "Truly, this was the Son of God!"', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 55, 'And many women who had come from Galilee with Jesus to care for him were watching from a distance.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 56, 'Among them were Mary Magdalene, Mary (the mother of James and Joseph), and Zebedee''s wife, the mother of James and John.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 57, 'As evening approached, Joseph, a rich man from Arimathea who was one of Jesus'' followers,', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 58, 'went to Pilate and asked for Jesus'' body. And Pilate issued an order to release it to him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 59, 'Joseph took the body and wrapped it in a long linen cloth.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 60, 'He placed it in his own new tomb, which had been carved out of the rock. Then he rolled a great stone across the entrance as he left.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 61, 'Both Mary Magdalene and the other Mary were sitting nearby watching.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 62, 'The next day--on the first day of the Passover ceremonies--the leading priests and Pharisees went to see Pilate.', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 63, 'They told him, "Sir, we remember what that deceiver once said while he was still alive: ''After three days I will be raised from the dead.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 64, 'So we request that you seal the tomb until the third day. This will prevent his disciples from coming and stealing his body and then telling everyone he came back to life! If that happens, we''ll be worse off than we were at first."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 65, 'Pilate replied, "Take guards and secure it the best you can."', 'NLT'),
(44, 27, 66, 'So they sealed the tomb and posted guards to protect it.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 1, 'Early on Sunday morning, as the new day was dawning, Mary Magdalene and the other Mary went out to see the tomb.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 2, 'Suddenly there was a great earthquake, because an angel of the Lord came down from heaven and rolled aside the stone and sat on it.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 3, 'His face shone like lightning, and his clothing was as white as snow.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 4, 'The guards shook with fear when they saw him, and they fell into a dead faint.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 5, 'Then the angel spoke to the women. "Don''t be afraid!" he said. "I know you are looking for Jesus, who was crucified.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 6, 'He isn''t here! He has been raised from the dead, just as he said would happen. Come, see where his body was lying.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 7, 'And now, go quickly and tell his disciples he has been raised from the dead, and he is going ahead of you to Galilee. You will see him there. Remember, I have told you."', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 8, 'The women ran quickly from the tomb. They were very frightened but also filled with great joy, and they rushed to find the disciples to give them the angel''s message.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 9, 'And as they went, Jesus met them. "Greetings!" he said. And they ran to him, held his feet, and worshiped him.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 10, 'Then Jesus said to them, "Don''t be afraid! Go tell my brothers to leave for Galilee, and they will see me there."', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 11, 'As the women were on their way into the city, some of the men who had been guarding the tomb went to the leading priests and told them what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 12, 'A meeting of all the religious leaders was called, and they decided to bribe the soldiers.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 13, 'They told the soldiers, "You must say, ''Jesus'' disciples came during the night while we were sleeping, and they stole his body.''', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 14, 'If the governor hears about it, we''ll stand up for you and everything will be all right."', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 15, 'So the guards accepted the bribe and said what they were told to say. Their story spread widely among the Jews, and they still tell it today.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 16, 'Then the eleven disciples left for Galilee, going to the mountain where Jesus had told them to go.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 17, 'When they saw him, they worshiped him--but some of them still doubted!', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 18, 'Jesus came and told his disciples, "I have been given complete authority in heaven and on earth.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 19, 'Therefore, go and make disciples of all the nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(44, 28, 20, 'Teach these new disciples to obey all the commands I have given you. And be sure of this: I am with you always, even to the end of the age."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 1, 'Here begins the Good News about Jesus the Messiah, the Son of God.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 2, 'In the book of the prophet Isaiah, God said, "Look, I am sending my messenger before you, and he will prepare your way.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 3, 'He is a voice shouting in the wilderness: ''Prepare a pathway for the Lord''s coming! Make a straight road for him!''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 4, 'This messenger was John the Baptist. He lived in the wilderness and was preaching that people should be baptized to show that they had turned from their sins and turned to God to be forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 5, 'People from Jerusalem and from all over Judea traveled out into the wilderness to see and hear John. And when they confessed their sins, he baptized them in the Jordan River.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 6, 'His clothes were woven from camel hair, and he wore a leather belt; his food was locusts and wild honey.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 7, 'He announced: "Someone is coming soon who is far greater than I am--so much greater that I am not even worthy to be his slave.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 8, 'I baptize you with water, but he will baptize you with the Holy Spirit!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 9, 'One day Jesus came from Nazareth in Galilee, and he was baptized by John in the Jordan River.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 10, 'And when Jesus came up out of the water, he saw the heavens split open and the Holy Spirit descending like a dove on him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 11, 'And a voice came from heaven saying, "You are my beloved Son, and I am fully pleased with you."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 12, 'Immediately the Holy Spirit compelled Jesus to go into the wilderness.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 13, 'He was there for forty days, being tempted by Satan. He was out among the wild animals, and angels took care of him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 14, 'Later on, after John was arrested by Herod Antipas, Jesus went to Galilee to preach God''s Good News.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 15, '"At last the time has come!" he announced. "The Kingdom of God is near! Turn from your sins and believe this Good News!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 16, 'One day as Jesus was walking along the shores of the Sea of Galilee, he saw Simon and his brother, Andrew, fishing with a net, for they were commercial fishermen.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 17, 'Jesus called out to them, "Come, be my disciples, and I will show you how to fish for people!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 18, 'And they left their nets at once and went with him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 19, 'A little farther up the shore Jesus saw Zebedee''s sons, James and John, in a boat mending their nets.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 20, 'He called them, too, and immediately they left their father, Zebedee, in the boat with the hired men and went with him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 21, 'Jesus and his companions went to the town of Capernaum, and every Sabbath day he went into the synagogue and taught the people.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 22, 'They were amazed at his teaching, for he taught as one who had real authority--quite unlike the teachers of religious law.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 23, 'A man possessed by an evil spirit was in the synagogue,', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 24, 'and he began shouting, "Why are you bothering us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are--the Holy One sent from God!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 25, 'Jesus cut him short. "Be silent! Come out of the man."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 26, 'At that, the evil spirit screamed and threw the man into a convulsion, but then he left him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 27, 'Amazement gripped the audience, and they began to discuss what had happened. "What sort of new teaching is this?" they asked excitedly. "It has such authority! Even evil spirits obey his orders!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 28, 'The news of what he had done spread quickly through that entire area of Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 29, 'After Jesus and his disciples left the synagogue, they went over to Simon and Andrew''s home, and James and John were with them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 30, 'Simon''s mother-in-law was sick in bed with a high fever. They told Jesus about her right away.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 31, 'He went to her bedside, and as he took her by the hand and helped her to sit up, the fever suddenly left, and she got up and prepared a meal for them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 32, 'That evening at sunset, many sick and demon-possessed people were brought to Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 33, 'And a huge crowd of people from all over Capernaum gathered outside the door to watch.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 34, 'So Jesus healed great numbers of sick people who had many different kinds of diseases, and he ordered many demons to come out of their victims. But because they knew who he was, he refused to allow the demons to speak.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 35, 'The next morning Jesus awoke long before daybreak and went out alone into the wilderness to pray.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 36, 'Later Simon and the others went out to find him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 37, 'They said, "Everyone is asking for you."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 38, 'But he replied, "We must go on to other towns as well, and I will preach to them, too, because that is why I came."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 39, 'So he traveled throughout the region of Galilee, preaching in the synagogues and expelling demons from many people.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 40, 'A man with leprosy came and knelt in front of Jesus, begging to be healed. "If you want to, you can make me well again," he said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 41, 'Moved with pity, Jesus touched him. "I want to," he said. "Be healed!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 42, 'Instantly the leprosy disappeared--the man was healed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 43, 'Then Jesus sent him on his way and told him sternly,', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 44, '"Go right over to the priest and let him examine you. Don''t talk to anyone along the way. Take along the offering required in the law of Moses for those who have been healed of leprosy, so everyone will have proof of your healing."', 'NLT'),
(45, 1, 45, 'But as the man went on his way, he spread the news, telling everyone what had happened to him. As a result, such crowds soon surrounded Jesus that he couldn''t enter a town anywhere publicly. He had to stay out in the secluded places, and people from everywhere came to him there.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 1, 'Several days later Jesus returned to Capernaum, and the news of his arrival spread quickly through the town.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 2, 'Soon the house where he was staying was so packed with visitors that there wasn''t room for one more person, not even outside the door. And he preached the word to them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 3, 'Four men arrived carrying a paralyzed man on a mat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 4, 'They couldn''t get to Jesus through the crowd, so they dug through the clay roof above his head. Then they lowered the sick man on his mat, right down in front of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 5, 'Seeing their faith, Jesus said to the paralyzed man, "My son, your sins are forgiven."', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 6, 'But some of the teachers of religious law who were sitting there said to themselves,', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 7, '"What? This is blasphemy! Who but God can forgive sins!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 8, 'Jesus knew what they were discussing among themselves, so he said to them, "Why do you think this is blasphemy?', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 9, 'Is it easier to say to the paralyzed man, ''Your sins are forgiven'' or ''Get up, pick up your mat, and walk''?', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 10, 'I will prove that I, the Son of Man, have the authority on earth to forgive sins." Then Jesus turned to the paralyzed man and said,', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 11, '"Stand up, take your mat, and go on home, because you are healed!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 12, 'The man jumped up, took the mat, and pushed his way through the stunned onlookers. Then they all praised God. "We''ve never seen anything like this before!" they exclaimed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 13, 'Then Jesus went out to the lakeshore again and taught the crowds that gathered around him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 14, 'As he walked along, he saw Levi son of Alphaeus sitting at his tax-collection booth. "Come, be my disciple," Jesus said to him. So Levi got up and followed him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 15, 'That night Levi invited Jesus and his disciples to be his dinner guests, along with his fellow tax collectors and many other notorious sinners. (There were many people of this kind among the crowds that followed Jesus.)', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 16, 'But when some of the teachers of religious law who were Pharisees saw him eating with people like that, they said to his disciples, "Why does he eat with such scum?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 17, 'When Jesus heard this, he told them, "Healthy people don''t need a doctor--sick people do. I have come to call sinners, not those who think they are already good enough."', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 18, 'John''s disciples and the Pharisees sometimes fasted. One day some people came to Jesus and asked, "Why do John''s disciples and the Pharisees fast, but your disciples don''t fast?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 19, 'Jesus replied, "Do wedding guests fast while celebrating with the groom? Of course not. They can''t fast while they are with the groom.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 20, 'But someday he will be taken away from them, and then they will fast.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 21, 'And who would patch an old garment with unshrunk cloth? For the new patch shrinks and pulls away from the old cloth, leaving an even bigger hole than before.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 22, 'And no one puts new wine into old wineskins. The wine would burst the wineskins, spilling the wine and ruining the skins. New wine needs new wineskins."', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 23, 'One Sabbath day as Jesus was walking through some grainfields, his disciples began breaking off heads of wheat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 24, 'But the Pharisees said to Jesus, "They shouldn''t be doing that! It''s against the law to work by harvesting grain on the Sabbath."', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 25, 'But Jesus replied, "Haven''t you ever read in the Scriptures what King David did when he and his companions were hungry?', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 26, 'He went into the house of God (during the days when Abiathar was high priest), ate the special bread reserved for the priests alone, and then gave some to his companions. That was breaking the law, too."', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 27, 'Then he said to them, "The Sabbath was made to benefit people, and not people to benefit the Sabbath.', 'NLT'),
(45, 2, 28, 'And I, the Son of Man, am master even of the Sabbath!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 1, 'Jesus went into the synagogue again and noticed a man with a deformed hand.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 2, 'Since it was the Sabbath, Jesus'' enemies watched him closely. Would he heal the man''s hand on the Sabbath? If he did, they planned to condemn him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 3, 'Jesus said to the man, "Come and stand in front of everyone."', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 4, 'Then he turned to his critics and asked, "Is it legal to do good deeds on the Sabbath, or is it a day for doing harm? Is this a day to save life or to destroy it?" But they wouldn''t answer him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 5, 'He looked around at them angrily, because he was deeply disturbed by their hard hearts. Then he said to the man, "Reach out your hand." The man reached out his hand, and it became normal again!', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 6, 'At once the Pharisees went away and met with the supporters of Herod to discuss plans for killing Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 7, 'Jesus and his disciples went out to the lake, followed by a huge crowd from all over Galilee, Judea,', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 8, 'Jerusalem, Idumea, from east of the Jordan River, and even from as far away as Tyre and Sidon. The news about his miracles had spread far and wide, and vast numbers of people came to see him for themselves.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 9, 'Jesus instructed his disciples to bring around a boat and to have it ready in case he was crowded off the beach.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 10, 'There had been many healings that day. As a result, many sick people were crowding around him, trying to touch him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 11, 'And whenever those possessed by evil spirits caught sight of him, they would fall down in front of him shrieking, "You are the Son of God!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 12, 'But Jesus strictly warned them not to say who he was.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 13, 'Afterward Jesus went up on a mountain and called the ones he wanted to go with him. And they came to him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 14, 'Then he selected twelve of them to be his regular companions, calling them apostles. He sent them out to preach,', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 15, 'and he gave them authority to cast out demons.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 16, 'These are the names of the twelve he chose: Simon (he renamed him Peter),', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 17, 'James and John (the sons of Zebedee, but Jesus nicknamed them "Sons of Thunder" ),', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 18, 'Andrew, Philip, Bartholomew, Matthew, Thomas, James (son of Alphaeus), Thaddaeus, Simon (the Zealot ),', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 19, 'Judas Iscariot (who later betrayed him).', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 20, 'When Jesus returned to the house where he was staying, the crowds began to gather again, and soon he and his disciples couldn''t even find time to eat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 21, 'When his family heard what was happening, they tried to take him home with them. "He''s out of his mind," they said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 22, 'But the teachers of religious law who had arrived from Jerusalem said, "He''s possessed by Satan, the prince of demons. That''s where he gets the power to cast out demons."', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 23, 'Jesus called them over and said to them by way of illustration, "How can Satan cast out Satan?', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 24, 'A kingdom at war with itself will collapse.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 25, 'A home divided against itself is doomed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 26, 'And if Satan is fighting against himself, how can he stand? He would never survive.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 27, 'Let me illustrate this. You can''t enter a strong man''s house and rob him without first tying him up. Only then can his house be robbed!', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 28, '"I assure you that any sin can be forgiven, including blasphemy;', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 29, 'but anyone who blasphemes against the Holy Spirit will never be forgiven. It is an eternal sin."', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 30, 'He told them this because they were saying he had an evil spirit.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 31, 'Jesus'' mother and brothers arrived at the house where he was teaching. They stood outside and sent word for him to come out and talk with them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 32, 'There was a crowd around Jesus, and someone said, "Your mother and your brothers and sisters are outside, asking for you."', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 33, 'Jesus replied, "Who is my mother? Who are my brothers?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 34, 'Then he looked at those around him and said, "These are my mother and brothers.', 'NLT'),
(45, 3, 35, 'Anyone who does God''s will is my brother and sister and mother."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 1, 'Once again Jesus began teaching by the lakeshore. There was such a large crowd along the shore that he got into a boat and sat down and spoke from there.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 2, 'He began to teach the people by telling many stories such as this one:', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 3, '"Listen! A farmer went out to plant some seed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 4, 'As he scattered it across his field, some seed fell on a footpath, and the birds came and ate it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 5, 'Other seed fell on shallow soil with underlying rock. The plant sprang up quickly,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 6, 'but it soon wilted beneath the hot sun and died because the roots had no nourishment in the shallow soil.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 7, 'Other seed fell among thorns that shot up and choked out the tender blades so that it produced no grain.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 8, 'Still other seed fell on fertile soil and produced a crop that was thirty, sixty, and even a hundred times as much as had been planted." Then he said,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 9, '"Anyone who is willing to hear should listen and understand!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 10, 'Later, when Jesus was alone with the twelve disciples and with the others who were gathered around, they asked him, "What do your stories mean?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 11, 'He replied, "You are permitted to understand the secret about the Kingdom of God. But I am using these stories to conceal everything about it from outsiders,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 12, 'so that the Scriptures might be fulfilled: ''They see what I do, but they don''t perceive its meaning. They hear my words, but they don''t understand. So they will not turn from their sins and be forgiven.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 13, '"But if you can''t understand this story, how will you understand all the others I am going to tell?', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 14, 'The farmer I talked about is the one who brings God''s message to others.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 15, 'The seed that fell on the hard path represents those who hear the message, but then Satan comes at once and takes it away from them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 16, 'The rocky soil represents those who hear the message and receive it with joy.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 17, 'But like young plants in such soil, their roots don''t go very deep. At first they get along fine, but they wilt as soon as they have problems or are persecuted because they believe the word.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 18, 'The thorny ground represents those who hear and accept the Good News,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 19, 'but all too quickly the message is crowded out by the cares of this life, the lure of wealth, and the desire for nice things, so no crop is produced.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 20, 'But the good soil represents those who hear and accept God''s message and produce a huge harvest--thirty, sixty, or even a hundred times as much as had been planted."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 21, 'Then Jesus asked them, "Would anyone light a lamp and then put it under a basket or under a bed to shut out the light? Of course not! A lamp is placed on a stand, where its light will shine.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 22, '"Everything that is now hidden or secret will eventually be brought to light.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 23, 'Anyone who is willing to hear should listen and understand!', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 24, 'And be sure to pay attention to what you hear. The more you do this, the more you will understand--and even more, besides.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 25, 'To those who are open to my teaching, more understanding will be given. But to those who are not listening, even what they have will be taken away from them."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 26, 'Jesus also said, "Here is another illustration of what the Kingdom of God is like: A farmer planted seeds in a field,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 27, 'and then he went on with his other activities. As the days went by, the seeds sprouted and grew without the farmer''s help,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 28, 'because the earth produces crops on its own. First a leaf blade pushes through, then the heads of wheat are formed, and finally the grain ripens.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 29, 'And as soon as the grain is ready, the farmer comes and harvests it with a sickle."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 30, 'Jesus asked, "How can I describe the Kingdom of God? What story should I use to illustrate it?', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 31, 'It is like a tiny mustard seed. Though this is one of the smallest of seeds,', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 32, 'it grows to become one of the largest of plants, with long branches where birds can come and find shelter."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 33, 'He used many such stories and illustrations to teach the people as much as they were able to understand.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 34, 'In fact, in his public teaching he taught only with parables, but afterward when he was alone with his disciples, he explained the meaning to them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 35, 'As evening came, Jesus said to his disciples, "Let''s cross to the other side of the lake."', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 36, 'He was already in the boat, so they started out, leaving the crowds behind (although other boats followed).', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 37, 'But soon a fierce storm arose. High waves began to break into the boat until it was nearly full of water.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 38, 'Jesus was sleeping at the back of the boat with his head on a cushion. Frantically they woke him up, shouting, "Teacher, don''t you even care that we are going to drown?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 39, 'When he woke up, he rebuked the wind and said to the water, "Quiet down!" Suddenly the wind stopped, and there was a great calm.', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 40, 'And he asked them, "Why are you so afraid? Do you still not have faith in me?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 4, 41, 'And they were filled with awe and said among themselves, "Who is this man, that even the wind and waves obey him?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 1, 'So they arrived at the other side of the lake, in the land of the Gerasenes.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 2, 'Just as Jesus was climbing from the boat, a man possessed by an evil spirit ran out from a cemetery to meet him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 3, 'This man lived among the tombs and could not be restrained, even with a chain.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 4, 'Whenever he was put into chains and shackles--as he often was--he snapped the chains from his wrists and smashed the shackles. No one was strong enough to control him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 5, 'All day long and throughout the night, he would wander among the tombs and in the hills, screaming and hitting himself with stones.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 6, 'When Jesus was still some distance away, the man saw him. He ran to meet Jesus and fell down before him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 7, 'He gave a terrible scream, shrieking, "Why are you bothering me, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? For God''s sake, don''t torture me!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 8, 'For Jesus had already said to the spirit, "Come out of the man, you evil spirit."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 9, 'Then Jesus asked, "What is your name?" And the spirit replied, "Legion, because there are many of us here inside this man."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 10, 'Then the spirits begged him again and again not to send them to some distant place.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 11, 'There happened to be a large herd of pigs feeding on the hillside nearby.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 12, '"Send us into those pigs," the evil spirits begged.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 13, 'Jesus gave them permission. So the evil spirits came out of the man and entered the pigs, and the entire herd of two thousand pigs plunged down the steep hillside into the lake, where they drowned.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 14, 'The herdsmen fled to the nearby city and the surrounding countryside, spreading the news as they ran. Everyone rushed out to see for themselves.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 15, 'A crowd soon gathered around Jesus, but they were frightened when they saw the man who had been demon possessed, for he was sitting there fully clothed and perfectly sane.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 16, 'Those who had seen what happened to the man and to the pigs told everyone about it,', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 17, 'and the crowd began pleading with Jesus to go away and leave them alone.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 18, 'When Jesus got back into the boat, the man who had been demon possessed begged to go, too.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 19, 'But Jesus said, "No, go home to your friends, and tell them what wonderful things the Lord has done for you and how merciful he has been."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 20, 'So the man started off to visit the Ten Towns of that region and began to tell everyone about the great things Jesus had done for him; and everyone was amazed at what he told them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 21, 'When Jesus went back across to the other side of the lake, a large crowd gathered around him on the shore.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 22, 'A leader of the local synagogue, whose name was Jairus, came and fell down before him,', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 23, 'pleading with him to heal his little daughter. "She is about to die," he said in desperation. "Please come and place your hands on her; heal her so she can live."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 24, 'Jesus went with him, and the crowd thronged behind.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 25, 'And there was a woman in the crowd who had had a hemorrhage for twelve years.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 26, 'She had suffered a great deal from many doctors through the years and had spent everything she had to pay them, but she had gotten no better. In fact, she was worse.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 27, 'She had heard about Jesus, so she came up behind him through the crowd and touched the fringe of his robe.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 28, 'For she thought to herself, "If I can just touch his clothing, I will be healed."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 29, 'Immediately the bleeding stopped, and she could feel that she had been healed!', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 30, 'Jesus realized at once that healing power had gone out from him, so he turned around in the crowd and asked, "Who touched my clothes?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 31, 'His disciples said to him, "All this crowd is pressing around you. How can you ask, ''Who touched me?''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 32, 'But he kept on looking around to see who had done it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 33, 'Then the frightened woman, trembling at the realization of what had happened to her, came and fell at his feet and told him what she had done.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 34, 'And he said to her, "Daughter, your faith has made you well. Go in peace. You have been healed."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 35, 'While he was still speaking to her, messengers arrived from Jairus''s home with the message, "Your daughter is dead. There''s no use troubling the Teacher now."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 36, 'But Jesus ignored their comments and said to Jairus, "Don''t be afraid. Just trust me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 37, 'Then Jesus stopped the crowd and wouldn''t let anyone go with him except Peter and James and John.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 38, 'When they came to the home of the synagogue leader, Jesus saw the commotion and the weeping and wailing.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 39, 'He went inside and spoke to the people. "Why all this weeping and commotion?" he asked. "The child isn''t dead; she is only asleep."', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 40, 'The crowd laughed at him, but he told them all to go outside. Then he took the girl''s father and mother and his three disciples into the room where the girl was lying.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 41, 'Holding her hand, he said to her, "Get up, little girl!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 42, 'And the girl, who was twelve years old, immediately stood up and walked around! Her parents were absolutely overwhelmed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 5, 43, 'Jesus commanded them not to tell anyone what had happened, and he told them to give her something to eat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 1, 'Jesus left that part of the country and returned with his disciples to Nazareth, his hometown.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 2, 'The next Sabbath he began teaching in the synagogue, and many who heard him were astonished. They asked, "Where did he get all his wisdom and the power to perform such miracles?', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 3, 'He''s just the carpenter, the son of Mary and brother of James, Joseph, Judas, and Simon. And his sisters live right here among us." They were deeply offended and refused to believe in him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 4, 'Then Jesus told them, "A prophet is honored everywhere except in his own hometown and among his relatives and his own family."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 5, 'And because of their unbelief, he couldn''t do any mighty miracles among them except to place his hands on a few sick people and heal them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 6, 'And he was amazed at their unbelief. Then Jesus went out from village to village, teaching.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 7, 'And he called his twelve disciples together and sent them out two by two, with authority to cast out evil spirits.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 8, 'He told them to take nothing with them except a walking stick--no food, no traveler''s bag, no money.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 9, 'He told them to wear sandals but not to take even an extra coat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 10, '"When you enter each village, be a guest in only one home," he said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 11, '"And if a village won''t welcome you or listen to you, shake off its dust from your feet as you leave. It is a sign that you have abandoned that village to its fate."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 12, 'So the disciples went out, telling all they met to turn from their sins.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 13, 'And they cast out many demons and healed many sick people, anointing them with olive oil.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 14, 'Herod Antipas, the king, soon heard about Jesus, because people everywhere were talking about him. Some were saying, "This must be John the Baptist come back to life again. That is why he can do such miracles."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 15, 'Others thought Jesus was the ancient prophet Elijah. Still others thought he was a prophet like the other great prophets of the past.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 16, 'When Herod heard about Jesus, he said, "John, the man I beheaded, has come back from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 17, 'For Herod had sent soldiers to arrest and imprison John as a favor to Herodias. She had been his brother Philip''s wife, but Herod had married her.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 18, 'John kept telling Herod, "It is illegal for you to marry your brother''s wife."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 19, 'Herodias was enraged and wanted John killed in revenge, but without Herod''s approval she was powerless.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 20, 'And Herod respected John, knowing that he was a good and holy man, so he kept him under his protection. Herod was disturbed whenever he talked with John, but even so, he liked to listen to him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 21, 'Herodias''s chance finally came. It was Herod''s birthday, and he gave a party for his palace aides, army officers, and the leading citizens of Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 22, 'Then his daughter, also named Herodias, came in and performed a dance that greatly pleased them all. "Ask me for anything you like," the king said to the girl, "and I will give it to you."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 23, 'Then he promised, "I will give you whatever you ask, up to half of my kingdom!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 24, 'She went out and asked her mother, "What should I ask for?" Her mother told her, "Ask for John the Baptist''s head!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 25, 'So the girl hurried back to the king and told him, "I want the head of John the Baptist, right now, on a tray!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 26, 'Then the king was very sorry, but he was embarrassed to break his oath in front of his guests.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 27, 'So he sent an executioner to the prison to cut off John''s head and bring it to him. The soldier beheaded John in the prison,', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 28, 'brought his head on a tray, and gave it to the girl, who took it to her mother.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 29, 'When John''s disciples heard what had happened, they came for his body and buried it in a tomb.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 30, 'The apostles returned to Jesus from their ministry tour and told him all they had done and what they had taught.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 31, 'Then Jesus said, "Let''s get away from the crowds for a while and rest." There were so many people coming and going that Jesus and his apostles didn''t even have time to eat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 32, 'They left by boat for a quieter spot.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 33, 'But many people saw them leaving, and people from many towns ran ahead along the shore and met them as they landed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 34, 'A vast crowd was there as he stepped from the boat, and he had compassion on them because they were like sheep without a shepherd. So he taught them many things.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 35, 'Late in the afternoon his disciples came to him and said, "This is a desolate place, and it is getting late.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 36, 'Send the crowds away so they can go to the nearby farms and villages and buy themselves some food."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 37, 'But Jesus said, "You feed them.With what?" they asked. "It would take a small fortune to buy food for all this crowd!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 38, '"How much food do you have?" he asked. "Go and find out." They came back and reported, "We have five loaves of bread and two fish."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 39, 'Then Jesus told the crowd to sit down in groups on the green grass.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 40, 'So they sat in groups of fifty or a hundred.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 41, 'Jesus took the five loaves and two fish, looked up toward heaven, and asked God''s blessing on the food. Breaking the loaves into pieces, he kept giving the bread and fish to the disciples to give to the people.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 42, 'They all ate as much as they wanted,', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 43, 'and they picked up twelve baskets of leftover bread and fish.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 44, 'Five thousand men had eaten from those five loaves!', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 45, 'Immediately after this, Jesus made his disciples get back into the boat and head out across the lake to Bethsaida, while he sent the people home.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 46, 'Afterward he went up into the hills by himself to pray.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 47, 'During the night, the disciples were in their boat out in the middle of the lake, and Jesus was alone on land.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 48, 'He saw that they were in serious trouble, rowing hard and struggling against the wind and waves. About three o''clock in the morning he came to them, walking on the water. He started to go past them,', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 49, 'but when they saw him walking on the water, they screamed in terror, thinking he was a ghost.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 50, 'They were all terrified when they saw him. But Jesus spoke to them at once. "It''s all right," he said. "I am here! Don''t be afraid."', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 51, 'Then he climbed into the boat, and the wind stopped. They were astonished at what they saw.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 52, 'They still didn''t understand the significance of the miracle of the multiplied loaves, for their hearts were hard and they did not believe.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 53, 'When they arrived at Gennesaret on the other side of the lake, they anchored the boat', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 54, 'and climbed out. The people standing there recognized him at once,', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 55, 'and they ran throughout the whole area and began carrying sick people to him on mats.', 'NLT'),
(45, 6, 56, 'Wherever he went--in villages and cities and out on the farms--they laid the sick in the market plazas and streets. The sick begged him to let them at least touch the fringe of his robe, and all who touched it were healed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 1, 'One day some Pharisees and teachers of religious law arrived from Jerusalem to confront Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 2, 'They noticed that some of Jesus'' disciples failed to follow the usual Jewish ritual of hand washing before eating.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 3, '(The Jews, especially the Pharisees, do not eat until they have poured water over their cupped hands, as required by their ancient traditions.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 4, 'Similarly, they eat nothing bought from the market unless they have immersed their hands in water. This is but one of many traditions they have clung to--such as their ceremony of washing cups, pitchers, and kettles. )', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 5, 'So the Pharisees and teachers of religious law asked him, "Why don''t your disciples follow our age-old customs? For they eat without first performing the hand-washing ceremony."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 6, 'Jesus replied, "You hypocrites! Isaiah was prophesying about you when he said,', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 7, '''These people honor me with their lips, but their hearts are far away. Their worship is a farce, for they replace God''s commands with their own man-made teachings.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 8, 'For you ignore God''s specific laws and substitute your own traditions."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 9, 'Then he said, "You reject God''s laws in order to hold on to your own traditions.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 10, 'For instance, Moses gave you this law from God: ''Honor your father and mother,'' and ''Anyone who speaks evil of father or mother must be put to death.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 11, 'But you say it is all right for people to say to their parents, ''Sorry, I can''t help you. For I have vowed to give to God what I could have given to you.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 12, 'You let them disregard their needy parents.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 13, 'As such, you break the law of God in order to protect your own tradition. And this is only one example. There are many, many others."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 14, 'Then Jesus called to the crowd to come and hear. "All of you listen," he said, "and try to understand.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 15, 'You are not defiled by what you eat; you are defiled by what you say and do! "', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 16, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 17, 'Then Jesus went into a house to get away from the crowds, and his disciples asked him what he meant by the statement he had made.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 18, '"Don''t you understand either?" he asked. "Can''t you see that what you eat won''t defile you?', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 19, 'Food doesn''t come in contact with your heart, but only passes through the stomach and then comes out again." (By saying this, he showed that every kind of food is acceptable.)', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 20, 'And then he added, "It is the thought-life that defiles you.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 21, 'For from within, out of a person''s heart, come evil thoughts, sexual immorality, theft, murder,', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 22, 'adultery, greed, wickedness, deceit, eagerness for lustful pleasure, envy, slander, pride, and foolishness.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 23, 'All these vile things come from within; they are what defile you and make you unacceptable to God."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 24, 'Then Jesus left Galilee and went north to the region of Tyre. He tried to keep it secret that he was there, but he couldn''t. As usual, the news of his arrival spread fast.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 25, 'Right away a woman came to him whose little girl was possessed by an evil spirit. She had heard about Jesus, and now she came and fell at his feet.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 26, 'She begged him to release her child from the demon''s control. Since she was a Gentile, born in Syrian Phoenicia,', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 27, 'Jesus told her, "First I should help my own family, the Jews. It isn''t right to take food from the children and throw it to the dogs."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 28, 'She replied, "That''s true, Lord, but even the dogs under the table are given some crumbs from the children''s plates."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 29, '"Good answer!" he said. "And because you have answered so well, I have healed your daughter."', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 30, 'And when she arrived home, her little girl was lying quietly in bed, and the demon was gone.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 31, 'Jesus left Tyre and went to Sidon, then back to the Sea of Galilee and the region of the Ten Towns.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 32, 'A deaf man with a speech impediment was brought to him, and the people begged Jesus to lay his hands on the man to heal him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 33, 'Jesus led him to a private place away from the crowd. He put his fingers into the man''s ears. Then, spitting onto his own fingers, he touched the man''s tongue with the spittle.', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 34, 'And looking up to heaven, he sighed and commanded, "Be opened!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 35, 'Instantly the man could hear perfectly and speak plainly!', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 36, 'Jesus told the crowd not to tell anyone, but the more he told them not to, the more they spread the news,', 'NLT'),
(45, 7, 37, 'for they were completely amazed. Again and again they said, "Everything he does is wonderful. He even heals those who are deaf and mute."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 1, 'About this time another great crowd had gathered, and the people ran out of food again. Jesus called his disciples and told them,', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 2, '"I feel sorry for these people. They have been here with me for three days, and they have nothing left to eat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 3, 'And if I send them home without feeding them, they will faint along the road. For some of them have come a long distance."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 4, '"How are we supposed to find enough food for them here in the wilderness?" his disciples asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 5, '"How many loaves of bread do you have?" he asked. "Seven," they replied.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 6, 'So Jesus told all the people to sit down on the ground. Then he took the seven loaves, thanked God for them, broke them into pieces, and gave them to his disciples, who distributed the bread to the crowd.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 7, 'A few small fish were found, too, so Jesus also blessed these and told the disciples to pass them out.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 8, 'They ate until they were full, and when the scraps were picked up, there were seven large baskets of food left over!', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 9, 'There were about four thousand people in the crowd that day, and he sent them home after they had eaten.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 10, 'Immediately after this, he got into a boat with his disciples and crossed over to the region of Dalmanutha.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 11, 'When the Pharisees heard that Jesus had arrived, they came to argue with him. Testing him to see if he was from God, they demanded, "Give us a miraculous sign from heaven to prove yourself."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 12, 'When he heard this, he sighed deeply and said, "Why do you people keep demanding a miraculous sign? I assure you, I will not give this generation any such sign."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 13, 'So he got back into the boat and left them, and he crossed to the other side of the lake.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 14, 'But the disciples discovered they had forgotten to bring any food, so there was only one loaf of bread with them in the boat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 15, 'As they were crossing the lake, Jesus warned them, "Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and of Herod."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 16, 'They decided he was saying this because they hadn''t brought any bread.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 17, 'Jesus knew what they were thinking, so he said, "Why are you so worried about having no food? Won''t you ever learn or understand? Are your hearts too hard to take it in?', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 18, '''You have eyes--can''t you see? You have ears--can''t you hear?'' Don''t you remember anything at all?', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 19, 'What about the five thousand men I fed with five loaves of bread? How many baskets of leftovers did you pick up afterward?Twelve," they said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 20, '"And when I fed the four thousand with seven loaves, how many large baskets of leftovers did you pick up?Seven," they said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 21, '"Don''t you understand even yet?" he asked them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 22, 'When they arrived at Bethsaida, some people brought a blind man to Jesus, and they begged him to touch and heal the man.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 23, 'Jesus took the blind man by the hand and led him out of the village. Then, spitting on the man''s eyes, he laid his hands on him and asked, "Can you see anything now?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 24, 'The man looked around. "Yes," he said, "I see people, but I can''t see them very clearly. They look like trees walking around."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 25, 'Then Jesus placed his hands over the man''s eyes again. As the man stared intently, his sight was completely restored, and he could see everything clearly.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 26, 'Jesus sent him home, saying, "Don''t go back into the village on your way home."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 27, 'Jesus and his disciples left Galilee and went up to the villages of Caesarea Philippi. As they were walking along, he asked them, "Who do people say I am?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 28, '"Well," they replied, "some say John the Baptist, some say Elijah, and others say you are one of the other prophets."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 29, 'Then Jesus asked, "Who do you say I am?" Peter replied, "You are the Messiah."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 30, 'But Jesus warned them not to tell anyone about him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 31, 'Then Jesus began to tell them that he, the Son of Man, would suffer many terrible things and be rejected by the leaders, the leading priests, and the teachers of religious law. He would be killed, and three days later he would rise again.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 32, 'As he talked about this openly with his disciples, Peter took him aside and told him he shouldn''t say things like that.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 33, 'Jesus turned and looked at his disciples and then said to Peter very sternly, "Get away from me, Satan! You are seeing things merely from a human point of view, not from God''s."', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 34, 'Then he called his disciples and the crowds to come over and listen. "If any of you wants to be my follower," he told them, "you must put aside your selfish ambition, shoulder your cross, and follow me.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 35, 'If you try to keep your life for yourself, you will lose it. But if you give up your life for my sake and for the sake of the Good News, you will find true life.', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 36, 'And how do you benefit if you gain the whole world but lose your own soul in the process?', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 37, 'Is anything worth more than your soul?', 'NLT'),
(45, 8, 38, 'If a person is ashamed of me and my message in these adulterous and sinful days, I, the Son of Man, will be ashamed of that person when I return in the glory of my Father with the holy angels."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 1, 'Jesus went on to say, "I assure you that some of you standing here right now will not die before you see the Kingdom of God arrive in great power!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 2, 'Six days later Jesus took Peter, James, and John to the top of a mountain. No one else was there. As the men watched, Jesus'' appearance changed,', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 3, 'and his clothing became dazzling white, far whiter than any earthly process could ever make it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 4, 'Then Elijah and Moses appeared and began talking with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 5, '"Teacher, this is wonderful!" Peter exclaimed. "We will make three shrines--one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 6, 'He didn''t really know what to say, for they were all terribly afraid.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 7, 'Then a cloud came over them, and a voice from the cloud said, "This is my beloved Son. Listen to him."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 8, 'Suddenly they looked around, and Moses and Elijah were gone, and only Jesus was with them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 9, 'As they descended the mountainside, he told them not to tell anyone what they had seen until he, the Son of Man, had risen from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 10, 'So they kept it to themselves, but they often asked each other what he meant by "rising from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 11, 'Now they began asking him, "Why do the teachers of religious law insist that Elijah must return before the Messiah comes?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 12, 'Jesus responded, "Elijah is indeed coming first to set everything in order. Why then is it written in the Scriptures that the Son of Man must suffer and be treated with utter contempt?', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 13, 'But I tell you, Elijah has already come, and he was badly mistreated, just as the Scriptures predicted."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 14, 'At the foot of the mountain they found a great crowd surrounding the other disciples, as some teachers of religious law were arguing with them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 15, 'The crowd watched Jesus in awe as he came toward them, and then they ran to greet him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 16, '"What is all this arguing about?" he asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 17, 'One of the men in the crowd spoke up and said, "Teacher, I brought my son for you to heal him. He can''t speak because he is possessed by an evil spirit that won''t let him talk.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 18, 'And whenever this evil spirit seizes him, it throws him violently to the ground and makes him foam at the mouth and grind his teeth and become rigid. So I asked your disciples to cast out the evil spirit, but they couldn''t do it."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 19, 'Jesus said to them, "You faithless people! How long must I be with you until you believe? How long must I put up with you? Bring the boy to me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 20, 'So they brought the boy. But when the evil spirit saw Jesus, it threw the child into a violent convulsion, and he fell to the ground, writhing and foaming at the mouth.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 21, '"How long has this been happening?" Jesus asked the boy''s father. He replied, "Since he was very small.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 22, 'The evil spirit often makes him fall into the fire or into water, trying to kill him. Have mercy on us and help us. Do something if you can."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 23, '"What do you mean, ''If I can''?" Jesus asked. "Anything is possible if a person believes."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 24, 'The father instantly replied, "I do believe, but help me not to doubt!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 25, 'When Jesus saw that the crowd of onlookers was growing, he rebuked the evil spirit. "Spirit of deafness and muteness," he said, "I command you to come out of this child and never enter him again!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 26, 'Then the spirit screamed and threw the boy into another violent convulsion and left him. The boy lay there motionless, and he appeared to be dead. A murmur ran through the crowd, "He''s dead."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 27, 'But Jesus took him by the hand and helped him to his feet, and he stood up.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 28, 'Afterward, when Jesus was alone in the house with his disciples, they asked him, "Why couldn''t we cast out that evil spirit?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 29, 'Jesus replied, "This kind can be cast out only by prayer. "', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 30, 'Leaving that region, they traveled through Galilee. Jesus tried to avoid all publicity', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 31, 'in order to spend more time with his disciples and teach them. He said to them, "The Son of Man is going to be betrayed. He will be killed, but three days later he will rise from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 32, 'But they didn''t understand what he was saying, and they were afraid to ask him what he meant.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 33, 'After they arrived at Capernaum, Jesus and his disciples settled in the house where they would be staying. Jesus asked them, "What were you discussing out on the road?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 34, 'But they didn''t answer, because they had been arguing about which of them was the greatest.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 35, 'He sat down and called the twelve disciples over to him. Then he said, "Anyone who wants to be the first must take last place and be the servant of everyone else."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 36, 'Then he put a little child among them. Taking the child in his arms, he said to them,', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 37, '"Anyone who welcomes a little child like this on my behalf welcomes me, and anyone who welcomes me welcomes my Father who sent me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 38, 'John said to Jesus, "Teacher, we saw a man using your name to cast out demons, but we told him to stop because he isn''t one of our group."', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 39, '"Don''t stop him!" Jesus said. "No one who performs miracles in my name will soon be able to speak evil of me.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 40, 'Anyone who is not against us is for us.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 41, 'If anyone gives you even a cup of water because you belong to the Messiah, I assure you, that person will be rewarded.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 42, '"But if anyone causes one of these little ones who trusts in me to lose faith, it would be better for that person to be thrown into the sea with a large millstone tied around the neck.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 43, 'If your hand causes you to sin, cut it off. It is better to enter heaven with only one hand than to go into the unquenchable fires of hell with two hands.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 44, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 45, 'If your foot causes you to sin, cut it off. It is better to enter heaven with only one foot than to be thrown into hell with two feet.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 46, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 47, 'And if your eye causes you to sin, gouge it out. It is better to enter the Kingdom of God half blind than to have two eyes and be thrown into hell,', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 48, '''where the worm never dies and the fire never goes out.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 49, '"For everyone will be purified with fire.', 'NLT'),
(45, 9, 50, 'Salt is good for seasoning. But if it loses its flavor, how do you make it salty again? You must have the qualities of salt among yourselves and live in peace with each other."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 1, 'Then Jesus left Capernaum and went southward to the region of Judea and into the area east of the Jordan River. As always there were the crowds, and as usual he taught them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 2, 'Some Pharisees came and tried to trap him with this question: "Should a man be allowed to divorce his wife?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 3, '"What did Moses say about divorce?" Jesus asked them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 4, '"Well, he permitted it," they replied. "He said a man merely has to write his wife an official letter of divorce and send her away."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 5, 'But Jesus responded, "He wrote those instructions only as a concession to your hard-hearted wickedness.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 6, 'But God''s plan was seen from the beginning of creation, for ''He made them male and female.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 7, '''This explains why a man leaves his father and mother and is joined to his wife,', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 8, 'and the two are united into one.'' Since they are no longer two but one,', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 9, 'let no one separate them, for God has joined them together."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 10, 'Later, when he was alone with his disciples in the house, they brought up the subject again.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 11, 'He told them, "Whoever divorces his wife and marries someone else commits adultery against her.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 12, 'And if a woman divorces her husband and remarries, she commits adultery."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 13, 'One day some parents brought their children to Jesus so he could touch them and bless them, but the disciples told them not to bother him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 14, 'But when Jesus saw what was happening, he was very displeased with his disciples. He said to them, "Let the children come to me. Don''t stop them! For the Kingdom of God belongs to such as these.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 15, 'I assure you, anyone who doesn''t have their kind of faith will never get into the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 16, 'Then he took the children into his arms and placed his hands on their heads and blessed them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 17, 'As he was starting out on a trip, a man came running up to Jesus, knelt down, and asked, "Good Teacher, what should I do to get eternal life?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 18, '"Why do you call me good?" Jesus asked. "Only God is truly good.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 19, 'But as for your question, you know the commandments: ''Do not murder. Do not commit adultery. Do not steal. Do not testify falsely. Do not cheat. Honor your father and mother.''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 20, '"Teacher," the man replied, "I''ve obeyed all these commandments since I was a child."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 21, 'Jesus felt genuine love for this man as he looked at him. "You lack only one thing," he told him. "Go and sell all you have and give the money to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 22, 'At this, the man''s face fell, and he went sadly away because he had many possessions.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 23, 'Jesus looked around and said to his disciples, "How hard it is for rich people to get into the Kingdom of God!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 24, 'This amazed them. But Jesus said again, "Dear children, it is very hard to get into the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 25, 'It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of God!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 26, 'The disciples were astounded. "Then who in the world can be saved?" they asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 27, 'Jesus looked at them intently and said, "Humanly speaking, it is impossible. But not with God. Everything is possible with God."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 28, 'Then Peter began to mention all that he and the other disciples had left behind. "We''ve given up everything to follow you," he said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 29, 'And Jesus replied, "I assure you that everyone who has given up house or brothers or sisters or mother or father or children or property, for my sake and for the Good News,', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 30, 'will receive now in return, a hundred times over, houses, brothers, sisters, mothers, children, and property--with persecutions. And in the world to come they will have eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 31, 'But many who seem to be important now will be the least important then, and those who are considered least here will be the greatest then. "', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 32, 'They were now on the way to Jerusalem, and Jesus was walking ahead of them. The disciples were filled with dread and the people following behind were overwhelmed with fear. Taking the twelve disciples aside, Jesus once more began to describe everything that was about to happen to him in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 33, '"When we get to Jerusalem," he told them, "the Son of Man will be betrayed to the leading priests and the teachers of religious law. They will sentence him to die and hand him over to the Romans.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 34, 'They will mock him, spit on him, beat him with their whips, and kill him, but after three days he will rise again."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 35, 'Then James and John, the sons of Zebedee, came over and spoke to him. "Teacher," they said, "we want you to do us a favor."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 36, '"What is it?" he asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 37, '"In your glorious Kingdom, we want to sit in places of honor next to you," they said, "one at your right and the other at your left."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 38, 'But Jesus answered, "You don''t know what you are asking! Are you able to drink from the bitter cup of sorrow I am about to drink? Are you able to be baptized with the baptism of suffering I must be baptized with?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 39, '"Oh yes," they said, "we are able!" And Jesus said, "You will indeed drink from my cup and be baptized with my baptism,', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 40, 'but I have no right to say who will sit on the thrones next to mine. God has prepared those places for the ones he has chosen."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 41, 'When the ten other disciples discovered what James and John had asked, they were indignant.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 42, 'So Jesus called them together and said, "You know that in this world kings are tyrants, and officials lord it over the people beneath them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 43, 'But among you it should be quite different. Whoever wants to be a leader among you must be your servant,', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 44, 'and whoever wants to be first must be the slave of all.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 45, 'For even I, the Son of Man, came here not to be served but to serve others, and to give my life as a ransom for many."', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 46, 'And so they reached Jericho. Later, as Jesus and his disciples left town, a great crowd was following. A blind beggar named Bartimaeus (son of Timaeus) was sitting beside the road as Jesus was going by.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 47, 'When Bartimaeus heard that Jesus from Nazareth was nearby, he began to shout out, "Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 48, '"Be quiet!" some of the people yelled at him. But he only shouted louder, "Son of David, have mercy on me!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 49, 'When Jesus heard him, he stopped and said, "Tell him to come here." So they called the blind man. "Cheer up," they said. "Come on, he''s calling you!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 50, 'Bartimaeus threw aside his coat, jumped up, and came to Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 51, '"What do you want me to do for you?" Jesus asked. "Teacher," the blind man said, "I want to see!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 10, 52, 'And Jesus said to him, "Go your way. Your faith has healed you." And instantly the blind man could see! Then he followed Jesus down the road.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 1, 'As Jesus and his disciples approached Jerusalem, they came to the towns of Bethphage and Bethany, on the Mount of Olives. Jesus sent two of them on ahead.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 2, '"Go into that village over there," he told them, "and as soon as you enter it, you will see a colt tied there that has never been ridden. Untie it and bring it here.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 3, 'If anyone asks what you are doing, just say, ''The Lord needs it and will return it soon.''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 4, 'The two disciples left and found the colt standing in the street, tied outside a house.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 5, 'As they were untying it, some bystanders demanded, "What are you doing, untying that colt?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 6, 'They said what Jesus had told them to say, and they were permitted to take it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 7, 'Then they brought the colt to Jesus and threw their garments over it, and he sat on it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 8, 'Many in the crowd spread their coats on the road ahead of Jesus, and others cut leafy branches in the fields and spread them along the way.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 9, 'He was in the center of the procession, and the crowds all around him were shouting, "Praise God! Bless the one who comes in the name of the Lord!', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 10, 'Bless the coming kingdom of our ancestor David! Praise God in highest heaven!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 11, 'So Jesus came to Jerusalem and went into the Temple. He looked around carefully at everything, and then he left because it was late in the afternoon. Then he went out to Bethany with the twelve disciples.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 12, 'The next morning as they were leaving Bethany, Jesus felt hungry.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 13, 'He noticed a fig tree a little way off that was in full leaf, so he went over to see if he could find any figs on it. But there were only leaves because it was too early in the season for fruit.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 14, 'Then Jesus said to the tree, "May no one ever eat your fruit again!" And the disciples heard him say it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 15, 'When they arrived back in Jerusalem, Jesus entered the Temple and began to drive out the merchants and their customers. He knocked over the tables of the money changers and the stalls of those selling doves,', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 16, 'and he stopped everyone from bringing in merchandise.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 17, 'He taught them, "The Scriptures declare, ''My Temple will be called a place of prayer for all nations,'' but you have turned it into a den of thieves."', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 18, 'When the leading priests and teachers of religious law heard what Jesus had done, they began planning how to kill him. But they were afraid of him because the people were so enthusiastic about Jesus'' teaching.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 19, 'That evening Jesus and the disciples left the city.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 20, 'The next morning as they passed by the fig tree he had cursed, the disciples noticed it was withered from the roots.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 21, 'Peter remembered what Jesus had said to the tree on the previous day and exclaimed, "Look, Teacher! The fig tree you cursed has withered!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 22, 'Then Jesus said to the disciples, "Have faith in God.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 23, 'I assure you that you can say to this mountain, ''May God lift you up and throw you into the sea,'' and your command will be obeyed. All that''s required is that you really believe and do not doubt in your heart.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 24, 'Listen to me! You can pray for anything, and if you believe, you will have it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 25, 'But when you are praying, first forgive anyone you are holding a grudge against, so that your Father in heaven will forgive your sins, too. "', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 26, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 27, 'By this time they had arrived in Jerusalem again. As Jesus was walking through the Temple area, the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the other leaders came up to him. They demanded,', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 28, '"By whose authority did you drive out the merchants from the Temple? Who gave you such authority?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 29, '"I''ll tell who gave me authority to do these things if you answer one question," Jesus replied.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 30, '"Did John''s baptism come from heaven or was it merely human? Answer me!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 31, 'They talked it over among themselves. "If we say it was from heaven, he will ask why we didn''t believe him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 32, 'But do we dare say it was merely human?" For they were afraid that the people would start a riot, since everyone thought that John was a prophet.', 'NLT'),
(45, 11, 33, 'So they finally replied, "We don''t know." And Jesus responded, "Then I won''t answer your question either."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 1, 'Then Jesus began telling them stories: "A man planted a vineyard, built a wall around it, dug a pit for pressing out the grape juice, and built a lookout tower. Then he leased the vineyard to tenant farmers and moved to another country.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 2, 'At grape-picking time he sent one of his servants to collect his share of the crop.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 3, 'But the farmers grabbed the servant, beat him up, and sent him back empty-handed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 4, '"The owner then sent another servant, but they beat him over the head and treated him shamefully.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 5, 'The next servant he sent was killed. Others who were sent were either beaten or killed,', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 6, 'until there was only one left--his son whom he loved dearly. The owner finally sent him, thinking, ''Surely they will respect my son.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 7, '"But the farmers said to one another, ''Here comes the heir to this estate. Let''s kill him and get the estate for ourselves!''', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 8, 'So they grabbed him and murdered him and threw his body out of the vineyard.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 9, '"What do you suppose the owner of the vineyard will do?" Jesus asked. "I''ll tell you--he will come and kill them all and lease the vineyard to others.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 10, 'Didn''t you ever read this in the Scriptures? ''The stone rejected by the builders has now become the cornerstone.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 11, 'This is the Lord''s doing, and it is marvelous to see.''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 12, 'The Jewish leaders wanted to arrest him for using this illustration because they realized he was pointing at them--they were the wicked farmers in his story. But they were afraid to touch him because of the crowds. So they left him and went away.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 13, 'The leaders sent some Pharisees and supporters of Herod to try to trap Jesus into saying something for which he could be arrested.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 14, '"Teacher," these men said, "we know how honest you are. You are impartial and don''t play favorites. You sincerely teach the ways of God. Now tell us--is it right to pay taxes to the Roman government or not?', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 15, 'Should we pay them, or should we not?" Jesus saw through their hypocrisy and said, "Whom are you trying to fool with your trick questions? Show me a Roman coin, and I''ll tell you."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 16, 'When they handed it to him, he asked, "Whose picture and title are stamped on it?Caesar''s," they replied.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 17, '"Well, then," Jesus said, "give to Caesar what belongs to him. But everything that belongs to God must be given to God." This reply completely amazed them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 18, 'Then the Sadducees stepped forward--a group of Jews who say there is no resurrection after death. They posed this question:', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 19, '"Teacher, Moses gave us a law that if a man dies, leaving a wife without children, his brother should marry the widow and have a child who will be the brother''s heir.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 20, 'Well, there were seven brothers. The oldest of them married and then died without children.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 21, 'So the second brother married the widow, but soon he too died and left no children. Then the next brother married her and died without children.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 22, 'This continued until all the brothers had married her and died, and still there were no children. Last of all, the woman died, too.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 23, 'So tell us, whose wife will she be in the resurrection? For all seven were married to her."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 24, 'Jesus replied, "Your problem is that you don''t know the Scriptures, and you don''t know the power of God.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 25, 'For when the dead rise, they won''t be married. They will be like the angels in heaven.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 26, 'But now, as to whether the dead will be raised--haven''t you ever read about this in the writings of Moses, in the story of the burning bush? Long after Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob had died, God said to Moses, ''I am the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 27, 'So he is the God of the living, not the dead. You have made a serious error."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 28, 'One of the teachers of religious law was standing there listening to the discussion. He realized that Jesus had answered well, so he asked, "Of all the commandments, which is the most important?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 29, 'Jesus replied, "The most important commandment is this: ''Hear, O Israel! The Lord our God is the one and only Lord.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 30, 'And you must love the Lord your God with all your heart, all your soul, all your mind, and all your strength.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 31, 'The second is equally important: ''Love your neighbor as yourself.'' No other commandment is greater than these."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 32, 'The teacher of religious law replied, "Well said, Teacher. You have spoken the truth by saying that there is only one God and no other.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 33, 'And I know it is important to love him with all my heart and all my understanding and all my strength, and to love my neighbors as myself. This is more important than to offer all of the burnt offerings and sacrifices required in the law."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 34, 'Realizing this man''s understanding, Jesus said to him, "You are not far from the Kingdom of God." And after that, no one dared to ask him any more questions.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 35, 'Later, as Jesus was teaching the people in the Temple, he asked, "Why do the teachers of religious law claim that the Messiah will be the son of David?', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 36, 'For David himself, speaking under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit, said, ''The LORD said to my Lord, Sit in honor at my right hand until I humble your enemies beneath your feet.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 37, 'Since David himself called him Lord, how can he be his son at the same time?" And the crowd listened to him with great interest.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 38, 'Here are some of the other things he taught them at this time: "Beware of these teachers of religious law! For they love to parade in flowing robes and to have everyone bow to them as they walk in the marketplaces.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 39, 'And how they love the seats of honor in the synagogues and at banquets.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 40, 'But they shamelessly cheat widows out of their property, and then, to cover up the kind of people they really are, they make long prayers in public. Because of this, their punishment will be the greater."', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 41, 'Jesus went over to the collection box in the Temple and sat and watched as the crowds dropped in their money. Many rich people put in large amounts.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 42, 'Then a poor widow came and dropped in two pennies.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 43, 'He called his disciples to him and said, "I assure you, this poor widow has given more than all the others have given.', 'NLT'),
(45, 12, 44, 'For they gave a tiny part of their surplus, but she, poor as she is, has given everything she has."', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 1, 'As Jesus was leaving the Temple that day, one of his disciples said, "Teacher, look at these tremendous buildings! Look at the massive stones in the walls!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 2, 'Jesus replied, "These magnificent buildings will be so completely demolished that not one stone will be left on top of another."', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 3, 'Later, Jesus sat on the slopes of the Mount of Olives across the valley from the Temple. Peter, James, John, and Andrew came to him privately and asked him,', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 4, '"When will all this take place? And will there be any sign ahead of time to show us when all this will be fulfilled?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 5, 'Jesus replied, "Don''t let anyone mislead you,', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 6, 'because many will come in my name, claiming to be the Messiah. They will lead many astray.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 7, 'And wars will break out near and far, but don''t panic. Yes, these things must come, but the end won''t follow immediately.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 8, 'Nations and kingdoms will proclaim war against each other, and there will be earthquakes in many parts of the world, and famines. But all this will be only the beginning of the horrors to come.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 9, 'But when these things begin to happen, watch out! You will be handed over to the courts and beaten in the synagogues. You will be accused before governors and kings of being my followers. This will be your opportunity to tell them about me.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 10, 'And the Good News must first be preached to every nation.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 11, 'But when you are arrested and stand trial, don''t worry about what to say in your defense. Just say what God tells you to. Then it is not you who will be speaking, but the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 12, '"Brother will betray brother to death, fathers will betray their own children, and children will rise against their parents and cause them to be killed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 13, 'And everyone will hate you because of your allegiance to me. But those who endure to the end will be saved.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 14, '"The time will come when you will see the sacrilegious object that causes desecration standing where it should not be"--reader, pay attention! "Then those in Judea must flee to the hills.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 15, 'A person outside the house must not go back into the house to pack.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 16, 'A person in the field must not return even to get a coat.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 17, 'How terrible it will be for pregnant women and for mothers nursing their babies in those days.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 18, 'And pray that your flight will not be in winter.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 19, 'For those will be days of greater horror than at any time since God created the world. And it will never happen again.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 20, 'In fact, unless the Lord shortens that time of calamity, the entire human race will be destroyed. But for the sake of his chosen ones he has shortened those days.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 21, '"And then if anyone tells you, ''Look, here is the Messiah,'' or, ''There he is,'' don''t pay any attention.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 22, 'For false messiahs and false prophets will rise up and perform miraculous signs and wonders so as to deceive, if possible, even God''s chosen ones.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 23, 'Watch out! I have warned you!', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 24, '"At that time, after those horrible days end, the sun will be darkened, the moon will not give light,', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 25, 'the stars will fall from the sky, and the powers of heaven will be shaken.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 26, 'Then everyone will see the Son of Man arrive on the clouds with great power and glory.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 27, 'And he will send forth his angels to gather together his chosen ones from all over the world--from the farthest ends of the earth and heaven.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 28, '"Now, learn a lesson from the fig tree. When its buds become tender and its leaves begin to sprout, you know without being told that summer is near.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 29, 'Just so, when you see the events I''ve described beginning to happen, you can be sure that his return is very near, right at the door.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 30, 'I assure you, this generation will not pass from the scene until all these events have taken place.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 31, 'Heaven and earth will disappear, but my words will remain forever.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 32, '"However, no one knows the day or hour when these things will happen, not even the angels in heaven or the Son himself. Only the Father knows.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 33, 'And since you don''t know when they will happen, stay alert and keep watch.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 34, '"The coming of the Son of Man can be compared with that of a man who left home to go on a trip. He gave each of his employees instructions about the work they were to do, and he told the gatekeeper to watch for his return.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 35, 'So keep a sharp lookout! For you do not know when the homeowner will return--at evening, midnight, early dawn, or late daybreak.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 36, 'Don''t let him find you sleeping when he arrives without warning.', 'NLT'),
(45, 13, 37, 'What I say to you I say to everyone: Watch for his return!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 1, 'It was now two days before the Passover celebration and the Festival of Unleavened Bread. The leading priests and the teachers of religious law were still looking for an opportunity to capture Jesus secretly and put him to death.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 2, '"But not during the Passover," they agreed, "or there will be a riot."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 3, 'Meanwhile, Jesus was in Bethany at the home of Simon, a man who had leprosy. During supper, a woman came in with a beautiful jar of expensive perfume. She broke the seal and poured the perfume over his head.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 4, 'Some of those at the table were indignant. "Why was this expensive perfume wasted?" they asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 5, '"She could have sold it for a small fortune and given the money to the poor!" And they scolded her harshly.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 6, 'But Jesus replied, "Leave her alone. Why berate her for doing such a good thing to me?', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 7, 'You will always have the poor among you, and you can help them whenever you want to. But I will not be here with you much longer.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 8, 'She has done what she could and has anointed my body for burial ahead of time.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 9, 'I assure you, wherever the Good News is preached throughout the world, this woman''s deed will be talked about in her memory."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 10, 'Then Judas Iscariot, one of the twelve disciples, went to the leading priests to arrange to betray Jesus to them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 11, 'The leading priests were delighted when they heard why he had come, and they promised him a reward. So he began looking for the right time and place to betray Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 12, 'On the first day of the Festival of Unleavened Bread (the day the Passover lambs were sacrificed), Jesus'' disciples asked him, "Where do you want us to go to prepare the Passover supper?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 13, 'So Jesus sent two of them into Jerusalem to make the arrangements. "As you go into the city," he told them, "a man carrying a pitcher of water will meet you. Follow him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 14, 'At the house he enters, say to the owner, ''The Teacher asks, Where is the guest room where I can eat the Passover meal with my disciples?''', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 15, 'He will take you upstairs to a large room that is already set up. That is the place; go ahead and prepare our supper there."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 16, 'So the two disciples went on ahead into the city and found everything just as Jesus had said, and they prepared the Passover supper there.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 17, 'In the evening Jesus arrived with the twelve disciples.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 18, 'As they were sitting around the table eating, Jesus said, "The truth is, one of you will betray me, one of you who is here eating with me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 19, 'Greatly distressed, one by one they began to ask him, "I''m not the one, am I?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 20, 'He replied, "It is one of you twelve, one who is eating with me now.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 21, 'For I, the Son of Man, must die, as the Scriptures declared long ago. But how terrible it will be for my betrayer. Far better for him if he had never been born!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 22, 'As they were eating, Jesus took a loaf of bread and asked God''s blessing on it. Then he broke it in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, "Take it, for this is my body."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 23, 'And he took a cup of wine and gave thanks to God for it. He gave it to them, and they all drank from it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 24, 'And he said to them, "This is my blood, poured out for many, sealing the covenant between God and his people.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 25, 'I solemnly declare that I will not drink wine again until that day when I drink it new in the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 26, 'Then they sang a hymn and went out to the Mount of Olives.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 27, '"All of you will desert me," Jesus told them. "For the Scriptures say, ''God will strike the Shepherd, and the sheep will be scattered.''', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 28, 'But after I am raised from the dead, I will go ahead of you to Galilee and meet you there."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 29, 'Peter said to him, "Even if everyone else deserts you, I never will."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 30, '"Peter," Jesus replied, "the truth is, this very night, before the rooster crows twice, you will deny me three times."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 31, '"No!" Peter insisted. "Not even if I have to die with you! I will never deny you!" And all the others vowed the same.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 32, 'And they came to an olive grove called Gethsemane, and Jesus said, "Sit here while I go and pray."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 33, 'He took Peter, James, and John with him, and he began to be filled with horror and deep distress.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 34, 'He told them, "My soul is crushed with grief to the point of death. Stay here and watch with me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 35, 'He went on a little farther and fell face down on the ground. He prayed that, if it were possible, the awful hour awaiting him might pass him by.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 36, '"Abba, Father," he said, "everything is possible for you. Please take this cup of suffering away from me. Yet I want your will, not mine."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 37, 'Then he returned and found the disciples asleep. "Simon!" he said to Peter. "Are you asleep? Couldn''t you stay awake and watch with me even one hour?', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 38, 'Keep alert and pray. Otherwise temptation will overpower you. For though the spirit is willing enough, the body is weak."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 39, 'Then Jesus left them again and prayed, repeating his pleadings.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 40, 'Again he returned to them and found them sleeping, for they just couldn''t keep their eyes open. And they didn''t know what to say.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 41, 'When he returned to them the third time, he said, "Still sleeping? Still resting? Enough! The time has come. I, the Son of Man, am betrayed into the hands of sinners.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 42, 'Up, let''s be going. See, my betrayer is here!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 43, 'And immediately, as he said this, Judas, one of the twelve disciples, arrived with a mob that was armed with swords and clubs. They had been sent out by the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the other leaders.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 44, 'Judas had given them a prearranged signal: "You will know which one to arrest when I go over and give him the kiss of greeting. Then you can take him away under guard."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 45, 'As soon as they arrived, Judas walked up to Jesus. "Teacher!" he exclaimed, and gave him the kiss.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 46, 'Then the others grabbed Jesus and arrested him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 47, 'But someone pulled out a sword and slashed off an ear of the high priest''s servant.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 48, 'Jesus asked them, "Am I some dangerous criminal, that you come armed with swords and clubs to arrest me?', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 49, 'Why didn''t you arrest me in the Temple? I was there teaching every day. But these things are happening to fulfill what the Scriptures say about me."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 50, 'Meanwhile, all his disciples deserted him and ran away.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 51, 'There was a young man following along behind, clothed only in a linen nightshirt. When the mob tried to grab him,', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 52, 'they tore off his clothes, but he escaped and ran away naked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 53, 'Jesus was led to the high priest''s home where the leading priests, other leaders, and teachers of religious law had gathered.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 54, 'Meanwhile, Peter followed far behind and then slipped inside the gates of the high priest''s courtyard. For a while he sat with the guards, warming himself by the fire.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 55, 'Inside, the leading priests and the entire high council were trying to find witnesses who would testify against Jesus, so they could put him to death. But their efforts were in vain.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 56, 'Many false witnesses spoke against him, but they contradicted each other.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 57, 'Finally, some men stood up to testify against him with this lie:', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 58, '"We heard him say, ''I will destroy this Temple made with human hands, and in three days I will build another, made without human hands.''"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 59, 'But even then they didn''t get their stories straight!', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 60, 'Then the high priest stood up before the others and asked Jesus, "Well, aren''t you going to answer these charges? What do you have to say for yourself?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 61, 'Jesus made no reply. Then the high priest asked him, "Are you the Messiah, the Son of the blessed God?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 62, 'Jesus said, "I am, and you will see me, the Son of Man, sitting at God''s right hand in the place of power and coming back on the clouds of heaven."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 63, 'Then the high priest tore his clothing to show his horror and said, "Why do we need other witnesses?', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 64, 'You have all heard his blasphemy. What is your verdict?" And they all condemned him to death.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 65, 'Then some of them began to spit at him, and they blindfolded him and hit his face with their fists. "Who hit you that time, you prophet?" they jeered. And even the guards were hitting him as they led him away.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 66, 'Meanwhile, Peter was below in the courtyard. One of the servant girls who worked for the high priest', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 67, 'noticed Peter warming himself at the fire. She looked at him closely and then said, "You were one of those with Jesus, the Nazarene."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 68, 'Peter denied it. "I don''t know what you''re talking about," he said, and he went out into the entryway. Just then, a rooster crowed.', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 69, 'The servant girl saw him standing there and began telling the others, "That man is definitely one of them!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 70, 'Peter denied it again. A little later some other bystanders began saying to Peter, "You must be one of them because you are from Galilee."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 71, 'Peter said, "I swear by God, I don''t know this man you''re talking about."', 'NLT'),
(45, 14, 72, 'And immediately the rooster crowed the second time. Suddenly, Jesus'' words flashed through Peter''s mind: "Before the rooster crows twice, you will deny me three times." And he broke down and cried.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 1, 'Very early in the morning the leading priests, other leaders, and teachers of religious law--the entire high council--met to discuss their next step. They bound Jesus and took him to Pilate, the Roman governor.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 2, 'Pilate asked Jesus, "Are you the King of the Jews?" Jesus replied, "Yes, it is as you say."', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 3, 'Then the leading priests accused him of many crimes,', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 4, 'and Pilate asked him, "Aren''t you going to say something? What about all these charges against you?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 5, 'But Jesus said nothing, much to Pilate''s surprise.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 6, 'Now it was the governor''s custom to release one prisoner each year at Passover time--anyone the people requested.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 7, 'One of the prisoners at that time was Barabbas, convicted along with others for murder during an insurrection.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 8, 'The mob began to crowd in toward Pilate, asking him to release a prisoner as usual.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 9, '"Should I give you the King of the Jews?" Pilate asked.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 10, '(For he realized by now that the leading priests had arrested Jesus out of envy.)', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 11, 'But at this point the leading priests stirred up the mob to demand the release of Barabbas instead of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 12, '"But if I release Barabbas," Pilate asked them, "what should I do with this man you call the King of the Jews?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 13, 'They shouted back, "Crucify him!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 14, '"Why?" Pilate demanded. "What crime has he committed?" But the crowd only roared the louder, "Crucify him!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 15, 'So Pilate, anxious to please the crowd, released Barabbas to them. He ordered Jesus flogged with a lead-tipped whip, then turned him over to the Roman soldiers to crucify him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 16, 'The soldiers took him into their headquarters and called out the entire battalion.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 17, 'They dressed him in a purple robe and made a crown of long, sharp thorns and put it on his head.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 18, 'Then they saluted, yelling, "Hail! King of the Jews!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 19, 'And they beat him on the head with a stick, spit on him, and dropped to their knees in mock worship.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 20, 'When they were finally tired of mocking him, they took off the purple robe and put his own clothes on him again. Then they led him away to be crucified.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 21, 'A man named Simon, who was from Cyrene, was coming in from the country just then, and they forced him to carry Jesus'' cross. (Simon is the father of Alexander and Rufus.)', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 22, 'And they brought Jesus to a place called Golgotha (which means Skull Hill).', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 23, 'They offered him wine drugged with myrrh, but he refused it.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 24, 'Then they nailed him to the cross. They gambled for his clothes, throwing dice to decide who would get them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 25, 'It was nine o''clock in the morning when the crucifixion took place.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 26, 'A signboard was fastened to the cross above Jesus'' head, announcing the charge against him. It read: "The King of the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 27, 'Two criminals were crucified with him, their crosses on either side of his.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 28, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 29, 'And the people passing by shouted abuse, shaking their heads in mockery. "Ha! Look at you now!" they yelled at him. "You can destroy the Temple and rebuild it in three days, can you?', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 30, 'Well then, save yourself and come down from the cross!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 31, 'The leading priests and teachers of religious law also mocked Jesus. "He saved others," they scoffed, "but he can''t save himself!', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 32, 'Let this Messiah, this king of Israel, come down from the cross so we can see it and believe him!" Even the two criminals who were being crucified with Jesus ridiculed him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 33, 'At noon, darkness fell across the whole land until three o''clock.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 34, 'Then, at that time Jesus called out with a loud voice, "Eloi, Eloi, lema sabachthani?" which means, "My God, my God, why have you forsaken me?"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 35, 'Some of the bystanders misunderstood and thought he was calling for the prophet Elijah.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 36, 'One of them ran and filled a sponge with sour wine, holding it up to him on a stick so he could drink. "Leave him alone. Let''s see whether Elijah will come and take him down!" he said.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 37, 'Then Jesus uttered another loud cry and breathed his last.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 38, 'And the curtain in the Temple was torn in two, from top to bottom.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 39, 'When the Roman officer who stood facing him saw how he had died, he exclaimed, "Truly, this was the Son of God!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 40, 'Some women were there, watching from a distance, including Mary Magdalene, Mary (the mother of James the younger and of Joseph ), and Salome.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 41, 'They had been followers of Jesus and had cared for him while he was in Galilee. Then they and many other women had come with him to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 42, 'This all happened on Friday, the day of preparation, the day before the Sabbath. As evening approached,', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 43, 'an honored member of the high council, Joseph from Arimathea (who was waiting for the Kingdom of God to come), gathered his courage and went to Pilate to ask for Jesus'' body.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 44, 'Pilate couldn''t believe that Jesus was already dead, so he called for the Roman military officer in charge and asked him.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 45, 'The officer confirmed the fact, and Pilate told Joseph he could have the body.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 46, 'Joseph bought a long sheet of linen cloth, and taking Jesus'' body down from the cross, he wrapped it in the cloth and laid it in a tomb that had been carved out of the rock. Then he rolled a stone in front of the entrance.', 'NLT'),
(45, 15, 47, 'Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joseph saw where Jesus'' body was laid.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 1, 'The next evening, when the Sabbath ended, Mary Magdalene and Salome and Mary the mother of James went out and purchased burial spices to put on Jesus'' body.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 2, 'Very early on Sunday morning, just at sunrise, they came to the tomb.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 3, 'On the way they were discussing who would roll the stone away from the entrance to the tomb.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 4, 'But when they arrived, they looked up and saw that the stone--a very large one--had already been rolled aside.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 5, 'So they entered the tomb, and there on the right sat a young man clothed in a white robe. The women were startled,', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 6, 'but the angel said, "Do not be so surprised. You are looking for Jesus, the Nazarene, who was crucified. He isn''t here! He has been raised from the dead! Look, this is where they laid his body.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 7, 'Now go and give this message to his disciples, including Peter: Jesus is going ahead of you to Galilee. You will see him there, just as he told you before he died!"', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 8, 'The women fled from the tomb, trembling and bewildered, saying nothing to anyone because they were too frightened to talk. Then they reported all these instructions briefly to Peter and his companions. Afterward Jesus himself sent them out from east to west with the sacred and unfailing message of salvation that gives eternal life. Amen.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 9, 'It was early on Sunday morning when Jesus rose from the dead, and the first person who saw him was Mary Magdalene, the woman from whom he had cast out seven demons.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 10, 'She went and found the disciples, who were grieving and weeping.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 11, 'But when she told them that Jesus was alive and she had seen him, they didn''t believe her.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 12, 'Afterward he appeared to two who were walking from Jerusalem into the country, but they didn''t recognize him at first because he had changed his appearance.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 13, 'When they realized who he was, they rushed back to tell the others, but no one believed them.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 14, 'Still later he appeared to the eleven disciples as they were eating together. He rebuked them for their unbelief--their stubborn refusal to believe those who had seen him after he had risen.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 15, 'And then he told them, "Go into all the world and preach the Good News to everyone, everywhere.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 16, 'Anyone who believes and is baptized will be saved. But anyone who refuses to believe will be condemned.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 17, 'These signs will accompany those who believe: They will cast out demons in my name, and they will speak new languages.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 18, 'They will be able to handle snakes with safety, and if they drink anything poisonous, it won''t hurt them. They will be able to place their hands on the sick and heal them."', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 19, 'When the Lord Jesus had finished talking with them, he was taken up into heaven and sat down in the place of honor at God''s right hand.', 'NLT'),
(45, 16, 20, 'And the disciples went everywhere and preached, and the Lord worked with them, confirming what they said by many miraculous signs.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 1, 'Most honorable Theophilus: Many people have written accounts about the events that took place among us.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 2, 'They used as their source material the reports circulating among us from the early disciples and other eyewitnesses of what God has done in fulfillment of his promises.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 3, 'Having carefully investigated all of these accounts from the beginning, I have decided to write a careful summary for you,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 4, 'to reassure you of the truth of all you were taught.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 5, 'It all begins with a Jewish priest, Zechariah, who lived when Herod was king of Judea. Zechariah was a member of the priestly order of Abijah. His wife, Elizabeth, was also from the priestly line of Aaron.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 6, 'Zechariah and Elizabeth were righteous in God''s eyes, careful to obey all of the Lord''s commandments and regulations.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 7, 'They had no children because Elizabeth was barren, and now they were both very old.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 8, 'One day Zechariah was serving God in the Temple, for his order was on duty that week.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 9, 'As was the custom of the priests, he was chosen by lot to enter the sanctuary and burn incense in the Lord''s presence.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 10, 'While the incense was being burned, a great crowd stood outside, praying.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 11, 'Zechariah was in the sanctuary when an angel of the Lord appeared, standing to the right of the incense altar.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 12, 'Zechariah was overwhelmed with fear.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 13, 'But the angel said, "Don''t be afraid, Zechariah! For God has heard your prayer, and your wife, Elizabeth, will bear you a son! And you are to name him John.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 14, 'You will have great joy and gladness, and many will rejoice with you at his birth,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 15, 'for he will be great in the eyes of the Lord. He must never touch wine or hard liquor, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit, even before his birth.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 16, 'And he will persuade many Israelites to turn to the Lord their God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 17, 'He will be a man with the spirit and power of Elijah, the prophet of old. He will precede the coming of the Lord, preparing the people for his arrival. He will turn the hearts of the fathers to their children, and he will change disobedient minds to accept godly wisdom."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 18, 'Zechariah said to the angel, "How can I know this will happen? I''m an old man now, and my wife is also well along in years."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 19, 'Then the angel said, "I am Gabriel! I stand in the very presence of God. It was he who sent me to bring you this good news!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 20, 'And now, since you didn''t believe what I said, you won''t be able to speak until the child is born. For my words will certainly come true at the proper time."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 21, 'Meanwhile, the people were waiting for Zechariah to come out, wondering why he was taking so long.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 22, 'When he finally did come out, he couldn''t speak to them. Then they realized from his gestures that he must have seen a vision in the Temple sanctuary.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 23, 'He stayed at the Temple until his term of service was over, and then he returned home.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 24, 'Soon afterward his wife, Elizabeth, became pregnant and went into seclusion for five months.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 25, '"How kind the Lord is!" she exclaimed. "He has taken away my disgrace of having no children!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 26, 'In the sixth month of Elizabeth''s pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a village in Galilee,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 27, 'to a virgin named Mary. She was engaged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of King David.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 28, 'Gabriel appeared to her and said, "Greetings, favored woman! The Lord is with you! "', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 29, 'Confused and disturbed, Mary tried to think what the angel could mean.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 30, '"Don''t be frightened, Mary," the angel told her, "for God has decided to bless you!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 31, 'You will become pregnant and have a son, and you are to name him Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 32, 'He will be very great and will be called the Son of the Most High. And the Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 33, 'And he will reign over Israel forever; his Kingdom will never end!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 34, 'Mary asked the angel, "But how can I have a baby? I am a virgin."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 35, 'The angel replied, "The Holy Spirit will come upon you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you. So the baby born to you will be holy, and he will be called the Son of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 36, 'What''s more, your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age! People used to say she was barren, but she''s already in her sixth month.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 37, 'For nothing is impossible with God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 38, 'Mary responded, "I am the Lord''s servant, and I am willing to accept whatever he wants. May everything you have said come true." And then the angel left.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 39, 'A few days later Mary hurried to the hill country of Judea, to the town', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 40, 'where Zechariah lived. She entered the house and greeted Elizabeth.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 41, 'At the sound of Mary''s greeting, Elizabeth''s child leaped within her, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 42, 'Elizabeth gave a glad cry and exclaimed to Mary, "You are blessed by God above all other women, and your child is blessed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 43, 'What an honor this is, that the mother of my Lord should visit me!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 44, 'When you came in and greeted me, my baby jumped for joy the instant I heard your voice!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 45, 'You are blessed, because you believed that the Lord would do what he said."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 46, 'Mary responded, "Oh, how I praise the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 47, 'How I rejoice in God my Savior!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 48, 'For he took notice of his lowly servant girl, and now generation after generation will call me blessed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 49, 'For he, the Mighty One, is holy, and he has done great things for me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 50, 'His mercy goes on from generation to generation, to all who fear him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 51, 'His mighty arm does tremendous things! How he scatters the proud and haughty ones!', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 52, 'He has taken princes from their thrones and exalted the lowly.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 53, 'He has satisfied the hungry with good things and sent the rich away with empty hands.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 54, 'And how he has helped his servant Israel! He has not forgotten his promise to be merciful.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 55, 'For he promised our ancestors--Abraham and his children--to be merciful to them forever."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 56, 'Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months and then went back to her own home.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 57, 'Now it was time for Elizabeth''s baby to be born, and it was a boy.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 58, 'The word spread quickly to her neighbors and relatives that the Lord had been very kind to her, and everyone rejoiced with her.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 59, 'When the baby was eight days old, all the relatives and friends came for the circumcision ceremony. They wanted to name him Zechariah, after his father.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 60, 'But Elizabeth said, "No! His name is John!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 61, '"What?" they exclaimed. "There is no one in all your family by that name."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 62, 'So they asked the baby''s father, communicating to him by making gestures.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 63, 'He motioned for a writing tablet, and to everyone''s surprise he wrote, "His name is John!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 64, 'Instantly Zechariah could speak again, and he began praising God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 65, 'Wonder fell upon the whole neighborhood, and the news of what had happened spread throughout the Judean hills.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 66, 'Everyone who heard about it reflected on these events and asked, "I wonder what this child will turn out to be? For the hand of the Lord is surely upon him in a special way."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 67, 'Then his father, Zechariah, was filled with the Holy Spirit and gave this prophecy:', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 68, '"Praise the Lord, the God of Israel, because he has visited his people and redeemed them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 69, 'He has sent us a mighty Savior from the royal line of his servant David,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 70, 'just as he promised through his holy prophets long ago.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 71, 'Now we will be saved from our enemies and from all who hate us.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 72, 'He has been merciful to our ancestors by remembering his sacred covenant with them,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 73, 'the covenant he gave to our ancestor Abraham.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 74, 'We have been rescued from our enemies, so we can serve God without fear,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 75, 'in holiness and righteousness forever.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 76, '"And you, my little son, will be called the prophet of the Most High, because you will prepare the way for the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 77, 'You will tell his people how to find salvation through forgiveness of their sins.', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 78, 'Because of God''s tender mercy, the light from heaven is about to break upon us,', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 79, 'to give light to those who sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, and to guide us to the path of peace."', 'NLT'),
(46, 1, 80, 'John grew up and became strong in spirit. Then he lived out in the wilderness until he began his public ministry to Israel.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 1, 'At that time the Roman emperor, Augustus, decreed that a census should be taken throughout the Roman Empire.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 2, '(This was the first census taken when Quirinius was governor of Syria.)', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 3, 'All returned to their own towns to register for this census.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 4, 'And because Joseph was a descendant of King David, he had to go to Bethlehem in Judea, David''s ancient home. He traveled there from the village of Nazareth in Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 5, 'He took with him Mary, his fiance, who was obviously pregnant by this time.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 6, 'And while they were there, the time came for her baby to be born.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 7, 'She gave birth to her first child, a son. She wrapped him snugly in strips of cloth and laid him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the village inn.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 8, 'That night some shepherds were in the fields outside the village, guarding their flocks of sheep.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 9, 'Suddenly, an angel of the Lord appeared among them, and the radiance of the Lord''s glory surrounded them. They were terribly frightened,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 10, 'but the angel reassured them. "Don''t be afraid!" he said. "I bring you good news of great joy for everyone!', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 11, 'The Savior--yes, the Messiah, the Lord--has been born tonight in Bethlehem, the city of David!', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 12, 'And this is how you will recognize him: You will find a baby lying in a manger, wrapped snugly in strips of cloth!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 13, 'Suddenly, the angel was joined by a vast host of others--the armies of heaven--praising God:', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 14, '"Glory to God in the highest heaven, and peace on earth to all whom God favors. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 15, 'When the angels had returned to heaven, the shepherds said to each other, "Come on, let''s go to Bethlehem! Let''s see this wonderful thing that has happened, which the Lord has told us about."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 16, 'They ran to the village and found Mary and Joseph. And there was the baby, lying in the manger.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 17, 'Then the shepherds told everyone what had happened and what the angel had said to them about this child.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 18, 'All who heard the shepherds'' story were astonished,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 19, 'but Mary quietly treasured these things in her heart and thought about them often.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 20, 'The shepherds went back to their fields and flocks, glorifying and praising God for what the angels had told them, and because they had seen the child, just as the angel had said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 21, 'Eight days later, when the baby was circumcised, he was named Jesus, the name given him by the angel even before he was conceived.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 22, 'Then it was time for the purification offering, as required by the law of Moses after the birth of a child; so his parents took him to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 23, 'The law of the Lord says, "If a woman''s first child is a boy, he must be dedicated to the Lord."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 24, 'So they offered a sacrifice according to what was required in the law of the Lord--"either a pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 25, 'Now there was a man named Simeon who lived in Jerusalem. He was a righteous man and very devout. He was filled with the Holy Spirit, and he eagerly expected the Messiah to come and rescue Israel.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 26, 'The Holy Spirit had revealed to him that he would not die until he had seen the Lord''s Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 27, 'That day the Spirit led him to the Temple. So when Mary and Joseph came to present the baby Jesus to the Lord as the law required,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 28, 'Simeon was there. He took the child in his arms and praised God, saying,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 29, '"Lord, now I can die in peace! As you promised me,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 30, 'I have seen the Savior', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 31, 'you have given to all people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 32, 'He is a light to reveal God to the nations, and he is the glory of your people Israel!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 33, 'Joseph and Mary were amazed at what was being said about Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 34, 'Then Simeon blessed them, and he said to Mary, "This child will be rejected by many in Israel, and it will be their undoing. But he will be the greatest joy to many others.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 35, 'Thus, the deepest thoughts of many hearts will be revealed. And a sword will pierce your very soul."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 36, 'Anna, a prophet, was also there in the Temple. She was the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher, and was very old. She was a widow, for her husband had died when they had been married only seven years.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 37, 'She was now eighty-four years old. She never left the Temple but stayed there day and night, worshiping God with fasting and prayer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 38, 'She came along just as Simeon was talking with Mary and Joseph, and she began praising God. She talked about Jesus to everyone who had been waiting for the promised King to come and deliver Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 39, 'When Jesus'' parents had fulfilled all the requirements of the law of the Lord, they returned home to Nazareth in Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 40, 'There the child grew up healthy and strong. He was filled with wisdom beyond his years, and God placed his special favor upon him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 41, 'Every year Jesus'' parents went to Jerusalem for the Passover festival.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 42, 'When Jesus was twelve years old, they attended the festival as usual.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 43, 'After the celebration was over, they started home to Nazareth, but Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem. His parents didn''t miss him at first,', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 44, 'because they assumed he was with friends among the other travelers. But when he didn''t show up that evening, they started to look for him among their relatives and friends.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 45, 'When they couldn''t find him, they went back to Jerusalem to search for him there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 46, 'Three days later they finally discovered him. He was in the Temple, sitting among the religious teachers, discussing deep questions with them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 47, 'And all who heard him were amazed at his understanding and his answers.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 48, 'His parents didn''t know what to think. "Son!" his mother said to him. "Why have you done this to us? Your father and I have been frantic, searching for you everywhere."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 49, '"But why did you need to search?" he asked. "You should have known that I would be in my Father''s house."', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 50, 'But they didn''t understand what he meant.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 51, 'Then he returned to Nazareth with them and was obedient to them; and his mother stored all these things in her heart.', 'NLT'),
(46, 2, 52, 'So Jesus grew both in height and in wisdom, and he was loved by God and by all who knew him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 1, 'It was now the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius, the Roman emperor. Pilate was governor over Judea; Herod Antipas was ruler over Galilee; his brother Philip was ruler over Iturea and Traconitis; Lysanias was ruler over Abilene.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 2, 'Annas and Caiaphas were the high priests. At this time a message from God came to John son of Zechariah, who was living out in the wilderness.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 3, 'Then John went from place to place on both sides of the Jordan River, preaching that people should be baptized to show that they had turned from their sins and turned to God to be forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 4, 'Isaiah had spoken of John when he said, "He is a voice shouting in the wilderness: ''Prepare a pathway for the Lord''s coming! Make a straight road for him!', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 5, 'Fill in the valleys, and level the mountains and hills! Straighten the curves, and smooth out the rough places!', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 6, 'And then all people will see the salvation sent from God.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 7, 'Here is a sample of John''s preaching to the crowds that came for baptism: "You brood of snakes! Who warned you to flee God''s coming judgment?', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 8, 'Prove by the way you live that you have really turned from your sins and turned to God. Don''t just say, ''We''re safe--we''re the descendants of Abraham.'' That proves nothing. God can change these stones here into children of Abraham.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 9, 'Even now the ax of God''s judgment is poised, ready to sever your roots. Yes, every tree that does not produce good fruit will be chopped down and thrown into the fire."', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 10, 'The crowd asked, "What should we do?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 11, 'John replied, "If you have two coats, give one to the poor. If you have food, share it with those who are hungry."', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 12, 'Even corrupt tax collectors came to be baptized and asked, "Teacher, what should we do?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 13, '"Show your honesty," he replied. "Make sure you collect no more taxes than the Roman government requires you to."', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 14, '"What should we do?" asked some soldiers. John replied, "Don''t extort money, and don''t accuse people of things you know they didn''t do. And be content with your pay."', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 15, 'Everyone was expecting the Messiah to come soon, and they were eager to know whether John might be the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 16, 'John answered their questions by saying, "I baptize with water; but someone is coming soon who is greater than I am--so much greater that I am not even worthy to be his slave. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 17, 'He is ready to separate the chaff from the grain with his winnowing fork. Then he will clean up the threshing area, storing the grain in his barn but burning the chaff with never-ending fire."', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 18, 'John used many such warnings as he announced the Good News to the people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 19, 'John also publicly criticized Herod Antipas, ruler of Galilee, for marrying Herodias, his brother''s wife, and for many other wrongs he had done.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 20, 'So Herod put John in prison, adding this sin to his many others.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 21, 'One day when the crowds were being baptized, Jesus himself was baptized. As he was praying, the heavens opened,', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 22, 'and the Holy Spirit descended on him in the form of a dove. And a voice from heaven said, "You are my beloved Son, and I am fully pleased with you. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 23, 'Jesus was about thirty years old when he began his public ministry. Jesus was known as the son of Joseph. Joseph was the son of Heli.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 24, 'Heli was the son of Matthat. Matthat was the son of Levi. Levi was the son of Melki. Melki was the son of Jannai. Jannai was the son of Joseph.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 25, 'Joseph was the son of Mattathias. Mattathias was the son of Amos. Amos was the son of Nahum. Nahum was the son of Esli. Esli was the son of Naggai.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 26, 'Naggai was the son of Maath. Maath was the son of Mattathias. Mattathias was the son of Semein. Semein was the son of Josech. Josech was the son of Joda.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 27, 'Joda was the son of Joanan. Joanan was the son of Rhesa. Rhesa was the son of Zerubbabel. Zerubbabel was the son of Shealtiel. Shealtiel was the son of Neri.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 28, 'Neri was the son of Melki. Melki was the son of Addi. Addi was the son of Cosam. Cosam was the son of Elmadam. Elmadam was the son of Er.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 29, 'Er was the son of Joshua. Joshua was the son of Eliezer. Eliezer was the son of Jorim. Jorim was the son of Matthat. Matthat was the son of Levi.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 30, 'Levi was the son of Simeon. Simeon was the son of Judah. Judah was the son of Joseph. Joseph was the son of Jonam. Jonam was the son of Eliakim.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 31, 'Eliakim was the son of Melea. Melea was the son of Menna. Menna was the son of Mattatha. Mattatha was the son of Nathan. Nathan was the son of David.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 32, 'David was the son of Jesse. Jesse was the son of Obed. Obed was the son of Boaz. Boaz was the son of Salmon. Salmon was the son of Nahshon.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 33, 'Nahshon was the son of Amminadab. Amminadab was the son of Admin. Admin was the son of Arni. Arni was the son of Hezron. Hezron was the son of Perez. Perez was the son of Judah.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 34, 'Judah was the son of Jacob. Jacob was the son of Isaac. Isaac was the son of Abraham. Abraham was the son of Terah. Terah was the son of Nahor.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 35, 'Nahor was the son of Serug. Serug was the son of Reu. Reu was the son of Peleg. Peleg was the son of Eber. Eber was the son of Shelah.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 36, 'Shelah was the son of Cainan. Cainan was the son of Arphaxad. Arphaxad was the son of Shem. Shem was the son of Noah. Noah was the son of Lamech.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 37, 'Lamech was the son of Methuselah. Methuselah was the son of Enoch. Enoch was the son of Jared. Jared was the son of Mahalalel. Mahalalel was the son of Kenan.', 'NLT'),
(46, 3, 38, 'Kenan was the son of Enosh. Enosh was the son of Seth. Seth was the son of Adam. Adam was the son of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 1, 'Then Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, left the Jordan River. He was led by the Spirit to go out into the wilderness,', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 2, 'where the Devil tempted him for forty days. He ate nothing all that time and was very hungry.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 3, 'Then the Devil said to him, "If you are the Son of God, change this stone into a loaf of bread."', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 4, 'But Jesus told him, "No! The Scriptures say, ''People need more than bread for their life.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 5, 'Then the Devil took him up and revealed to him all the kingdoms of the world in a moment of time.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 6, 'The Devil told him, "I will give you the glory of these kingdoms and authority over them--because they are mine to give to anyone I please.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 7, 'I will give it all to you if you will bow down and worship me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 8, 'Jesus replied, "The Scriptures say, ''You must worship the Lord your God; serve only him.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 9, 'Then the Devil took him to Jerusalem, to the highest point of the Temple, and said, "If you are the Son of God, jump off!', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 10, 'For the Scriptures say, ''He orders his angels to protect and guard you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 11, 'And they will hold you with their hands to keep you from striking your foot on a stone.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 12, 'Jesus responded, "The Scriptures also say, ''Do not test the Lord your God.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 13, 'When the Devil had finished tempting Jesus, he left him until the next opportunity came.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 14, 'Then Jesus returned to Galilee, filled with the Holy Spirit''s power. Soon he became well known throughout the surrounding country.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 15, 'He taught in their synagogues and was praised by everyone.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 16, 'When he came to the village of Nazareth, his boyhood home, he went as usual to the synagogue on the Sabbath and stood up to read the Scriptures.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 17, 'The scroll containing the messages of Isaiah the prophet was handed to him, and he unrolled the scroll to the place where it says:', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 18, '"The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, for he has appointed me to preach Good News to the poor. He has sent me to proclaim that captives will be released, that the blind will see, that the downtrodden will be freed from their oppressors,', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 19, 'and that the time of the Lord''s favor has come. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 20, 'He rolled up the scroll, handed it back to the attendant, and sat down. Everyone in the synagogue stared at him intently.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 21, 'Then he said, "This Scripture has come true today before your very eyes!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 22, 'All who were there spoke well of him and were amazed by the gracious words that fell from his lips. "How can this be?" they asked. "Isn''t this Joseph''s son?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 23, 'Then he said, "Probably you will quote me that proverb, ''Physician, heal yourself''--meaning, ''Why don''t you do miracles here in your hometown like those you did in Capernaum?''', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 24, 'But the truth is, no prophet is accepted in his own hometown.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 25, '"Certainly there were many widows in Israel who needed help in Elijah''s time, when there was no rain for three and a half years and hunger stalked the land.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 26, 'Yet Elijah was not sent to any of them. He was sent instead to a widow of Zarephath--a foreigner in the land of Sidon.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 27, 'Or think of the prophet Elisha, who healed Naaman, a Syrian, rather than the many lepers in Israel who needed help."', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 28, 'When they heard this, the people in the synagogue were furious.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 29, 'Jumping up, they mobbed him and took him to the edge of the hill on which the city was built. They intended to push him over the cliff,', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 30, 'but he slipped away through the crowd and left them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 31, 'Then Jesus went to Capernaum, a town in Galilee, and taught there in the synagogue every Sabbath day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 32, 'There, too, the people were amazed at the things he said, because he spoke with authority.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 33, 'Once when he was in the synagogue, a man possessed by a demon began shouting at Jesus,', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 34, '"Go away! Why are you bothering us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are--the Holy One sent from God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 35, 'Jesus cut him short. "Be silent!" he told the demon. "Come out of the man!" The demon threw the man to the floor as the crowd watched; then it left him without hurting him further.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 36, 'Amazed, the people exclaimed, "What authority and power this man''s words possess! Even evil spirits obey him and flee at his command!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 37, 'The story of what he had done spread like wildfire throughout the whole region.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 38, 'After leaving the synagogue that day, Jesus went to Simon''s home, where he found Simon''s mother-in-law very sick with a high fever. "Please heal her," everyone begged.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 39, 'Standing at her bedside, he spoke to the fever, rebuking it, and immediately her temperature returned to normal. She got up at once and prepared a meal for them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 40, 'As the sun went down that evening, people throughout the village brought sick family members to Jesus. No matter what their diseases were, the touch of his hand healed every one.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 41, 'Some were possessed by demons; and the demons came out at his command, shouting, "You are the Son of God." But because they knew he was the Messiah, he stopped them and told them to be silent.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 42, 'Early the next morning Jesus went out into the wilderness. The crowds searched everywhere for him, and when they finally found him, they begged him not to leave them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 43, 'But he replied, "I must preach the Good News of the Kingdom of God in other places, too, because that is why I was sent."', 'NLT'),
(46, 4, 44, 'So he continued to travel around, preaching in synagogues throughout Judea.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 1, 'One day as Jesus was preaching on the shore of the Sea of Galilee, great crowds pressed in on him to listen to the word of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 2, 'He noticed two empty boats at the water''s edge, for the fishermen had left them and were washing their nets.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 3, 'Stepping into one of the boats, Jesus asked Simon, its owner, to push it out into the water. So he sat in the boat and taught the crowds from there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 4, 'When he had finished speaking, he said to Simon, "Now go out where it is deeper and let down your nets, and you will catch many fish."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 5, '"Master," Simon replied, "we worked hard all last night and didn''t catch a thing. But if you say so, we''ll try again."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 6, 'And this time their nets were so full they began to tear!', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 7, 'A shout for help brought their partners in the other boat, and soon both boats were filled with fish and on the verge of sinking.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 8, 'When Simon Peter realized what had happened, he fell to his knees before Jesus and said, "Oh, Lord, please leave me--I''m too much of a sinner to be around you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 9, 'For he was awestruck by the size of their catch, as were the others with him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 10, 'His partners, James and John, the sons of Zebedee, were also amazed. Jesus replied to Simon, "Don''t be afraid! From now on you''ll be fishing for people!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 11, 'And as soon as they landed, they left everything and followed Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 12, 'In one of the villages, Jesus met a man with an advanced case of leprosy. When the man saw Jesus, he fell to the ground, face down in the dust, begging to be healed. "Lord," he said, "if you want to, you can make me well again."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 13, 'Jesus reached out and touched the man. "I want to," he said. "Be healed!" And instantly the leprosy disappeared.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 14, 'Then Jesus instructed him not to tell anyone what had happened. He said, "Go right to the priest and let him examine you. Take along the offering required in the law of Moses for those who have been healed of leprosy, so everyone will have proof of your healing."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 15, 'Yet despite Jesus'' instructions, the report of his power spread even faster, and vast crowds came to hear him preach and to be healed of their diseases.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 16, 'But Jesus often withdrew to the wilderness for prayer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 17, 'One day while Jesus was teaching, some Pharisees and teachers of religious law were sitting nearby. (It seemed that these men showed up from every village in all Galilee and Judea, as well as from Jerusalem.) And the Lord''s healing power was strongly with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 18, 'Some men came carrying a paralyzed man on a sleeping mat. They tried to push through the crowd to Jesus,', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 19, 'but they couldn''t reach him. So they went up to the roof, took off some tiles, and lowered the sick man down into the crowd, still on his mat, right in front of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 20, 'Seeing their faith, Jesus said to the man, "Son, your sins are forgiven."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 21, '"Who does this man think he is?" the Pharisees and teachers of religious law said to each other. "This is blasphemy! Who but God can forgive sins?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 22, 'Jesus knew what they were thinking, so he asked them, "Why do you think this is blasphemy?', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 23, 'Is it easier to say, ''Your sins are forgiven'' or ''Get up and walk''?', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 24, 'I will prove that I, the Son of Man, have the authority on earth to forgive sins." Then Jesus turned to the paralyzed man and said, "Stand up, take your mat, and go on home, because you are healed!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 25, 'And immediately, as everyone watched, the man jumped to his feet, picked up his mat, and went home praising God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 26, 'Everyone was gripped with great wonder and awe. And they praised God, saying over and over again, "We have seen amazing things today."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 27, 'Later, as Jesus left the town, he saw a tax collector named Levi sitting at his tax-collection booth. "Come, be my disciple!" Jesus said to him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 28, 'So Levi got up, left everything, and followed him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 29, 'Soon Levi held a banquet in his home with Jesus as the guest of honor. Many of Levi''s fellow tax collectors and other guests were there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 30, 'But the Pharisees and their teachers of religious law complained bitterly to Jesus'' disciples, "Why do you eat and drink with such scum?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 31, 'Jesus answered them, "Healthy people don''t need a doctor--sick people do.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 32, 'I have come to call sinners to turn from their sins, not to spend my time with those who think they are already good enough."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 33, 'The religious leaders complained that Jesus'' disciples were feasting instead of fasting. "John the Baptist''s disciples always fast and pray," they declared, "and so do the disciples of the Pharisees. Why are yours always feasting?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 34, 'Jesus asked, "Do wedding guests fast while celebrating with the groom?', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 35, 'Someday he will be taken away from them, and then they will fast."', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 36, 'Then Jesus gave them this illustration: "No one tears a piece of cloth from a new garment and uses it to patch an old garment. For then the new garment would be torn, and the patch wouldn''t even match the old garment.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 37, 'And no one puts new wine into old wineskins. The new wine would burst the old skins, spilling the wine and ruining the skins.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 38, 'New wine must be put into new wineskins.', 'NLT'),
(46, 5, 39, 'But no one who drinks the old wine seems to want the fresh and the new. ''The old is better,'' they say."', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 1, 'One Sabbath day as Jesus was walking through some grainfields, his disciples broke off heads of wheat, rubbed off the husks in their hands, and ate the grains.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 2, 'But some Pharisees said, "You shouldn''t be doing that! It''s against the law to work by harvesting grain on the Sabbath."', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 3, 'Jesus replied, "Haven''t you ever read in the Scriptures what King David did when he and his companions were hungry?', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 4, 'He went into the house of God, ate the special bread reserved for the priests alone, and then gave some to his friends. That was breaking the law, too."', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 5, 'And Jesus added, "I, the Son of Man, am master even of the Sabbath."', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 6, 'On another Sabbath day, a man with a deformed right hand was in the synagogue while Jesus was teaching.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 7, 'The teachers of religious law and the Pharisees watched closely to see whether Jesus would heal the man on the Sabbath, because they were eager to find some legal charge to bring against him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 8, 'But Jesus knew their thoughts. He said to the man with the deformed hand, "Come and stand here where everyone can see." So the man came forward.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 9, 'Then Jesus said to his critics, "I have a question for you. Is it legal to do good deeds on the Sabbath, or is it a day for doing harm? Is this a day to save life or to destroy it?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 10, 'He looked around at them one by one and then said to the man, "Reach out your hand." The man reached out his hand, and it became normal again!', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 11, 'At this, the enemies of Jesus were wild with rage and began to discuss what to do with him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 12, 'One day soon afterward Jesus went to a mountain to pray, and he prayed to God all night.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 13, 'At daybreak he called together all of his disciples and chose twelve of them to be apostles. Here are their names:', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 14, 'Simon (he also called him Peter), Andrew (Peter''s brother), James, John, Philip, Bartholomew,', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 15, 'Matthew, Thomas, James (son of Alphaeus), Simon (the Zealot),', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 16, 'Judas (son of James), Judas Iscariot (who later betrayed him).', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 17, 'When they came down the slopes of the mountain, the disciples stood with Jesus on a large, level area, surrounded by many of his followers and by the crowds. There were people from all over Judea and from Jerusalem and from as far north as the seacoasts of Tyre and Sidon.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 18, 'They had come to hear him and to be healed, and Jesus cast out many evil spirits.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 19, 'Everyone was trying to touch him, because healing power went out from him, and they were all cured.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 20, 'Then Jesus turned to his disciples and said, "God blesses you who are poor, for the Kingdom of God is given to you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 21, 'God blesses you who are hungry now, for you will be satisfied. God blesses you who weep now, for the time will come when you will laugh with joy.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 22, 'God blesses you who are hated and excluded and mocked and cursed because you are identified with me, the Son of Man.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 23, '"When that happens, rejoice! Yes, leap for joy! For a great reward awaits you in heaven. And remember, the ancient prophets were also treated that way by your ancestors.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 24, '"What sorrows await you who are rich, for you have your only happiness now.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 25, 'What sorrows await you who are satisfied and prosperous now, for a time of awful hunger is before you. What sorrows await you who laugh carelessly, for your laughing will turn to mourning and sorrow.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 26, 'What sorrows await you who are praised by the crowds, for their ancestors also praised false prophets.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 27, '"But if you are willing to listen, I say, love your enemies. Do good to those who hate you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 28, 'Pray for the happiness of those who curse you. Pray for those who hurt you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 29, 'If someone slaps you on one cheek, turn the other cheek. If someone demands your coat, offer your shirt also.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 30, 'Give what you have to anyone who asks you for it; and when things are taken away from you, don''t try to get them back.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 31, 'Do for others as you would like them to do for you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 32, '"Do you think you deserve credit merely for loving those who love you? Even the sinners do that!', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 33, 'And if you do good only to those who do good to you, is that so wonderful? Even sinners do that much!', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 34, 'And if you lend money only to those who can repay you, what good is that? Even sinners will lend to their own kind for a full return.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 35, '"Love your enemies! Do good to them! Lend to them! And don''t be concerned that they might not repay. Then your reward from heaven will be very great, and you will truly be acting as children of the Most High, for he is kind to the unthankful and to those who are wicked.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 36, 'You must be compassionate, just as your Father is compassionate.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 37, '"Stop judging others, and you will not be judged. Stop criticizing others, or it will all come back on you. If you forgive others, you will be forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 38, 'If you give, you will receive. Your gift will return to you in full measure, pressed down, shaken together to make room for more, and running over. Whatever measure you use in giving--large or small--it will be used to measure what is given back to you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 39, 'Then Jesus gave the following illustration: "What good is it for one blind person to lead another? The first one will fall into a ditch and pull the other down also.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 40, 'A student is not greater than the teacher. But the student who works hard will become like the teacher.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 41, '"And why worry about a speck in your friend''s eye when you have a log in your own?', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 42, 'How can you think of saying, ''Friend, let me help you get rid of that speck in your eye,'' when you can''t see past the log in your own eye? Hypocrite! First get rid of the log from your own eye; then perhaps you will see well enough to deal with the speck in your friend''s eye.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 43, '"A good tree can''t produce bad fruit, and a bad tree can''t produce good fruit.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 44, 'A tree is identified by the kind of fruit it produces. Figs never grow on thornbushes or grapes on bramble bushes.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 45, 'A good person produces good deeds from a good heart, and an evil person produces evil deeds from an evil heart. Whatever is in your heart determines what you say.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 46, '"So why do you call me ''Lord,'' when you won''t obey me?', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 47, 'I will show you what it''s like when someone comes to me, listens to my teaching, and then obeys me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 48, 'It is like a person who builds a house on a strong foundation laid upon the underlying rock. When the floodwaters rise and break against the house, it stands firm because it is well built.', 'NLT'),
(46, 6, 49, 'But anyone who listens and doesn''t obey is like a person who builds a house without a foundation. When the floods sweep down against that house, it will crumble into a heap of ruins."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 1, 'When Jesus had finished saying all this, he went back to Capernaum.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 2, 'Now the highly valued slave of a Roman officer was sick and near death.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 3, 'When the officer heard about Jesus, he sent some respected Jewish leaders to ask him to come and heal his slave.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 4, 'So they earnestly begged Jesus to come with them and help the man. "If anyone deserves your help, it is he," they said,', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 5, '"for he loves the Jews and even built a synagogue for us."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 6, 'So Jesus went with them. But just before they arrived at the house, the officer sent some friends to say, "Lord, don''t trouble yourself by coming to my home, for I am not worthy of such an honor.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 7, 'I am not even worthy to come and meet you. Just say the word from where you are, and my servant will be healed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 8, 'I know because I am under the authority of my superior officers, and I have authority over my soldiers. I only need to say, ''Go,'' and they go, or ''Come,'' and they come. And if I say to my slaves, ''Do this or that,'' they do it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 9, 'When Jesus heard this, he was amazed. Turning to the crowd, he said, "I tell you, I haven''t seen faith like this in all the land of Israel!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 10, 'And when the officer''s friends returned to his house, they found the slave completely healed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 11, 'Soon afterward Jesus went with his disciples to the village of Nain, with a great crowd following him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 12, 'A funeral procession was coming out as he approached the village gate. The boy who had died was the only son of a widow, and many mourners from the village were with her.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 13, 'When the Lord saw her, his heart overflowed with compassion. "Don''t cry!" he said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 14, 'Then he walked over to the coffin and touched it, and the bearers stopped. "Young man," he said, "get up."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 15, 'Then the dead boy sat up and began to talk to those around him! And Jesus gave him back to his mother.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 16, 'Great fear swept the crowd, and they praised God, saying, "A mighty prophet has risen among us," and "We have seen the hand of God at work today."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 17, 'The report of what Jesus had done that day spread all over Judea and even out across its borders.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 18, 'The disciples of John the Baptist told John about everything Jesus was doing. So John called for two of his disciples,', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 19, 'and he sent them to the Lord to ask him, "Are you the Messiah we''ve been expecting, or should we keep looking for someone else?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 20, 'John''s two disciples found Jesus and said to him, "John the Baptist sent us to ask, ''Are you the Messiah we''ve been expecting, or should we keep looking for someone else?''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 21, 'At that very time, he cured many people of their various diseases, and he cast out evil spirits and restored sight to the blind.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 22, 'Then he told John''s disciples, "Go back to John and tell him what you have seen and heard--the blind see, the lame walk, the lepers are cured, the deaf hear, the dead are raised to life, and the Good News is being preached to the poor.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 23, 'And tell him, ''God blesses those who are not offended by me. ''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 24, 'After they left, Jesus talked to the crowd about John. "Who is this man in the wilderness that you went out to see? Did you find him weak as a reed, moved by every breath of wind?', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 25, 'Or were you expecting to see a man dressed in expensive clothes? No, people who wear beautiful clothes and live in luxury are found in palaces, not in the wilderness.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 26, 'Were you looking for a prophet? Yes, and he is more than a prophet.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 27, 'John is the man to whom the Scriptures refer when they say, ''Look, I am sending my messenger before you, and he will prepare your way before you.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 28, 'I tell you, of all who have ever lived, none is greater than John. Yet even the most insignificant person in the Kingdom of God is greater than he is!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 29, 'When they heard this, all the people, including the unjust tax collectors, agreed that God''s plan was right, for they had been baptized by John.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 30, 'But the Pharisees and experts in religious law had rejected God''s plan for them, for they had refused John''s baptism.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 31, '"How shall I describe this generation?" Jesus asked. "With what will I compare them?', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 32, 'They are like a group of children playing a game in the public square. They complain to their friends, ''We played wedding songs, and you weren''t happy, so we played funeral songs, but you weren''t sad.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 33, 'For John the Baptist didn''t drink wine and he often fasted, and you say, ''He''s demon possessed.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 34, 'And I, the Son of Man, feast and drink, and you say, ''He''s a glutton and a drunkard, and a friend of the worst sort of sinners!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 35, 'But wisdom is shown to be right by the lives of those who follow it. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 36, 'One of the Pharisees asked Jesus to come to his home for a meal, so Jesus accepted the invitation and sat down to eat.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 37, 'A certain immoral woman heard he was there and brought a beautiful jar filled with expensive perfume.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 38, 'Then she knelt behind him at his feet, weeping. Her tears fell on his feet, and she wiped them off with her hair. Then she kept kissing his feet and putting perfume on them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 39, 'When the Pharisee who was the host saw what was happening and who the woman was, he said to himself, "This proves that Jesus is no prophet. If God had really sent him, he would know what kind of woman is touching him. She''s a sinner!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 40, 'Then Jesus spoke up and answered his thoughts. "Simon," he said to the Pharisee, "I have something to say to you.All right, Teacher," Simon replied, "go ahead."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 41, 'Then Jesus told him this story: "A man loaned money to two people--five hundred pieces of silver to one and fifty pieces to the other.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 42, 'But neither of them could repay him, so he kindly forgave them both, canceling their debts. Who do you suppose loved him more after that?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 43, 'Simon answered, "I suppose the one for whom he canceled the larger debt.That''s right," Jesus said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 44, 'Then he turned to the woman and said to Simon, "Look at this woman kneeling here. When I entered your home, you didn''t offer me water to wash the dust from my feet, but she has washed them with her tears and wiped them with her hair.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 45, 'You didn''t give me a kiss of greeting, but she has kissed my feet again and again from the time I first came in.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 46, 'You neglected the courtesy of olive oil to anoint my head, but she has anointed my feet with rare perfume.', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 47, 'I tell you, her sins--and they are many--have been forgiven, so she has shown me much love. But a person who is forgiven little shows only little love."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 48, 'Then Jesus said to the woman, "Your sins are forgiven."', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 49, 'The men at the table said among themselves, "Who does this man think he is, going around forgiving sins?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 7, 50, 'And Jesus said to the woman, "Your faith has saved you; go in peace."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 1, 'Not long afterward Jesus began a tour of the nearby cities and villages to announce the Good News concerning the Kingdom of God. He took his twelve disciples with him,', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 2, 'along with some women he had healed and from whom he had cast out evil spirits. Among them were Mary Magdalene, from whom he had cast out seven demons;', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 3, 'Joanna, the wife of Chuza, Herod''s business manager; Susanna; and many others who were contributing from their own resources to support Jesus and his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 4, 'One day Jesus told this story to a large crowd that had gathered from many towns to hear him:', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 5, '"A farmer went out to plant some seed. As he scattered it across his field, some seed fell on a footpath, where it was stepped on, and the birds came and ate it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 6, 'Other seed fell on shallow soil with underlying rock. This seed began to grow, but soon it withered and died for lack of moisture.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 7, 'Other seed fell among thorns that shot up and choked out the tender blades.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 8, 'Still other seed fell on fertile soil. This seed grew and produced a crop one hundred times as much as had been planted." When he had said this, he called out, "Anyone who is willing to hear should listen and understand!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 9, 'His disciples asked him what the story meant.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 10, 'He replied, "You have been permitted to understand the secrets of the Kingdom of God. But I am using these stories to conceal everything about it from outsiders, so that the Scriptures might be fulfilled: ''They see what I do, but they don''t really see; they hear what I say, but they don''t understand.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 11, '"This is the meaning of the story: The seed is God''s message.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 12, 'The seed that fell on the hard path represents those who hear the message, but then the Devil comes and steals it away and prevents them from believing and being saved.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 13, 'The rocky soil represents those who hear the message with joy. But like young plants in such soil, their roots don''t go very deep. They believe for a while, but they wilt when the hot winds of testing blow.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 14, 'The thorny ground represents those who hear and accept the message, but all too quickly the message is crowded out by the cares and riches and pleasures of this life. And so they never grow into maturity.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 15, 'But the good soil represents honest, good-hearted people who hear God''s message, cling to it, and steadily produce a huge harvest.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 16, '"No one would light a lamp and then cover it up or put it under a bed. No, lamps are mounted in the open, where they can be seen by those entering the house.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 17, 'For everything that is hidden or secret will eventually be brought to light and made plain to all.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 18, 'So be sure to pay attention to what you hear. To those who are open to my teaching, more understanding will be given. But to those who are not listening, even what they think they have will be taken away from them."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 19, 'Once when Jesus'' mother and brothers came to see him, they couldn''t get to him because of the crowds.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 20, 'Someone told Jesus, "Your mother and your brothers are outside, and they want to see you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 21, 'Jesus replied, "My mother and my brothers are all those who hear the message of God and obey it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 22, 'One day Jesus said to his disciples, "Let''s cross over to the other side of the lake." So they got into a boat and started out.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 23, 'On the way across, Jesus lay down for a nap, and while he was sleeping the wind began to rise. A fierce storm developed that threatened to swamp them, and they were in real danger.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 24, 'The disciples woke him up, shouting, "Master, Master, we''re going to drown!" So Jesus rebuked the wind and the raging waves. The storm stopped and all was calm!', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 25, 'Then he asked them, "Where is your faith?" And they were filled with awe and amazement. They said to one another, "Who is this man, that even the winds and waves obey him?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 26, 'So they arrived in the land of the Gerasenes, across the lake from Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 27, 'As Jesus was climbing out of the boat, a man who was possessed by demons came out to meet him. Homeless and naked, he had lived in a cemetery for a long time.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 28, 'As soon as he saw Jesus, he shrieked and fell to the ground before him, screaming, "Why are you bothering me, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? Please, I beg you, don''t torture me!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 29, 'For Jesus had already commanded the evil spirit to come out of him. This spirit had often taken control of the man. Even when he was shackled with chains, he simply broke them and rushed out into the wilderness, completely under the demon''s power.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 30, '"What is your name?" Jesus asked. "Legion," he replied--for the man was filled with many demons.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 31, 'The demons kept begging Jesus not to send them into the Bottomless Pit.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 32, 'A large herd of pigs was feeding on the hillside nearby, and the demons pleaded with him to let them enter into the pigs. Jesus gave them permission.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 33, 'So the demons came out of the man and entered the pigs, and the whole herd plunged down the steep hillside into the lake, where they drowned.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 34, 'When the herdsmen saw it, they fled to the nearby city and the surrounding countryside, spreading the news as they ran.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 35, 'A crowd soon gathered around Jesus, for they wanted to see for themselves what had happened. And they saw the man who had been possessed by demons sitting quietly at Jesus'' feet, clothed and sane. And the whole crowd was afraid.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 36, 'Then those who had seen what happened told the others how the demon-possessed man had been healed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 37, 'And all the people in that region begged Jesus to go away and leave them alone, for a great wave of fear swept over them. So Jesus returned to the boat and left, crossing back to the other side of the lake.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 38, 'The man who had been demon possessed begged to go, too, but Jesus said,', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 39, '"No, go back to your family and tell them all the wonderful things God has done for you." So he went all through the city telling about the great thing Jesus had done for him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 40, 'On the other side of the lake the crowds received Jesus with open arms because they had been waiting for him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 41, 'And now a man named Jairus, a leader of the local synagogue, came and fell down at Jesus'' feet, begging him to come home with him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 42, 'His only child was dying, a little girl twelve years old. As Jesus went with him, he was surrounded by the crowds.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 43, 'And there was a woman in the crowd who had had a hemorrhage for twelve years. She had spent everything she had on doctors and still could find no cure.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 44, 'She came up behind Jesus and touched the fringe of his robe. Immediately, the bleeding stopped.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 45, '"Who touched me?" Jesus asked. Everyone denied it, and Peter said, "Master, this whole crowd is pressing up against you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 46, 'But Jesus told him, "No, someone deliberately touched me, for I felt healing power go out from me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 47, 'When the woman realized that Jesus knew, she began to tremble and fell to her knees before him. The whole crowd heard her explain why she had touched him and that she had been immediately healed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 48, '"Daughter," he said to her, "your faith has made you well. Go in peace."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 49, 'While he was still speaking to her, a messenger arrived from Jairus''s home with the message, "Your little girl is dead. There''s no use troubling the Teacher now."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 50, 'But when Jesus heard what had happened, he said to Jairus, "Don''t be afraid. Just trust me, and she will be all right."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 51, 'When they arrived at the house, Jesus wouldn''t let anyone go in with him except Peter, James, John, and the little girl''s father and mother.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 52, 'The house was filled with people weeping and wailing, but he said, "Stop the weeping! She isn''t dead; she is only asleep."', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 53, 'But the crowd laughed at him because they all knew she had died.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 54, 'Then Jesus took her by the hand and said in a loud voice, "Get up, my child!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 55, 'And at that moment her life returned, and she immediately stood up! Then Jesus told them to give her something to eat.', 'NLT'),
(46, 8, 56, 'Her parents were overwhelmed, but Jesus insisted that they not tell anyone what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 1, 'One day Jesus called together his twelve apostles and gave them power and authority to cast out demons and to heal all diseases.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 2, 'Then he sent them out to tell everyone about the coming of the Kingdom of God and to heal the sick.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 3, '"Don''t even take along a walking stick," he instructed them, "nor a traveler''s bag, nor food, nor money. Not even an extra coat.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 4, 'When you enter each village, be a guest in only one home.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 5, 'If the people of the village won''t receive your message when you enter it, shake off its dust from your feet as you leave. It is a sign that you have abandoned that village to its fate."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 6, 'So they began their circuit of the villages, preaching the Good News and healing the sick.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 7, 'When reports of Jesus'' miracles reached Herod Antipas, he was worried and puzzled because some were saying, "This is John the Baptist come back to life again."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 8, 'Others were saying, "It is Elijah or some other ancient prophet risen from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 9, '"I beheaded John," Herod said, "so who is this man about whom I hear such strange stories?" And he tried to see him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 10, 'When the apostles returned, they told Jesus everything they had done. Then he slipped quietly away with them toward the town of Bethsaida.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 11, 'But the crowds found out where he was going, and they followed him. And he welcomed them, teaching them about the Kingdom of God and curing those who were ill.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 12, 'Late in the afternoon the twelve disciples came to him and said, "Send the crowds away to the nearby villages and farms, so they can find food and lodging for the night. There is nothing to eat here in this deserted place."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 13, 'But Jesus said, "You feed them.Impossible!" they protested. "We have only five loaves of bread and two fish. Or are you expecting us to go and buy enough food for this whole crowd?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 14, 'For there were about five thousand men there. "Just tell them to sit down on the ground in groups of about fifty each," Jesus replied.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 15, 'So the people all sat down.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 16, 'Jesus took the five loaves and two fish, looked up toward heaven, and asked God''s blessing on the food. Breaking the loaves into pieces, he kept giving the bread and fish to the disciples to give to the people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 17, 'They all ate as much as they wanted, and they picked up twelve baskets of leftovers!', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 18, 'One day as Jesus was alone, praying, he came over to his disciples and asked them, "Who do people say I am?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 19, '"Well," they replied, "some say John the Baptist, some say Elijah, and others say you are one of the other ancient prophets risen from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 20, 'Then he asked them, "Who do you say I am?" Peter replied, "You are the Messiah sent from God!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 21, 'Jesus warned them not to tell anyone about this.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 22, '"For I, the Son of Man, must suffer many terrible things," he said. "I will be rejected by the leaders, the leading priests, and the teachers of religious law. I will be killed, but three days later I will be raised from the dead."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 23, 'Then he said to the crowd, "If any of you wants to be my follower, you must put aside your selfish ambition, shoulder your cross daily, and follow me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 24, 'If you try to keep your life for yourself, you will lose it. But if you give up your life for me, you will find true life.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 25, 'And how do you benefit if you gain the whole world but lose or forfeit your own soul in the process?', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 26, 'If a person is ashamed of me and my message, I, the Son of Man, will be ashamed of that person when I return in my glory and in the glory of the Father and the holy angels.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 27, 'And I assure you that some of you standing here right now will not die before you see the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 28, 'About eight days later Jesus took Peter, James, and John to a mountain to pray.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 29, 'And as he was praying, the appearance of his face changed, and his clothing became dazzling white.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 30, 'Then two men, Moses and Elijah, appeared and began talking with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 31, 'They were glorious to see. And they were speaking of how he was about to fulfill God''s plan by dying in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 32, 'Peter and the others were very drowsy and had fallen asleep. Now they woke up and saw Jesus'' glory and the two men standing with him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 33, 'As Moses and Elijah were starting to leave, Peter, not even knowing what he was saying, blurted out, "Master, this is wonderful! We will make three shrines--one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 34, 'But even as he was saying this, a cloud came over them; and terror gripped them as it covered them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 35, 'Then a voice from the cloud said, "This is my Son, my Chosen One. Listen to him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 36, 'When the voice died away, Jesus was there alone. They didn''t tell anyone what they had seen until long after this happened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 37, 'The next day, after they had come down the mountain, a huge crowd met Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 38, 'A man in the crowd called out to him, "Teacher, look at my boy, who is my only son.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 39, 'An evil spirit keeps seizing him, making him scream. It throws him into convulsions so that he foams at the mouth. It is always hitting and injuring him. It hardly ever leaves him alone.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 40, 'I begged your disciples to cast the spirit out, but they couldn''t do it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 41, '"You stubborn, faithless people," Jesus said, "how long must I be with you and put up with you? Bring him here."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 42, 'As the boy came forward, the demon knocked him to the ground and threw him into a violent convulsion. But Jesus rebuked the evil spirit and healed the boy. Then he gave him back to his father.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 43, 'Awe gripped the people as they saw this display of God''s power. While everyone was marveling over all the wonderful things he was doing, Jesus said to his disciples,', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 44, '"Listen to me and remember what I say. The Son of Man is going to be betrayed."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 45, 'But they didn''t know what he meant. Its significance was hidden from them, so they could not understand it, and they were afraid to ask him about it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 46, 'Then there was an argument among them as to which of them would be the greatest.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 47, 'But Jesus knew their thoughts, so he brought a little child to his side.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 48, 'Then he said to them, "Anyone who welcomes a little child like this on my behalf welcomes me, and anyone who welcomes me welcomes my Father who sent me. Whoever is the least among you is the greatest."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 49, 'John said to Jesus, "Master, we saw someone using your name to cast out demons. We tried to stop him because he isn''t in our group."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 50, 'But Jesus said, "Don''t stop him! Anyone who is not against you is for you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 51, 'As the time drew near for his return to heaven, Jesus resolutely set out for Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 52, 'He sent messengers ahead to a Samaritan village to prepare for his arrival.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 53, 'But they were turned away. The people of the village refused to have anything to do with Jesus because he had resolved to go to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 54, 'When James and John heard about it, they said to Jesus, "Lord, should we order down fire from heaven to burn them up?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 55, 'But Jesus turned and rebuked them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 56, 'So they went on to another village.', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 57, 'As they were walking along someone said to Jesus, "I will follow you no matter where you go."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 58, 'But Jesus replied, "Foxes have dens to live in, and birds have nests, but I, the Son of Man, have no home of my own, not even a place to lay my head."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 59, 'He said to another person, "Come, be my disciple." The man agreed, but he said, "Lord, first let me return home and bury my father."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 60, 'Jesus replied, "Let those who are spiritually dead care for their own dead. Your duty is to go and preach the coming of the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 61, 'Another said, "Yes, Lord, I will follow you, but first let me say good-bye to my family."', 'NLT'),
(46, 9, 62, 'But Jesus told him, "Anyone who puts a hand to the plow and then looks back is not fit for the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 1, 'The Lord now chose seventy-two other disciples and sent them on ahead in pairs to all the towns and villages he planned to visit.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 2, 'These were his instructions to them: "The harvest is so great, but the workers are so few. Pray to the Lord who is in charge of the harvest, and ask him to send out more workers for his fields.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 3, 'Go now, and remember that I am sending you out as lambs among wolves.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 4, 'Don''t take along any money, or a traveler''s bag, or even an extra pair of sandals. And don''t stop to greet anyone on the road.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 5, '"Whenever you enter a home, give it your blessing.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 6, 'If those who live there are worthy, the blessing will stand; if they are not, the blessing will return to you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 7, 'When you enter a town, don''t move around from home to home. Stay in one place, eating and drinking what they provide you. Don''t hesitate to accept hospitality, because those who work deserve their pay.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 8, '"If a town welcomes you, eat whatever is set before you', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 9, 'and heal the sick. As you heal them, say, ''The Kingdom of God is near you now.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 10, 'But if a town refuses to welcome you, go out into its streets and say,', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 11, '''We wipe the dust of your town from our feet as a public announcement of your doom. And don''t forget the Kingdom of God is near!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 12, 'The truth is, even wicked Sodom will be better off than such a town on the judgment day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 13, '"What horrors await you, Korazin and Bethsaida! For if the miracles I did in you had been done in wicked Tyre and Sidon, their people would have sat in deep repentance long ago, clothed in sackcloth and throwing ashes on their heads to show their remorse.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 14, 'Yes, Tyre and Sidon will be better off on the judgment day than you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 15, 'And you people of Capernaum, will you be exalted to heaven? No, you will be brought down to the place of the dead. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 16, 'Then he said to the disciples, "Anyone who accepts your message is also accepting me. And anyone who rejects you is rejecting me. And anyone who rejects me is rejecting God who sent me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 17, 'When the seventy-two disciples returned, they joyfully reported to him, "Lord, even the demons obey us when we use your name!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 18, '"Yes," he told them, "I saw Satan falling from heaven as a flash of lightning!', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 19, 'And I have given you authority over all the power of the enemy, and you can walk among snakes and scorpions and crush them. Nothing will injure you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 20, 'But don''t rejoice just because evil spirits obey you; rejoice because your names are registered as citizens of heaven."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 21, 'Then Jesus was filled with the joy of the Holy Spirit and said, "O Father, Lord of heaven and earth, thank you for hiding the truth from those who think themselves so wise and clever, and for revealing it to the childlike. Yes, Father, it pleased you to do it this way.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 22, '"My Father has given me authority over everything. No one really knows the Son except the Father, and no one really knows the Father except the Son and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 23, 'Then when they were alone, he turned to the disciples and said, "How privileged you are to see what you have seen.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 24, 'I tell you, many prophets and kings have longed to see and hear what you have seen and heard, but they could not."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 25, 'One day an expert in religious law stood up to test Jesus by asking him this question: "Teacher, what must I do to receive eternal life?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 26, 'Jesus replied, "What does the law of Moses say? How do you read it?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 27, 'The man answered, "''You must love the Lord your God with all your heart, all your soul, all your strength, and all your mind.'' And, ''Love your neighbor as yourself.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 28, '"Right!" Jesus told him. "Do this and you will live!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 29, 'The man wanted to justify his actions, so he asked Jesus, "And who is my neighbor?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 30, 'Jesus replied with an illustration: "A Jewish man was traveling on a trip from Jerusalem to Jericho, and he was attacked by bandits. They stripped him of his clothes and money, beat him up, and left him half dead beside the road.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 31, '"By chance a Jewish priest came along; but when he saw the man lying there, he crossed to the other side of the road and passed him by.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 32, 'A Temple assistant walked over and looked at him lying there, but he also passed by on the other side.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 33, '"Then a despised Samaritan came along, and when he saw the man, he felt deep pity.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 34, 'Kneeling beside him, the Samaritan soothed his wounds with medicine and bandaged them. Then he put the man on his own donkey and took him to an inn, where he took care of him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 35, 'The next day he handed the innkeeper two pieces of silver and told him to take care of the man. ''If his bill runs higher than that,'' he said, ''I''ll pay the difference the next time I am here.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 36, '"Now which of these three would you say was a neighbor to the man who was attacked by bandits?" Jesus asked.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 37, 'The man replied, "The one who showed him mercy." Then Jesus said, "Yes, now go and do the same."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 38, 'As Jesus and the disciples continued on their way to Jerusalem, they came to a village where a woman named Martha welcomed them into her home.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 39, 'Her sister, Mary, sat at the Lord''s feet, listening to what he taught.', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 40, 'But Martha was worrying over the big dinner she was preparing. She came to Jesus and said, "Lord, doesn''t it seem unfair to you that my sister just sits here while I do all the work? Tell her to come and help me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 41, 'But the Lord said to her, "My dear Martha, you are so upset over all these details!', 'NLT'),
(46, 10, 42, 'There is really only one thing worth being concerned about. Mary has discovered it--and I won''t take it away from her."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 1, 'Once when Jesus had been out praying, one of his disciples came to him as he finished and said, "Lord, teach us to pray, just as John taught his disciples."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 2, 'He said, "This is how you should pray: "Father, may your name be honored. May your Kingdom come soon.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 3, 'Give us our food day by day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 4, 'And forgive us our sins--just as we forgive those who have sinned against us. And don''t let us yield to temptation. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 5, 'Then, teaching them more about prayer, he used this illustration: "Suppose you went to a friend''s house at midnight, wanting to borrow three loaves of bread. You would say to him,', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 6, '''A friend of mine has just arrived for a visit, and I have nothing for him to eat.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 7, 'He would call out from his bedroom, ''Don''t bother me. The door is locked for the night, and we are all in bed. I can''t help you this time.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 8, 'But I tell you this--though he won''t do it as a friend, if you keep knocking long enough, he will get up and give you what you want so his reputation won''t be damaged.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 9, '"And so I tell you, keep on asking, and you will be given what you ask for. Keep on looking, and you will find. Keep on knocking, and the door will be opened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 10, 'For everyone who asks, receives. Everyone who seeks, finds. And the door is opened to everyone who knocks.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 11, '"You fathers--if your children ask for a fish, do you give them a snake instead?', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 12, 'Or if they ask for an egg, do you give them a scorpion? Of course not!', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 13, 'If you sinful people know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 14, 'One day Jesus cast a demon out of a man who couldn''t speak, and the man''s voice returned to him. The crowd was amazed,', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 15, 'but some said, "No wonder he can cast out demons. He gets his power from Satan, the prince of demons!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 16, 'Trying to test Jesus, others asked for a miraculous sign from heaven to see if he was from God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 17, 'He knew their thoughts, so he said, "Any kingdom at war with itself is doomed. A divided home is also doomed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 18, 'You say I am empowered by the prince of demons. But if Satan is fighting against himself by empowering me to cast out his demons, how can his kingdom survive?', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 19, 'And if I am empowered by the prince of demons, what about your own followers? They cast out demons, too, so they will judge you for what you have said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 20, 'But if I am casting out demons by the power of God, then the Kingdom of God has arrived among you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 21, 'For when Satan, who is completely armed, guards his palace, it is safe--', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 22, 'until someone who is stronger attacks and overpowers him, strips him of his weapons, and carries off his belongings.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 23, '"Anyone who isn''t helping me opposes me, and anyone who isn''t working with me is actually working against me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 24, '"When an evil spirit leaves a person, it goes into the desert, searching for rest. But when it finds none, it says, ''I will return to the person I came from.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 25, 'So it returns and finds that its former home is all swept and clean.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 26, 'Then the spirit finds seven other spirits more evil than itself, and they all enter the person and live there. And so that person is worse off than before."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 27, 'As he was speaking, a woman in the crowd called out, "God bless your mother--the womb from which you came, and the breasts that nursed you!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 28, 'He replied, "But even more blessed are all who hear the word of God and put it into practice."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 29, 'As the crowd pressed in on Jesus, he said, "These are evil times, and this evil generation keeps asking me to show them a miraculous sign. But the only sign I will give them is the sign of the prophet Jonah.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 30, 'What happened to him was a sign to the people of Nineveh that God had sent him. What happens to me will be a sign that God has sent me, the Son of Man, to these people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 31, '"The queen of Sheba will rise up against this generation on judgment day and condemn it, because she came from a distant land to hear the wisdom of Solomon. And now someone greater than Solomon is here--and you refuse to listen to him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 32, 'The people of Nineveh, too, will rise up against this generation on judgment day and condemn it, because they repented at the preaching of Jonah. And now someone greater than Jonah is here--and you refuse to repent.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 33, '"No one lights a lamp and then hides it or puts it under a basket. Instead, it is put on a lampstand to give light to all who enter the room.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 34, 'Your eye is a lamp for your body. A pure eye lets sunshine into your soul. But an evil eye shuts out the light and plunges you into darkness.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 35, 'Make sure that the light you think you have is not really darkness.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 36, 'If you are filled with light, with no dark corners, then your whole life will be radiant, as though a floodlight is shining on you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 37, 'As Jesus was speaking, one of the Pharisees invited him home for a meal. So he went in and took his place at the table.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 38, 'His host was amazed to see that he sat down to eat without first performing the ceremonial washing required by Jewish custom.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 39, 'Then the Lord said to him, "You Pharisees are so careful to clean the outside of the cup and the dish, but inside you are still filthy--full of greed and wickedness!', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 40, 'Fools! Didn''t God make the inside as well as the outside?', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 41, 'So give to the needy what you greedily possess, and you will be clean all over.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 42, '"But how terrible it will be for you Pharisees! For you are careful to tithe even the tiniest part of your income, but you completely forget about justice and the love of God. You should tithe, yes, but you should not leave undone the more important things.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 43, '"How terrible it will be for you Pharisees! For how you love the seats of honor in the synagogues and the respectful greetings from everyone as you walk through the markets!', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 44, 'Yes, how terrible it will be for you. For you are like hidden graves in a field. People walk over them without knowing the corruption they are stepping on."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 45, '"Teacher," said an expert in religious law, "you have insulted us, too, in what you just said."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 46, '"Yes," said Jesus, "how terrible it will be for you experts in religious law! For you crush people beneath impossible religious demands, and you never lift a finger to help ease the burden.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 47, 'How terrible it will be for you! For you build tombs for the very prophets your ancestors killed long ago.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 48, 'Murderers! You agree with your ancestors that what they did was right. You would have done the same yourselves.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 49, 'This is what God in his wisdom said about you: ''I will send prophets and apostles to them, and they will kill some and persecute the others.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 50, '"And you of this generation will be held responsible for the murder of all God''s prophets from the creation of the world--', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 51, 'from the murder of Abel to the murder of Zechariah, who was killed between the altar and the sanctuary. Yes, it will surely be charged against you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 52, '"How terrible it will be for you experts in religious law! For you hide the key to knowledge from the people. You don''t enter the Kingdom yourselves, and you prevent others from entering."', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 53, 'As Jesus finished speaking, the Pharisees and teachers of religious law were furious. From that time on they grilled him with many hostile questions,', 'NLT'),
(46, 11, 54, 'trying to trap him into saying something they could use against him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 1, 'Meanwhile, the crowds grew until thousands were milling about and crushing each other. Jesus turned first to his disciples and warned them, "Beware of the yeast of the Pharisees--beware of their hypocrisy.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 2, 'The time is coming when everything will be revealed; all that is secret will be made public.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 3, 'Whatever you have said in the dark will be heard in the light, and what you have whispered behind closed doors will be shouted from the housetops for all to hear!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 4, '"Dear friends, don''t be afraid of those who want to kill you. They can only kill the body; they cannot do any more to you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 5, 'But I''ll tell you whom to fear. Fear God, who has the power to kill people and then throw them into hell.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 6, '"What is the price of five sparrows? A couple of pennies? Yet God does not forget a single one of them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 7, 'And the very hairs on your head are all numbered. So don''t be afraid; you are more valuable to him than a whole flock of sparrows.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 8, '"And I assure you of this: If anyone acknowledges me publicly here on earth, I, the Son of Man, will openly acknowledge that person in the presence of God''s angels.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 9, 'But if anyone denies me here on earth, I will deny that person before God''s angels.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 10, 'Yet those who speak against the Son of Man may be forgiven, but anyone who speaks blasphemies against the Holy Spirit will never be forgiven.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 11, '"And when you are brought to trial in the synagogues and before rulers and authorities, don''t worry about what to say in your defense,', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 12, 'for the Holy Spirit will teach you what needs to be said even as you are standing there."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 13, 'Then someone called from the crowd, "Teacher, please tell my brother to divide our father''s estate with me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 14, 'Jesus replied, "Friend, who made me a judge over you to decide such things as that?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 15, 'Then he said, "Beware! Don''t be greedy for what you don''t have. Real life is not measured by how much we own."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 16, 'And he gave an illustration: "A rich man had a fertile farm that produced fine crops.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 17, 'In fact, his barns were full to overflowing.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 18, 'So he said, ''I know! I''ll tear down my barns and build bigger ones. Then I''ll have room enough to store everything.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 19, 'And I''ll sit back and say to myself, My friend, you have enough stored away for years to come. Now take it easy! Eat, drink, and be merry!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 20, '"But God said to him, ''You fool! You will die this very night. Then who will get it all?''', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 21, '"Yes, a person is a fool to store up earthly wealth but not have a rich relationship with God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 22, 'Then turning to his disciples, Jesus said, "So I tell you, don''t worry about everyday life--whether you have enough food to eat or clothes to wear.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 23, 'For life consists of far more than food and clothing.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 24, 'Look at the ravens. They don''t need to plant or harvest or put food in barns because God feeds them. And you are far more valuable to him than any birds!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 25, 'Can all your worries add a single moment to your life? Of course not!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 26, 'And if worry can''t do little things like that, what''s the use of worrying over bigger things?', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 27, '"Look at the lilies and how they grow. They don''t work or make their clothing, yet Solomon in all his glory was not dressed as beautifully as they are.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 28, 'And if God cares so wonderfully for flowers that are here today and gone tomorrow, won''t he more surely care for you? You have so little faith!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 29, 'And don''t worry about food--what to eat and drink. Don''t worry whether God will provide it for you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 30, 'These things dominate the thoughts of most people, but your Father already knows your needs.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 31, 'He will give you all you need from day to day if you make the Kingdom of God your primary concern.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 32, '"So don''t be afraid, little flock. For it gives your Father great happiness to give you the Kingdom.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 33, '"Sell what you have and give to those in need. This will store up treasure for you in heaven! And the purses of heaven have no holes in them. Your treasure will be safe--no thief can steal it and no moth can destroy it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 34, 'Wherever your treasure is, there your heart and thoughts will also be.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 35, '"Be dressed for service and well prepared,', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 36, 'as though you were waiting for your master to return from the wedding feast. Then you will be ready to open the door and let him in the moment he arrives and knocks.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 37, 'There will be special favor for those who are ready and waiting for his return. I tell you, he himself will seat them, put on an apron, and serve them as they sit and eat!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 38, 'He may come in the middle of the night or just before dawn. But whenever he comes, there will be special favor for his servants who are ready!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 39, '"Know this: A homeowner who knew exactly when a burglar was coming would not permit the house to be broken into.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 40, 'You must be ready all the time, for the Son of Man will come when least expected."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 41, 'Peter asked, "Lord, is this illustration just for us or for everyone?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 42, 'And the Lord replied, "I''m talking to any faithful, sensible servant to whom the master gives the responsibility of managing his household and feeding his family.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 43, 'If the master returns and finds that the servant has done a good job, there will be a reward.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 44, 'I assure you, the master will put that servant in charge of all he owns.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 45, 'But if the servant thinks, ''My master won''t be back for a while,'' and begins oppressing the other servants, partying, and getting drunk--', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 46, 'well, the master will return unannounced and unexpected. He will tear the servant apart and banish him with the unfaithful.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 47, 'The servant will be severely punished, for though he knew his duty, he refused to do it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 48, '"But people who are not aware that they are doing wrong will be punished only lightly. Much is required from those to whom much is given, and much more is required from those to whom much more is given.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 49, '"I have come to bring fire to the earth, and I wish that my task were already completed!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 50, 'There is a terrible baptism ahead of me, and I am under a heavy burden until it is accomplished.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 51, 'Do you think I have come to bring peace to the earth? No, I have come to bring strife and division!', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 52, 'From now on families will be split apart, three in favor of me, and two against--or the other way around.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 53, 'There will be a division between father and son, mother and daughter, mother-in-law and daughter-in-law."', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 54, 'Then Jesus turned to the crowd and said, "When you see clouds beginning to form in the west, you say, ''Here comes a shower.'' And you are right.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 55, 'When the south wind blows, you say, ''Today will be a scorcher.'' And it is.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 56, 'You hypocrites! You know how to interpret the appearance of the earth and the sky, but you can''t interpret these present times.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 57, '"Why can''t you decide for yourselves what is right?', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 58, 'If you are on the way to court and you meet your accuser, try to settle the matter before it reaches the judge, or you may be sentenced and handed over to an officer and thrown in jail.', 'NLT'),
(46, 12, 59, 'And if that happens, you won''t be free again until you have paid the last penny."', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 1, 'About this time Jesus was informed that Pilate had murdered some people from Galilee as they were sacrificing at the Temple in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 2, '"Do you think those Galileans were worse sinners than other people from Galilee?" he asked. "Is that why they suffered?', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 3, 'Not at all! And you will also perish unless you turn from your evil ways and turn to God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 4, 'And what about the eighteen men who died when the Tower of Siloam fell on them? Were they the worst sinners in Jerusalem?', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 5, 'No, and I tell you again that unless you repent, you will also perish."', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 6, 'Then Jesus used this illustration: "A man planted a fig tree in his garden and came again and again to see if there was any fruit on it, but he was always disappointed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 7, 'Finally, he said to his gardener, ''I''ve waited three years, and there hasn''t been a single fig! Cut it down. It''s taking up space we can use for something else.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 8, '"The gardener answered, ''Give it one more chance. Leave it another year, and I''ll give it special attention and plenty of fertilizer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 9, 'If we get figs next year, fine. If not, you can cut it down.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 10, 'One Sabbath day as Jesus was teaching in a synagogue,', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 11, 'he saw a woman who had been crippled by an evil spirit. She had been bent double for eighteen years and was unable to stand up straight.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 12, 'When Jesus saw her, he called her over and said, "Woman, you are healed of your sickness!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 13, 'Then he touched her, and instantly she could stand straight. How she praised and thanked God!', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 14, 'But the leader in charge of the synagogue was indignant that Jesus had healed her on the Sabbath day. "There are six days of the week for working," he said to the crowd. "Come on those days to be healed, not on the Sabbath."', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 15, 'But the Lord replied, "You hypocrite! You work on the Sabbath day! Don''t you untie your ox or your donkey from their stalls on the Sabbath and lead them out for water?', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 16, 'Wasn''t it necessary for me, even on the Sabbath day, to free this dear woman from the bondage in which Satan has held her for eighteen years?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 17, 'This shamed his enemies. And all the people rejoiced at the wonderful things he did.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 18, 'Then Jesus said, "What is the Kingdom of God like? How can I illustrate it?', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 19, 'It is like a tiny mustard seed planted in a garden; it grows and becomes a tree, and the birds come and find shelter among its branches."', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 20, 'He also asked, "What else is the Kingdom of God like?', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 21, 'It is like yeast used by a woman making bread. Even though she used a large amount of flour, the yeast permeated every part of the dough."', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 22, 'Jesus went through the towns and villages, teaching as he went, always pressing on toward Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 23, 'Someone asked him, "Lord, will only a few be saved?" He replied,', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 24, '"The door to heaven is narrow. Work hard to get in, because many will try to enter,', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 25, 'but when the head of the house has locked the door, it will be too late. Then you will stand outside knocking and pleading, ''Lord, open the door for us!'' But he will reply, ''I do not know you.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 26, 'You will say, ''But we ate and drank with you, and you taught in our streets.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 27, 'And he will reply, ''I tell you, I don''t know you. Go away, all you who do evil.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 28, '"And there will be great weeping and gnashing of teeth, for you will see Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, and all the prophets within the Kingdom of God, but you will be thrown out.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 29, 'Then people will come from all over the world to take their places in the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 30, 'And note this: Some who are despised now will be greatly honored then; and some who are greatly honored now will be despised then. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 31, 'A few minutes later some Pharisees said to him, "Get out of here if you want to live, because Herod Antipas wants to kill you!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 32, 'Jesus replied, "Go tell that fox that I will keep on casting out demons and doing miracles of healing today and tomorrow; and the third day I will accomplish my purpose.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 33, 'Yes, today, tomorrow, and the next day I must proceed on my way. For it wouldn''t do for a prophet of God to be killed except in Jerusalem!', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 34, '"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the city that kills the prophets and stones God''s messengers! How often I have wanted to gather your children together as a hen protects her chicks beneath her wings, but you wouldn''t let me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 13, 35, 'And now look, your house is left to you empty. And you will never see me again until you say, ''Bless the one who comes in the name of the Lord!''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 1, 'One Sabbath day Jesus was in the home of a leader of the Pharisees. The people were watching him closely,', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 2, 'because there was a man there whose arms and legs were swollen.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 3, 'Jesus asked the Pharisees and experts in religious law, "Well, is it permitted in the law to heal people on the Sabbath day, or not?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 4, 'When they refused to answer, Jesus touched the sick man and healed him and sent him away.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 5, 'Then he turned to them and asked, "Which of you doesn''t work on the Sabbath? If your son or your cow falls into a pit, don''t you proceed at once to get him out?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 6, 'Again they had no answer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 7, 'When Jesus noticed that all who had come to the dinner were trying to sit near the head of the table, he gave them this advice:', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 8, '"If you are invited to a wedding feast, don''t always head for the best seat. What if someone more respected than you has also been invited?', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 9, 'The host will say, ''Let this person sit here instead.'' Then you will be embarrassed and will have to take whatever seat is left at the foot of the table!', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 10, '"Do this instead--sit at the foot of the table. Then when your host sees you, he will come and say, ''Friend, we have a better place than this for you!'' Then you will be honored in front of all the other guests.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 11, 'For the proud will be humbled, but the humble will be honored."', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 12, 'Then he turned to his host. "When you put on a luncheon or a dinner," he said, "don''t invite your friends, brothers, relatives, and rich neighbors. For they will repay you by inviting you back.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 13, 'Instead, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, and the blind.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 14, 'Then at the resurrection of the godly, God will reward you for inviting those who could not repay you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 15, 'Hearing this, a man sitting at the table with Jesus exclaimed, "What a privilege it would be to have a share in the Kingdom of God!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 16, 'Jesus replied with this illustration: "A man prepared a great feast and sent out many invitations.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 17, 'When all was ready, he sent his servant around to notify the guests that it was time for them to come.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 18, 'But they all began making excuses. One said he had just bought a field and wanted to inspect it, so he asked to be excused.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 19, 'Another said he had just bought five pair of oxen and wanted to try them out.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 20, 'Another had just been married, so he said he couldn''t come.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 21, '"The servant returned and told his master what they had said. His master was angry and said, ''Go quickly into the streets and alleys of the city and invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, and the blind.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 22, 'After the servant had done this, he reported, ''There is still room for more.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 23, 'So his master said, ''Go out into the country lanes and behind the hedges and urge anyone you find to come, so that the house will be full.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 24, 'For none of those I invited first will get even the smallest taste of what I had prepared for them.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 25, 'Great crowds were following Jesus. He turned around and said to them,', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 26, '"If you want to be my follower you must love me more than your own father and mother, wife and children, brothers and sisters--yes, more than your own life. Otherwise, you cannot be my disciple.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 27, 'And you cannot be my disciple if you do not carry your own cross and follow me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 28, '"But don''t begin until you count the cost. For who would begin construction of a building without first getting estimates and then checking to see if there is enough money to pay the bills?', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 29, 'Otherwise, you might complete only the foundation before running out of funds. And then how everyone would laugh at you!', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 30, 'They would say, ''There''s the person who started that building and ran out of money before it was finished!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 31, '"Or what king would ever dream of going to war without first sitting down with his counselors and discussing whether his army of ten thousand is strong enough to defeat the twenty thousand soldiers who are marching against him?', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 32, 'If he is not able, then while the enemy is still far away, he will send a delegation to discuss terms of peace.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 33, 'So no one can become my disciple without giving up everything for me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 34, '"Salt is good for seasoning. But if it loses its flavor, how do you make it salty again?', 'NLT'),
(46, 14, 35, 'Flavorless salt is good neither for the soil nor for fertilizer. It is thrown away. Anyone who is willing to hear should listen and understand!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 1, 'Tax collectors and other notorious sinners often came to listen to Jesus teach.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 2, 'This made the Pharisees and teachers of religious law complain that he was associating with such despicable people--even eating with them!', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 3, 'So Jesus used this illustration:', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 4, '"If you had one hundred sheep, and one of them strayed away and was lost in the wilderness, wouldn''t you leave the ninety-nine others to go and search for the lost one until you found it?', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 5, 'And then you would joyfully carry it home on your shoulders.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 6, 'When you arrived, you would call together your friends and neighbors to rejoice with you because your lost sheep was found.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 7, 'In the same way, heaven will be happier over one lost sinner who returns to God than over ninety-nine others who are righteous and haven''t strayed away!', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 8, '"Or suppose a woman has ten valuable silver coins and loses one. Won''t she light a lamp and look in every corner of the house and sweep every nook and cranny until she finds it?', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 9, 'And when she finds it, she will call in her friends and neighbors to rejoice with her because she has found her lost coin.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 10, 'In the same way, there is joy in the presence of God''s angels when even one sinner repents."', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 11, 'To illustrate the point further, Jesus told them this story: "A man had two sons.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 12, 'The younger son told his father, ''I want my share of your estate now, instead of waiting until you die.'' So his father agreed to divide his wealth between his sons.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 13, '"A few days later this younger son packed all his belongings and took a trip to a distant land, and there he wasted all his money on wild living.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 14, 'About the time his money ran out, a great famine swept over the land, and he began to starve.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 15, 'He persuaded a local farmer to hire him to feed his pigs.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 16, 'The boy became so hungry that even the pods he was feeding the pigs looked good to him. But no one gave him anything.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 17, '"When he finally came to his senses, he said to himself, ''At home even the hired men have food enough to spare, and here I am, dying of hunger!', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 18, 'I will go home to my father and say, "Father, I have sinned against both heaven and you,', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 19, 'and I am no longer worthy of being called your son. Please take me on as a hired man."''', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 20, '"So he returned home to his father. And while he was still a long distance away, his father saw him coming. Filled with love and compassion, he ran to his son, embraced him, and kissed him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 21, 'His son said to him, ''Father, I have sinned against both heaven and you, and I am no longer worthy of being called your son. ''', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 22, '"But his father said to the servants, ''Quick! Bring the finest robe in the house and put it on him. Get a ring for his finger, and sandals for his feet.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 23, 'And kill the calf we have been fattening in the pen. We must celebrate with a feast,', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 24, 'for this son of mine was dead and has now returned to life. He was lost, but now he is found.'' So the party began.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 25, '"Meanwhile, the older son was in the fields working. When he returned home, he heard music and dancing in the house,', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 26, 'and he asked one of the servants what was going on.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 27, '''Your brother is back,'' he was told, ''and your father has killed the calf we were fattening and has prepared a great feast. We are celebrating because of his safe return.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 28, '"The older brother was angry and wouldn''t go in. His father came out and begged him,', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 29, 'but he replied, ''All these years I''ve worked hard for you and never once refused to do a single thing you told me to. And in all that time you never gave me even one young goat for a feast with my friends.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 30, 'Yet when this son of yours comes back after squandering your money on prostitutes, you celebrate by killing the finest calf we have.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 31, '"His father said to him, ''Look, dear son, you and I are very close, and everything I have is yours.', 'NLT'),
(46, 15, 32, 'We had to celebrate this happy day. For your brother was dead and has come back to life! He was lost, but now he is found!''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 1, 'Jesus told this story to his disciples: "A rich man hired a manager to handle his affairs, but soon a rumor went around that the manager was thoroughly dishonest.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 2, 'So his employer called him in and said, ''What''s this I hear about your stealing from me? Get your report in order, because you are going to be dismissed.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 3, '"The manager thought to himself, ''Now what? I''m through here, and I don''t have the strength to go out and dig ditches, and I''m too proud to beg.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 4, 'I know just the thing! And then I''ll have plenty of friends to take care of me when I leave!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 5, '"So he invited each person who owed money to his employer to come and discuss the situation. He asked the first one, ''How much do you owe him?''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 6, 'The man replied, ''I owe him eight hundred gallons of olive oil.'' So the manager told him, ''Tear up that bill and write another one for four hundred gallons. ''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 7, '"''And how much do you owe my employer?'' he asked the next man. ''A thousand bushels of wheat,'' was the reply. ''Here,'' the manager said, ''take your bill and replace it with one for only eight hundred bushels. ''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 8, '"The rich man had to admire the dishonest rascal for being so shrewd. And it is true that the citizens of this world are more shrewd than the godly are.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 9, 'I tell you, use your worldly resources to benefit others and make friends. In this way, your generosity stores up a reward for you in heaven.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 10, '"Unless you are faithful in small matters, you won''t be faithful in large ones. If you cheat even a little, you won''t be honest with greater responsibilities.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 11, 'And if you are untrustworthy about worldly wealth, who will trust you with the true riches of heaven?', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 12, 'And if you are not faithful with other people''s money, why should you be trusted with money of your own?', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 13, '"No one can serve two masters. For you will hate one and love the other, or be devoted to one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money."', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 14, 'The Pharisees, who dearly loved their money, naturally scoffed at all this.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 15, 'Then he said to them, "You like to look good in public, but God knows your evil hearts. What this world honors is an abomination in the sight of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 16, '"Until John the Baptist began to preach, the laws of Moses and the messages of the prophets were your guides. But now the Good News of the Kingdom of God is preached, and eager multitudes are forcing their way in.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 17, 'But that doesn''t mean that the law has lost its force in even the smallest point. It is stronger and more permanent than heaven and earth.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 18, '"Anyone who divorces his wife and marries someone else commits adultery, and anyone who marries a divorced woman commits adultery."', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 19, 'Jesus said, "There was a certain rich man who was splendidly clothed and who lived each day in luxury.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 20, 'At his door lay a diseased beggar named Lazarus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 21, 'As Lazarus lay there longing for scraps from the rich man''s table, the dogs would come and lick his open sores.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 22, 'Finally, the beggar died and was carried by the angels to be with Abraham. The rich man also died and was buried,', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 23, 'and his soul went to the place of the dead. There, in torment, he saw Lazarus in the far distance with Abraham.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 24, '"The rich man shouted, ''Father Abraham, have some pity! Send Lazarus over here to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue, because I am in anguish in these flames.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 25, '"But Abraham said to him, ''Son, remember that during your lifetime you had everything you wanted, and Lazarus had nothing. So now he is here being comforted, and you are in anguish.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 26, 'And besides, there is a great chasm separating us. Anyone who wanted to cross over to you from here is stopped at its edge, and no one there can cross over to us.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 27, '"Then the rich man said, ''Please, Father Abraham, send him to my father''s home.', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 28, 'For I have five brothers, and I want him to warn them about this place of torment so they won''t have to come here when they die.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 29, '"But Abraham said, ''Moses and the prophets have warned them. Your brothers can read their writings anytime they want to.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 30, '"The rich man replied, ''No, Father Abraham! But if someone is sent to them from the dead, then they will turn from their sins.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 16, 31, '"But Abraham said, ''If they won''t listen to Moses and the prophets, they won''t listen even if someone rises from the dead.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 1, 'One day Jesus said to his disciples, "There will always be temptations to sin, but how terrible it will be for the person who does the tempting.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 2, 'It would be better to be thrown into the sea with a large millstone tied around the neck than to face the punishment in store for harming one of these little ones.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 3, 'I am warning you! If another believer sins, rebuke him; then if he repents, forgive him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 4, 'Even if he wrongs you seven times a day and each time turns again and asks forgiveness, forgive him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 5, 'One day the apostles said to the Lord, "We need more faith; tell us how to get it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 6, '"Even if you had faith as small as a mustard seed," the Lord answered, "you could say to this mulberry tree, ''May God uproot you and throw you into the sea,'' and it would obey you!', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 7, '"When a servant comes in from plowing or taking care of sheep, he doesn''t just sit down and eat.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 8, 'He must first prepare his master''s meal and serve him his supper before eating his own.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 9, 'And the servant is not even thanked, because he is merely doing what he is supposed to do.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 10, 'In the same way, when you obey me you should say, ''We are not worthy of praise. We are servants who have simply done our duty.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 11, 'As Jesus continued on toward Jerusalem, he reached the border between Galilee and Samaria.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 12, 'As he entered a village there, ten lepers stood at a distance,', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 13, 'crying out, "Jesus, Master, have mercy on us!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 14, 'He looked at them and said, "Go show yourselves to the priests." And as they went, their leprosy disappeared.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 15, 'One of them, when he saw that he was healed, came back to Jesus, shouting, "Praise God, I''m healed!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 16, 'He fell face down on the ground at Jesus'' feet, thanking him for what he had done. This man was a Samaritan.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 17, 'Jesus asked, "Didn''t I heal ten men? Where are the other nine?', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 18, 'Does only this foreigner return to give glory to God?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 19, 'And Jesus said to the man, "Stand up and go. Your faith has made you well."', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 20, 'One day the Pharisees asked Jesus, "When will the Kingdom of God come?" Jesus replied, "The Kingdom of God isn''t ushered in with visible signs.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 21, 'You won''t be able to say, ''Here it is!'' or ''It''s over there!'' For the Kingdom of God is among you. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 22, 'Later he talked again about this with his disciples. "The time is coming when you will long to share in the days of the Son of Man, but you won''t be able to," he said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 23, '"Reports will reach you that the Son of Man has returned and that he is in this place or that. Don''t believe such reports or go out to look for him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 24, 'For when the Son of Man returns, you will know it beyond all doubt. It will be as evident as the lightning that flashes across the sky.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 25, 'But first the Son of Man must suffer terribly and be rejected by this generation.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 26, '"When the Son of Man returns, the world will be like the people were in Noah''s day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 27, 'In those days before the flood, the people enjoyed banquets and parties and weddings right up to the time Noah entered his boat and the flood came to destroy them all.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 28, '"And the world will be as it was in the days of Lot. People went about their daily business--eating and drinking, buying and selling, farming and building--', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 29, 'until the morning Lot left Sodom. Then fire and burning sulfur rained down from heaven and destroyed them all.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 30, 'Yes, it will be ''business as usual'' right up to the hour when the Son of Man returns.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 31, 'On that day a person outside the house must not go into the house to pack. A person in the field must not return to town.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 32, 'Remember what happened to Lot''s wife!', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 33, 'Whoever clings to this life will lose it, and whoever loses this life will save it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 34, 'That night two people will be asleep in one bed; one will be taken away, and the other will be left.', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 35, 'Two women will be grinding flour together at the mill; one will be taken, the other left. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 36, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(46, 17, 37, '"Lord, where will this happen?" the disciples asked. Jesus replied, "Just as the gathering of vultures shows there is a carcass nearby, so these signs indicate that the end is near."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 1, 'One day Jesus told his disciples a story to illustrate their need for constant prayer and to show them that they must never give up.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 2, '"There was a judge in a certain city," he said, "who was a godless man with great contempt for everyone.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 3, 'A widow of that city came to him repeatedly, appealing for justice against someone who had harmed her.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 4, 'The judge ignored her for a while, but eventually she wore him out. ''I fear neither God nor man,'' he said to himself,', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 5, '''but this woman is driving me crazy. I''m going to see that she gets justice, because she is wearing me out with her constant requests!''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 6, 'Then the Lord said, "Learn a lesson from this evil judge.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 7, 'Even he rendered a just decision in the end, so don''t you think God will surely give justice to his chosen people who plead with him day and night? Will he keep putting them off?', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 8, 'I tell you, he will grant justice to them quickly! But when I, the Son of Man, return, how many will I find who have faith?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 9, 'Then Jesus told this story to some who had great self-confidence and scorned everyone else:', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 10, '"Two men went to the Temple to pray. One was a Pharisee, and the other was a dishonest tax collector.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 11, 'The proud Pharisee stood by himself and prayed this prayer: ''I thank you, God, that I am not a sinner like everyone else, especially like that tax collector over there! For I never cheat, I don''t sin, I don''t commit adultery,', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 12, 'I fast twice a week, and I give you a tenth of my income.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 13, '"But the tax collector stood at a distance and dared not even lift his eyes to heaven as he prayed. Instead, he beat his chest in sorrow, saying, ''O God, be merciful to me, for I am a sinner.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 14, 'I tell you, this sinner, not the Pharisee, returned home justified before God. For the proud will be humbled, but the humble will be honored."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 15, 'One day some parents brought their little children to Jesus so he could touch them and bless them, but the disciples told them not to bother him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 16, 'Then Jesus called for the children and said to the disciples, "Let the children come to me. Don''t stop them! For the Kingdom of God belongs to such as these.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 17, 'I assure you, anyone who doesn''t have their kind of faith will never get into the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 18, 'Once a religious leader asked Jesus this question: "Good teacher, what should I do to get eternal life?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 19, '"Why do you call me good?" Jesus asked him. "Only God is truly good.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 20, 'But as for your question, you know the commandments: ''Do not commit adultery. Do not murder. Do not steal. Do not testify falsely. Honor your father and mother.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 21, 'The man replied, "I''ve obeyed all these commandments since I was a child."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 22, '"There is still one thing you lack," Jesus said. "Sell all you have and give the money to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 23, 'But when the man heard this, he became sad because he was very rich.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 24, 'Jesus watched him go and then said to his disciples, "How hard it is for rich people to get into the Kingdom of God!', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 25, 'It is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle than for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of God!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 26, 'Those who heard this said, "Then who in the world can be saved?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 27, 'He replied, "What is impossible from a human perspective is possible with God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 28, 'Peter said, "We have left our homes and followed you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 29, '"Yes," Jesus replied, "and I assure you, everyone who has given up house or wife or brothers or parents or children, for the sake of the Kingdom of God,', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 30, 'will be repaid many times over in this life, as well as receiving eternal life in the world to come."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 31, 'Gathering the twelve disciples around him, Jesus told them, "As you know, we are going to Jerusalem. And when we get there, all the predictions of the ancient prophets concerning the Son of Man will come true.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 32, 'He will be handed over to the Romans to be mocked, treated shamefully, and spit upon.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 33, 'They will whip him and kill him, but on the third day he will rise again."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 34, 'But they didn''t understand a thing he said. Its significance was hidden from them, and they failed to grasp what he was talking about.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 35, 'As they approached Jericho, a blind beggar was sitting beside the road.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 36, 'When he heard the noise of a crowd going past, he asked what was happening.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 37, 'They told him that Jesus of Nazareth was going by.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 38, 'So he began shouting, "Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 39, 'The crowds ahead of Jesus tried to hush the man, but he only shouted louder, "Son of David, have mercy on me!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 40, 'When Jesus heard him, he stopped and ordered that the man be brought to him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 41, 'Then Jesus asked the man, "What do you want me to do for you?Lord," he pleaded, "I want to see!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 42, 'And Jesus said, "All right, you can see! Your faith has healed you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 18, 43, 'Instantly the man could see, and he followed Jesus, praising God. And all who saw it praised God, too.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 1, 'Jesus entered Jericho and made his way through the town.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 2, 'There was a man there named Zacchaeus. He was one of the most influential Jews in the Roman tax-collecting business, and he had become very rich.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 3, 'He tried to get a look at Jesus, but he was too short to see over the crowds.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 4, 'So he ran ahead and climbed a sycamore tree beside the road, so he could watch from there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 5, 'When Jesus came by, he looked up at Zacchaeus and called him by name. "Zacchaeus!" he said. "Quick, come down! For I must be a guest in your home today."', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 6, 'Zacchaeus quickly climbed down and took Jesus to his house in great excitement and joy.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 7, 'But the crowds were displeased. "He has gone to be the guest of a notorious sinner," they grumbled.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 8, 'Meanwhile, Zacchaeus stood there and said to the Lord, "I will give half my wealth to the poor, Lord, and if I have overcharged people on their taxes, I will give them back four times as much!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 9, 'Jesus responded, "Salvation has come to this home today, for this man has shown himself to be a son of Abraham.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 10, 'And I, the Son of Man, have come to seek and save those like him who are lost."', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 11, 'The crowd was listening to everything Jesus said. And because he was nearing Jerusalem, he told a story to correct the impression that the Kingdom of God would begin right away.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 12, 'He said, "A nobleman was called away to a distant empire to be crowned king and then return.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 13, 'Before he left, he called together ten servants and gave them ten pounds of silver to invest for him while he was gone.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 14, 'But his people hated him and sent a delegation after him to say they did not want him to be their king.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 15, '"When he returned, the king called in the servants to whom he had given the money. He wanted to find out what they had done with the money and what their profits were.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 16, 'The first servant reported a tremendous gain--ten times as much as the original amount!', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 17, '''Well done!'' the king exclaimed. ''You are a trustworthy servant. You have been faithful with the little I entrusted to you, so you will be governor of ten cities as your reward.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 18, '"The next servant also reported a good gain--five times the original amount.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 19, '''Well done!'' the king said. ''You can be governor over five cities.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 20, '"But the third servant brought back only the original amount of money and said, ''I hid it and kept it safe.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 21, 'I was afraid because you are a hard man to deal with, taking what isn''t yours and harvesting crops you didn''t plant.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 22, '"''You wicked servant!'' the king roared. ''Hard, am I? If you knew so much about me and how tough I am,', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 23, 'why didn''t you deposit the money in the bank so I could at least get some interest on it?''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 24, 'Then turning to the others standing nearby, the king ordered, ''Take the money from this servant, and give it to the one who earned the most.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 25, '"''But, master,'' they said, ''that servant has enough already!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 26, '"''Yes,'' the king replied, ''but to those who use well what they are given, even more will be given. But from those who are unfaithful, even what little they have will be taken away.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 27, 'And now about these enemies of mine who didn''t want me to be their king--bring them in and execute them right here in my presence.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 28, 'After telling this story, Jesus went on toward Jerusalem, walking ahead of his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 29, 'As they came to the towns of Bethphage and Bethany, on the Mount of Olives, he sent two disciples ahead.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 30, '"Go into that village over there," he told them, "and as you enter it, you will see a colt tied there that has never been ridden. Untie it and bring it here.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 31, 'If anyone asks what you are doing, just say, ''The Lord needs it.''"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 32, 'So they went and found the colt, just as Jesus had said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 33, 'And sure enough, as they were untying it, the owners asked them, "Why are you untying our colt?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 34, 'And the disciples simply replied, "The Lord needs it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 35, 'So they brought the colt to Jesus and threw their garments over it for him to ride on.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 36, 'Then the crowds spread out their coats on the road ahead of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 37, 'As they reached the place where the road started down from the Mount of Olives, all of his followers began to shout and sing as they walked along, praising God for all the wonderful miracles they had seen.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 38, '"Bless the King who comes in the name of the Lord! Peace in heaven and glory in highest heaven!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 39, 'But some of the Pharisees among the crowd said, "Teacher, rebuke your followers for saying things like that!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 40, 'He replied, "If they kept quiet, the stones along the road would burst into cheers!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 41, 'But as they came closer to Jerusalem and Jesus saw the city ahead, he began to cry.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 42, '"I wish that even today you would find the way of peace. But now it is too late, and peace is hidden from you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 43, 'Before long your enemies will build ramparts against your walls and encircle you and close in on you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 44, 'They will crush you to the ground, and your children with you. Your enemies will not leave a single stone in place, because you have rejected the opportunity God offered you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 45, 'Then Jesus entered the Temple and began to drive out the merchants from their stalls.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 46, 'He told them, "The Scriptures declare, ''My Temple will be a place of prayer,'' but you have turned it into a den of thieves."', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 47, 'After that, he taught daily in the Temple, but the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and the other leaders of the people began planning how to kill him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 19, 48, 'But they could think of nothing, because all the people hung on every word he said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 1, 'One day as Jesus was teaching and preaching the Good News in the Temple, the leading priests and teachers of religious law and other leaders came up to him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 2, 'They demanded, "By whose authority did you drive out the merchants from the Temple? Who gave you such authority?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 3, '"Let me ask you a question first," he replied.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 4, '"Did John''s baptism come from heaven, or was it merely human?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 5, 'They talked it over among themselves. "If we say it was from heaven, he will ask why we didn''t believe him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 6, 'But if we say it was merely human, the people will stone us, because they are convinced he was a prophet."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 7, 'Finally they replied, "We don''t know."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 8, 'And Jesus responded, "Then I won''t answer your question either."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 9, 'Now Jesus turned to the people again and told them this story: "A man planted a vineyard, leased it out to tenant farmers, and moved to another country to live for several years.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 10, 'At grape-picking time, he sent one of his servants to collect his share of the crop. But the farmers attacked the servant, beat him up, and sent him back empty-handed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 11, 'So the owner sent another servant, but the same thing happened; he was beaten up and treated shamefully, and he went away empty-handed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 12, 'A third man was sent and the same thing happened. He, too, was wounded and chased away.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 13, '"''What will I do?'' the owner asked himself. ''I know! I''ll send my cherished son. Surely they will respect him.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 14, '"But when the farmers saw his son, they said to each other, ''Here comes the heir to this estate. Let''s kill him and get the estate for ourselves!''', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 15, 'So they dragged him out of the vineyard and murdered him. "What do you suppose the owner of the vineyard will do to those farmers?" Jesus asked.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 16, '"I''ll tell you--he will come and kill them all and lease the vineyard to others.But God forbid that such a thing should ever happen," his listeners protested.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 17, 'Jesus looked at them and said, "Then what do the Scriptures mean? ''The stone rejected by the builders has now become the cornerstone.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 18, 'All who stumble over that stone will be broken to pieces, and it will crush anyone on whom it falls."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 19, 'When the teachers of religious law and the leading priests heard this story, they wanted to arrest Jesus immediately because they realized he was pointing at them--that they were the farmers in the story. But they were afraid there would be a riot if they arrested him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 20, 'Watching for their opportunity, the leaders sent secret agents pretending to be honest men. They tried to get Jesus to say something that could be reported to the Roman governor so he would arrest Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 21, 'They said, "Teacher, we know that you speak and teach what is right and are not influenced by what others think. You sincerely teach the ways of God.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 22, 'Now tell us--is it right to pay taxes to the Roman government or not?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 23, 'He saw through their trickery and said,', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 24, '"Show me a Roman coin. Whose picture and title are stamped on it?Caesar''s," they replied.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 25, '"Well then," he said, "give to Caesar what belongs to him. But everything that belongs to God must be given to God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 26, 'So they failed to trap him in the presence of the people. Instead, they were amazed by his answer, and they were silenced.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 27, 'Then some Sadducees stepped forward--a group of Jews who say there is no resurrection after death.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 28, 'They posed this question: "Teacher, Moses gave us a law that if a man dies, leaving a wife but no children, his brother should marry the widow and have a child who will be the brother''s heir.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 29, 'Well, there were seven brothers. The oldest married and then died without children.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 30, 'His brother married the widow, but he also died. Still no children.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 31, 'And so it went, one after the other, until each of the seven had married her and died, leaving no children.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 32, 'Finally, the woman died, too.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 33, 'So tell us, whose wife will she be in the resurrection? For all seven were married to her!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 34, 'Jesus replied, "Marriage is for people here on earth.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 35, 'But that is not the way it will be in the age to come. For those worthy of being raised from the dead won''t be married then.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 36, 'And they will never die again. In these respects they are like angels. They are children of God raised up to new life.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 37, 'But now, as to whether the dead will be raised--even Moses proved this when he wrote about the burning bush. Long after Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob had died, he referred to the Lord as ''the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 38, 'So he is the God of the living, not the dead. They are all alive to him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 39, '"Well said, Teacher!" remarked some of the teachers of religious law who were standing there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 40, 'And that ended their questions; no one dared to ask any more.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 41, 'Then Jesus presented them with a question. "Why is it," he asked, "that the Messiah is said to be the son of David?', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 42, 'For David himself wrote in the book of Psalms: ''The LORD said to my Lord, Sit in honor at my right hand', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 43, 'until I humble your enemies, making them a footstool under your feet.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 44, 'Since David called him Lord, how can he be his son at the same time?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 45, 'Then, with the crowds listening, he turned to his disciples and said,', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 46, '"Beware of these teachers of religious law! For they love to parade in flowing robes and to have everyone bow to them as they walk in the marketplaces. And how they love the seats of honor in the synagogues and at banquets.', 'NLT'),
(46, 20, 47, 'But they shamelessly cheat widows out of their property, and then, to cover up the kind of people they really are, they make long prayers in public. Because of this, their punishment will be the greater."', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 1, 'While Jesus was in the Temple, he watched the rich people putting their gifts into the collection box.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 2, 'Then a poor widow came by and dropped in two pennies.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 3, '"I assure you," he said, "this poor widow has given more than all the rest of them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 4, 'For they have given a tiny part of their surplus, but she, poor as she is, has given everything she has."', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 5, 'Some of his disciples began talking about the beautiful stonework of the Temple and the memorial decorations on the walls. But Jesus said,', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 6, '"The time is coming when all these things will be so completely demolished that not one stone will be left on top of another."', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 7, '"Teacher," they asked, "when will all this take place? And will there be any sign ahead of time?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 8, 'He replied, "Don''t let anyone mislead you. For many will come in my name, claiming to be the Messiah and saying, ''The time has come!'' But don''t believe them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 9, 'And when you hear of wars and insurrections, don''t panic. Yes, these things must come, but the end won''t follow immediately."', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 10, 'Then he added, "Nations and kingdoms will proclaim war against each other.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 11, 'There will be great earthquakes, and there will be famines and epidemics in many lands, and there will be terrifying things and great miraculous signs in the heavens.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 12, '"But before all this occurs, there will be a time of great persecution. You will be dragged into synagogues and prisons, and you will be accused before kings and governors of being my followers.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 13, 'This will be your opportunity to tell them about me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 14, 'So don''t worry about how to answer the charges against you,', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 15, 'for I will give you the right words and such wisdom that none of your opponents will be able to reply!', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 16, 'Even those closest to you--your parents, brothers, relatives, and friends--will betray you. And some of you will be killed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 17, 'And everyone will hate you because of your allegiance to me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 18, 'But not a hair of your head will perish!', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 19, 'By standing firm, you will win your souls.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 20, '"And when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then you will know that the time of its destruction has arrived.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 21, 'Then those in Judea must flee to the hills. Let those in Jerusalem escape, and those outside the city should not enter it for shelter.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 22, 'For those will be days of God''s vengeance, and the prophetic words of the Scriptures will be fulfilled.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 23, 'How terrible it will be for pregnant women and for mothers nursing their babies. For there will be great distress in the land and wrath upon this people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 24, 'They will be brutally killed by the sword or sent away as captives to all the nations of the world. And Jerusalem will be conquered and trampled down by the Gentiles until the age of the Gentiles comes to an end.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 25, '"And there will be strange events in the skies--signs in the sun, moon, and stars. And down here on earth the nations will be in turmoil, perplexed by the roaring seas and strange tides.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 26, 'The courage of many people will falter because of the fearful fate they see coming upon the earth, because the stability of the very heavens will be broken up.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 27, 'Then everyone will see the Son of Man arrive on the clouds with power and great glory.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 28, 'So when all these things begin to happen, stand straight and look up, for your salvation is near!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 29, 'Then he gave them this illustration: "Notice the fig tree, or any other tree.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 30, 'When the leaves come out, you know without being told that summer is near.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 31, 'Just so, when you see the events I''ve described taking place, you can be sure that the Kingdom of God is near.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 32, 'I assure you, this generation will not pass from the scene until all these events have taken place.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 33, 'Heaven and earth will disappear, but my words will remain forever.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 34, '"Watch out! Don''t let me find you living in careless ease and drunkenness, and filled with the worries of this life. Don''t let that day catch you unaware,', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 35, 'as in a trap. For that day will come upon everyone living on the earth.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 36, 'Keep a constant watch. And pray that, if possible, you may escape these horrors and stand before the Son of Man."', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 37, 'Every day Jesus went to the Temple to teach, and each evening he returned to spend the night on the Mount of Olives.', 'NLT'),
(46, 21, 38, 'The crowds gathered early each morning to hear him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 1, 'The Festival of Unleavened Bread, which begins with the Passover celebration, was drawing near.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 2, 'The leading priests and teachers of religious law were actively plotting Jesus'' murder. But they wanted to kill him without starting a riot, a possibility they greatly feared.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 3, 'Then Satan entered into Judas Iscariot, who was one of the twelve disciples,', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 4, 'and he went over to the leading priests and captains of the Temple guard to discuss the best way to betray Jesus to them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 5, 'They were delighted that he was ready to help them, and they promised him a reward.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 6, 'So he began looking for an opportunity to betray Jesus so they could arrest him quietly when the crowds weren''t around.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 7, 'Now the Festival of Unleavened Bread arrived, when the Passover lambs were sacrificed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 8, 'Jesus sent Peter and John ahead and said, "Go and prepare the Passover meal, so we can eat it together."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 9, '"Where do you want us to go?" they asked him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 10, 'He replied, "As soon as you enter Jerusalem, a man carrying a pitcher of water will meet you. Follow him. At the house he enters,', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 11, 'say to the owner, ''The Teacher asks, Where is the guest room where I can eat the Passover meal with my disciples?''', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 12, 'He will take you upstairs to a large room that is already set up. That is the place. Go ahead and prepare our supper there."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 13, 'They went off to the city and found everything just as Jesus had said, and they prepared the Passover supper there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 14, 'Then at the proper time Jesus and the twelve apostles sat down together at the table.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 15, 'Jesus said, "I have looked forward to this hour with deep longing, anxious to eat this Passover meal with you before my suffering begins.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 16, 'For I tell you now that I won''t eat it again until it comes to fulfillment in the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 17, 'Then he took a cup of wine, and when he had given thanks for it, he said, "Take this and share it among yourselves.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 18, 'For I will not drink wine again until the Kingdom of God has come."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 19, 'Then he took a loaf of bread; and when he had thanked God for it, he broke it in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, "This is my body, given for you. Do this in remembrance of me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 20, 'After supper he took another cup of wine and said, "This wine is the token of God''s new covenant to save you--an agreement sealed with the blood I will pour out for you.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 21, '"But here at this table, sitting among us as a friend, is the man who will betray me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 22, 'For I, the Son of Man, must die since it is part of God''s plan. But how terrible it will be for my betrayer!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 23, 'Then the disciples began to ask each other which of them would ever do such a thing.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 24, 'And they began to argue among themselves as to who would be the greatest in the coming Kingdom.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 25, 'Jesus told them, "In this world the kings and great men order their people around, and yet they are called ''friends of the people.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 26, 'But among you, those who are the greatest should take the lowest rank, and the leader should be like a servant.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 27, 'Normally the master sits at the table and is served by his servants. But not here! For I am your servant.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 28, 'You have remained true to me in my time of trial.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 29, 'And just as my Father has granted me a Kingdom, I now grant you the right', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 30, 'to eat and drink at my table in that Kingdom. And you will sit on thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 31, '"Simon, Simon, Satan has asked to have all of you, to sift you like wheat.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 32, 'But I have pleaded in prayer for you, Simon, that your faith should not fail. So when you have repented and turned to me again, strengthen and build up your brothers."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 33, 'Peter said, "Lord, I am ready to go to prison with you, and even to die with you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 34, 'But Jesus said, "Peter, let me tell you something. The rooster will not crow tomorrow morning until you have denied three times that you even know me."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 35, 'Then Jesus asked them, "When I sent you out to preach the Good News and you did not have money, a traveler''s bag, or extra clothing, did you lack anything?No," they replied.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 36, '"But now," he said, "take your money and a traveler''s bag. And if you don''t have a sword, sell your clothes and buy one!', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 37, 'For the time has come for this prophecy about me to be fulfilled: ''He was counted among those who were rebels.'' Yes, everything written about me by the prophets will come true."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 38, '"Lord," they replied, "we have two swords among us.That''s enough," he said.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 39, 'Then, accompanied by the disciples, Jesus left the upstairs room and went as usual to the Mount of Olives.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 40, 'There he told them, "Pray that you will not be overcome by temptation."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 41, 'He walked away, about a stone''s throw, and knelt down and prayed,', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 42, '"Father, if you are willing, please take this cup of suffering away from me. Yet I want your will, not mine."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 43, 'Then an angel from heaven appeared and strengthened him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 44, 'He prayed more fervently, and he was in such agony of spirit that his sweat fell to the ground like great drops of blood.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 45, 'At last he stood up again and returned to the disciples, only to find them asleep, exhausted from grief.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 46, '"Why are you sleeping?" he asked. "Get up and pray. Otherwise temptation will overpower you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 47, 'But even as he said this, a mob approached, led by Judas, one of his twelve disciples. Judas walked over to Jesus and greeted him with a kiss.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 48, 'But Jesus said, "Judas, how can you betray me, the Son of Man, with a kiss?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 49, 'When the other disciples saw what was about to happen, they exclaimed, "Lord, should we fight? We brought the swords!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 50, 'And one of them slashed at the high priest''s servant and cut off his right ear.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 51, 'But Jesus said, "Don''t resist anymore." And he touched the place where the man''s ear had been and healed him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 52, 'Then Jesus spoke to the leading priests and captains of the Temple guard and the other leaders who headed the mob. "Am I some dangerous criminal," he asked, "that you have come armed with swords and clubs to arrest me?', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 53, 'Why didn''t you arrest me in the Temple? I was there every day. But this is your moment, the time when the power of darkness reigns."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 54, 'So they arrested him and led him to the high priest''s residence, and Peter was following far behind.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 55, 'The guards lit a fire in the courtyard and sat around it, and Peter joined them there.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 56, 'A servant girl noticed him in the firelight and began staring at him. Finally she said, "This man was one of Jesus'' followers!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 57, 'Peter denied it. "Woman," he said, "I don''t even know the man!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 58, 'After a while someone else looked at him and said, "You must be one of them!No, man, I''m not!" Peter replied.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 59, 'About an hour later someone else insisted, "This must be one of Jesus'' disciples because he is a Galilean, too."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 60, 'But Peter said, "Man, I don''t know what you are talking about." And as soon as he said these words, the rooster crowed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 61, 'At that moment the Lord turned and looked at Peter. Then Peter remembered that the Lord had said, "Before the rooster crows tomorrow morning, you will deny me three times."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 62, 'And Peter left the courtyard, crying bitterly.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 63, 'Now the guards in charge of Jesus began mocking and beating him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 64, 'They blindfolded him; then they hit him and asked, "Who hit you that time, you prophet?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 65, 'And they threw all sorts of terrible insults at him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 66, 'At daybreak all the leaders of the people assembled, including the leading priests and the teachers of religious law. Jesus was led before this high council,', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 67, 'and they said, "Tell us if you are the Messiah." But he replied, "If I tell you, you won''t believe me.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 68, 'And if I ask you a question, you won''t answer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 69, 'But the time is soon coming when I, the Son of Man, will be sitting at God''s right hand in the place of power."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 70, 'They all shouted, "Then you claim you are the Son of God?" And he replied, "You are right in saying that I am."', 'NLT'),
(46, 22, 71, '"What need do we have for other witnesses?" they shouted. "We ourselves heard him say it."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 1, 'Then the entire council took Jesus over to Pilate, the Roman governor.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 2, 'They began at once to state their case: "This man has been leading our people to ruin by telling them not to pay their taxes to the Roman government and by claiming he is the Messiah, a king."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 3, 'So Pilate asked him, "Are you the King of the Jews?" Jesus replied, "Yes, it is as you say."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 4, 'Pilate turned to the leading priests and to the crowd and said, "I find nothing wrong with this man!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 5, 'Then they became desperate. "But he is causing riots everywhere he goes, all over Judea, from Galilee to Jerusalem!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 6, '"Oh, is he a Galilean?" Pilate asked.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 7, 'When they answered that he was, Pilate sent him to Herod Antipas, because Galilee was under Herod''s jurisdiction, and Herod happened to be in Jerusalem at the time.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 8, 'Herod was delighted at the opportunity to see Jesus, because he had heard about him and had been hoping for a long time to see him perform a miracle.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 9, 'He asked Jesus question after question, but Jesus refused to answer.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 10, 'Meanwhile, the leading priests and the teachers of religious law stood there shouting their accusations.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 11, 'Now Herod and his soldiers began mocking and ridiculing Jesus. Then they put a royal robe on him and sent him back to Pilate.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 12, 'Herod and Pilate, who had been enemies before, became friends that day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 13, 'Then Pilate called together the leading priests and other religious leaders, along with the people,', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 14, 'and he announced his verdict. "You brought this man to me, accusing him of leading a revolt. I have examined him thoroughly on this point in your presence and find him innocent.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 15, 'Herod came to the same conclusion and sent him back to us. Nothing this man has done calls for the death penalty.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 16, 'So I will have him flogged, but then I will release him."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 17, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 18, 'Then a mighty roar rose from the crowd, and with one voice they shouted, "Kill him, and release Barabbas to us!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 19, '(Barabbas was in prison for murder and for taking part in an insurrection in Jerusalem against the government.)', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 20, 'Pilate argued with them, because he wanted to release Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 21, 'But they shouted, "Crucify him! Crucify him!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 22, 'For the third time he demanded, "Why? What crime has he committed? I have found no reason to sentence him to death. I will therefore flog him and let him go."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 23, 'But the crowd shouted louder and louder for Jesus'' death, and their voices prevailed.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 24, 'So Pilate sentenced Jesus to die as they demanded.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 25, 'As they had requested, he released Barabbas, the man in prison for insurrection and murder. But he delivered Jesus over to them to do as they wished.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 26, 'As they led Jesus away, Simon of Cyrene, who was coming in from the country just then, was forced to follow Jesus and carry his cross.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 27, 'Great crowds trailed along behind, including many grief-stricken women.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 28, 'But Jesus turned and said to them, "Daughters of Jerusalem, don''t weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 29, 'For the days are coming when they will say, ''Fortunate indeed are the women who are childless, the wombs that have not borne a child and the breasts that have never nursed.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 30, 'People will beg the mountains to fall on them and the hills to bury them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 31, 'For if these things are done when the tree is green, what will happen when it is dry? "', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 32, 'Two others, both criminals, were led out to be executed with him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 33, 'Finally, they came to a place called The Skull. All three were crucified there--Jesus on the center cross, and the two criminals on either side.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 34, 'Jesus said, "Father, forgive these people, because they don''t know what they are doing." And the soldiers gambled for his clothes by throwing dice.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 35, 'The crowd watched, and the leaders laughed and scoffed. "He saved others," they said, "let him save himself if he is really God''s Chosen One, the Messiah."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 36, 'The soldiers mocked him, too, by offering him a drink of sour wine.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 37, 'They called out to him, "If you are the King of the Jews, save yourself!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 38, 'A signboard was nailed to the cross above him with these words: "This is the King of the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 39, 'One of the criminals hanging beside him scoffed, "So you''re the Messiah, are you? Prove it by saving yourself--and us, too, while you''re at it!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 40, 'But the other criminal protested, "Don''t you fear God even when you are dying?', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 41, 'We deserve to die for our evil deeds, but this man hasn''t done anything wrong."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 42, 'Then he said, "Jesus, remember me when you come into your Kingdom."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 43, 'And Jesus replied, "I assure you, today you will be with me in paradise."', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 44, 'By this time it was noon, and darkness fell across the whole land until three o''clock.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 45, 'The light from the sun was gone. And suddenly, the thick veil hanging in the Temple was torn apart.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 46, 'Then Jesus shouted, "Father, I entrust my spirit into your hands!" And with those words he breathed his last.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 47, 'When the captain of the Roman soldiers handling the executions saw what had happened, he praised God and said, "Surely this man was innocent. "', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 48, 'And when the crowd that came to see the crucifixion saw all that had happened, they went home in deep sorrow.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 49, 'But Jesus'' friends, including the women who had followed him from Galilee, stood at a distance watching.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 50, 'Now there was a good and righteous man named Joseph. He was a member of the Jewish high council,', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 51, 'but he had not agreed with the decision and actions of the other religious leaders. He was from the town of Arimathea in Judea, and he had been waiting for the Kingdom of God to come.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 52, 'He went to Pilate and asked for Jesus'' body.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 53, 'Then he took the body down from the cross and wrapped it in a long linen cloth and laid it in a new tomb that had been carved out of rock.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 54, 'This was done late on Friday afternoon, the day of preparation for the Sabbath.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 55, 'As his body was taken away, the women from Galilee followed and saw the tomb where they placed his body.', 'NLT'),
(46, 23, 56, 'Then they went home and prepared spices and ointments to embalm him. But by the time they were finished it was the Sabbath, so they rested all that day as required by the law.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 1, 'But very early on Sunday morning the women came to the tomb, taking the spices they had prepared.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 2, 'They found that the stone covering the entrance had been rolled aside.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 3, 'So they went in, but they couldn''t find the body of the Lord Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 4, 'They were puzzled, trying to think what could have happened to it. Suddenly, two men appeared to them, clothed in dazzling robes.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 5, 'The women were terrified and bowed low before them. Then the men asked, "Why are you looking in a tomb for someone who is alive?', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 6, 'He isn''t here! He has risen from the dead! Don''t you remember what he told you back in Galilee,', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 7, 'that the Son of Man must be betrayed into the hands of sinful men and be crucified, and that he would rise again the third day?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 8, 'Then they remembered that he had said this.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 9, 'So they rushed back to tell his eleven disciples--and everyone else--what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 10, 'The women who went to the tomb were Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary the mother of James, and several others. They told the apostles what had happened,', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 11, 'but the story sounded like nonsense, so they didn''t believe it.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 12, 'However, Peter ran to the tomb to look. Stooping, he peered in and saw the empty linen wrappings; then he went home again, wondering what had happened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 13, 'That same day two of Jesus'' followers were walking to the village of Emmaus, seven miles out of Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 14, 'As they walked along they were talking about everything that had happened.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 15, 'Suddenly, Jesus himself came along and joined them and began walking beside them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 16, 'But they didn''t know who he was, because God kept them from recognizing him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 17, '"You seem to be in a deep discussion about something," he said. "What are you so concerned about?" They stopped short, sadness written across their faces.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 18, 'Then one of them, Cleopas, replied, "You must be the only person in Jerusalem who hasn''t heard about all the things that have happened there the last few days."', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 19, '"What things?" Jesus asked. "The things that happened to Jesus, the man from Nazareth," they said. "He was a prophet who did wonderful miracles. He was a mighty teacher, highly regarded by both God and all the people.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 20, 'But our leading priests and other religious leaders arrested him and handed him over to be condemned to death, and they crucified him.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 21, 'We had thought he was the Messiah who had come to rescue Israel. That all happened three days ago.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 22, 'Then some women from our group of his followers were at his tomb early this morning, and they came back with an amazing report.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 23, 'They said his body was missing, and they had seen angels who told them Jesus is alive!', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 24, 'Some of our men ran out to see, and sure enough, Jesus'' body was gone, just as the women had said."', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 25, 'Then Jesus said to them, "You are such foolish people! You find it so hard to believe all that the prophets wrote in the Scriptures.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 26, 'Wasn''t it clearly predicted by the prophets that the Messiah would have to suffer all these things before entering his time of glory?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 27, 'Then Jesus quoted passages from the writings of Moses and all the prophets, explaining what all the Scriptures said about himself.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 28, 'By this time they were nearing Emmaus and the end of their journey. Jesus would have gone on,', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 29, 'but they begged him to stay the night with them, since it was getting late. So he went home with them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 30, 'As they sat down to eat, he took a small loaf of bread, asked God''s blessing on it, broke it, then gave it to them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 31, 'Suddenly, their eyes were opened, and they recognized him. And at that moment he disappeared!', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 32, 'They said to each other, "Didn''t our hearts feel strangely warm as he talked with us on the road and explained the Scriptures to us?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 33, 'And within the hour they were on their way back to Jerusalem, where the eleven disciples and the other followers of Jesus were gathered. When they arrived, they were greeted with the report,', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 34, '"The Lord has really risen! He appeared to Peter!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 35, 'Then the two from Emmaus told their story of how Jesus had appeared to them as they were walking along the road and how they had recognized him as he was breaking the bread.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 36, 'And just as they were telling about it, Jesus himself was suddenly standing there among them. He said, "Peace be with you."', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 37, 'But the whole group was terribly frightened, thinking they were seeing a ghost!', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 38, '"Why are you frightened?" he asked. "Why do you doubt who I am?', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 39, 'Look at my hands. Look at my feet. You can see that it''s really me. Touch me and make sure that I am not a ghost, because ghosts don''t have bodies, as you see that I do!"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 40, 'As he spoke, he held out his hands for them to see, and he showed them his feet.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 41, 'Still they stood there doubting, filled with joy and wonder. Then he asked them, "Do you have anything here to eat?"', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 42, 'They gave him a piece of broiled fish,', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 43, 'and he ate it as they watched.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 44, 'Then he said, "When I was with you before, I told you that everything written about me by Moses and the prophets and in the Psalms must all come true."', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 45, 'Then he opened their minds to understand these many Scriptures.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 46, 'And he said, "Yes, it was written long ago that the Messiah must suffer and die and rise again from the dead on the third day.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 47, 'With my authority, take this message of repentance to all the nations, beginning in Jerusalem: ''There is forgiveness of sins for all who turn to me.''', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 48, 'You are witnesses of all these things.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 49, '"And now I will send the Holy Spirit, just as my Father promised. But stay here in the city until the Holy Spirit comes and fills you with power from heaven."', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 50, 'Then Jesus led them to Bethany, and lifting his hands to heaven, he blessed them.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 51, 'While he was blessing them, he left them and was taken up to heaven.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 52, 'They worshiped him and then returned to Jerusalem filled with great joy.', 'NLT'),
(46, 24, 53, 'And they spent all of their time in the Temple, praising God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 1, 'In the beginning the Word already existed. He was with God, and he was God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 2, 'He was in the beginning with God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 3, 'He created everything there is. Nothing exists that he didn''t make.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 4, 'Life itself was in him, and this life gives light to everyone.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 5, 'The light shines through the darkness, and the darkness can never extinguish it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 6, 'God sent John the Baptist', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 7, 'to tell everyone about the light so that everyone might believe because of his testimony.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 8, 'John himself was not the light; he was only a witness to the light.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 9, 'The one who is the true light, who gives light to everyone, was going to come into the world.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 10, 'But although the world was made through him, the world didn''t recognize him when he came.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 11, 'Even in his own land and among his own people, he was not accepted.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 12, 'But to all who believed him and accepted him, he gave the right to become children of God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 13, 'They are reborn! This is not a physical birth resulting from human passion or plan--this rebirth comes from God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 14, 'So the Word became human and lived here on earth among us. He was full of unfailing love and faithfulness. And we have seen his glory, the glory of the only Son of the Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 15, 'John pointed him out to the people. He shouted to the crowds, "This is the one I was talking about when I said, ''Someone is coming who is far greater than I am, for he existed long before I did.''"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 16, 'We have all benefited from the rich blessings he brought to us--one gracious blessing after another.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 17, 'For the law was given through Moses; God''s unfailing love and faithfulness came through Jesus Christ.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 18, 'No one has ever seen God. But his only Son, who is himself God, is near to the Father''s heart; he has told us about him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 19, 'This was the testimony of John when the Jewish leaders sent priests and Temple assistants from Jerusalem to ask John whether he claimed to be the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 20, 'He flatly denied it. "I am not the Messiah," he said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 21, '"Well then, who are you?" they asked. "Are you Elijah?No," he replied. "Are you the Prophet?No."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 22, '"Then who are you? Tell us, so we can give an answer to those who sent us. What do you have to say about yourself?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 23, 'John replied in the words of Isaiah: "I am a voice shouting in the wilderness, ''Prepare a straight pathway for the Lord''s coming!''"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 24, 'Then those who were sent by the Pharisees', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 25, 'asked him, "If you aren''t the Messiah or Elijah or the Prophet, what right do you have to baptize?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 26, 'John told them, "I baptize with water, but right here in the crowd is someone you do not know,', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 27, 'who will soon begin his ministry. I am not even worthy to be his slave. "', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 28, 'This incident took place at Bethany, a village east of the Jordan River, where John was baptizing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 29, 'The next day John saw Jesus coming toward him and said, "Look! There is the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world!', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 30, 'He is the one I was talking about when I said, ''Soon a man is coming who is far greater than I am, for he existed long before I did.''', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 31, 'I didn''t know he was the one, but I have been baptizing with water in order to point him out to Israel."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 32, 'Then John said, "I saw the Holy Spirit descending like a dove from heaven and resting upon him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 33, 'I didn''t know he was the one, but when God sent me to baptize with water, he told me, ''When you see the Holy Spirit descending and resting upon someone, he is the one you are looking for. He is the one who baptizes with the Holy Spirit.''', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 34, 'I saw this happen to Jesus, so I testify that he is the Son of God. "', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 35, 'The following day, John was again standing with two of his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 36, 'As Jesus walked by, John looked at him and then declared, "Look! There is the Lamb of God!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 37, 'Then John''s two disciples turned and followed Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 38, 'Jesus looked around and saw them following. "What do you want?" he asked them. They replied, "Rabbi" (which means Teacher), "where are you staying?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 39, '"Come and see," he said. It was about four o''clock in the afternoon when they went with him to the place, and they stayed there the rest of the day.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 40, 'Andrew, Simon Peter''s brother, was one of these men who had heard what John said and then followed Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 41, 'The first thing Andrew did was to find his brother, Simon, and tell him, "We have found the Messiah" (which means the Christ).', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 42, 'Then Andrew brought Simon to meet Jesus. Looking intently at Simon, Jesus said, "You are Simon, the son of John--but you will be called Cephas" (which means Peter ).', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 43, 'The next day Jesus decided to go to Galilee. He found Philip and said to him, "Come, be my disciple."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 44, 'Philip was from Bethsaida, Andrew and Peter''s hometown.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 45, 'Philip went off to look for Nathanael and told him, "We have found the very person Moses and the prophets wrote about! His name is Jesus, the son of Joseph from Nazareth."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 46, '"Nazareth!" exclaimed Nathanael. "Can anything good come from there?Just come and see for yourself," Philip said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 47, 'As they approached, Jesus said, "Here comes an honest man--a true son of Israel."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 48, '"How do you know about me?" Nathanael asked. And Jesus replied, "I could see you under the fig tree before Philip found you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 49, 'Nathanael replied, "Teacher, you are the Son of God--the King of Israel!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 50, 'Jesus asked him, "Do you believe all this just because I told you I had seen you under the fig tree? You will see greater things than this."', 'NLT'),
(6, 1, 51, 'Then he said, "The truth is, you will all see heaven open and the angels of God going up and down upon the Son of Man."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 1, 'The next day Jesus'' mother was a guest at a wedding celebration in the village of Cana in Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 2, 'Jesus and his disciples were also invited to the celebration.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 3, 'The wine supply ran out during the festivities, so Jesus'' mother spoke to him about the problem. "They have no more wine," she told him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 4, '"How does that concern you and me?" Jesus asked. "My time has not yet come."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 5, 'But his mother told the servants, "Do whatever he tells you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 6, 'Six stone waterpots were standing there; they were used for Jewish ceremonial purposes and held twenty to thirty gallons each.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 7, 'Jesus told the servants, "Fill the jars with water." When the jars had been filled to the brim,', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 8, 'he said, "Dip some out and take it to the master of ceremonies." So they followed his instructions.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 9, 'When the master of ceremonies tasted the water that was now wine, not knowing where it had come from (though, of course, the servants knew), he called the bridegroom over.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 10, '"Usually a host serves the best wine first," he said. "Then, when everyone is full and doesn''t care, he brings out the less expensive wines. But you have kept the best until now!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 11, 'This miraculous sign at Cana in Galilee was Jesus'' first display of his glory. And his disciples believed in him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 12, 'After the wedding he went to Capernaum for a few days with his mother, his brothers, and his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 13, 'It was time for the annual Passover celebration, and Jesus went to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 14, 'In the Temple area he saw merchants selling cattle, sheep, and doves for sacrifices; and he saw money changers behind their counters.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 15, 'Jesus made a whip from some ropes and chased them all out of the Temple. He drove out the sheep and oxen, scattered the money changers'' coins over the floor, and turned over their tables.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 16, 'Then, going over to the people who sold doves, he told them, "Get these things out of here. Don''t turn my Father''s house into a marketplace!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 17, 'Then his disciples remembered this prophecy from the Scriptures: "Passion for God''s house burns within me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 18, '"What right do you have to do these things?" the Jewish leaders demanded. "If you have this authority from God, show us a miraculous sign to prove it."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 19, '"All right," Jesus replied. "Destroy this temple, and in three days I will raise it up."', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 20, '"What!" they exclaimed. "It took forty-six years to build this Temple, and you can do it in three days?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 21, 'But by "this temple," Jesus meant his body.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 22, 'After he was raised from the dead, the disciples remembered that he had said this. And they believed both Jesus and the Scriptures.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 23, 'Because of the miraculous signs he did in Jerusalem at the Passover celebration, many people were convinced that he was indeed the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 24, 'But Jesus didn''t trust them, because he knew what people were really like.', 'NLT'),
(6, 2, 25, 'No one needed to tell him about human nature.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 1, 'After dark one evening, a Jewish religious leader named Nicodemus, a Pharisee,', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 2, 'came to speak with Jesus. "Teacher," he said, "we all know that God has sent you to teach us. Your miraculous signs are proof enough that God is with you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 3, 'Jesus replied, "I assure you, unless you are born again, you can never see the Kingdom of God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 4, '"What do you mean?" exclaimed Nicodemus. "How can an old man go back into his mother''s womb and be born again?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 5, 'Jesus replied, "The truth is, no one can enter the Kingdom of God without being born of water and the Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 6, 'Humans can reproduce only human life, but the Holy Spirit gives new life from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 7, 'So don''t be surprised at my statement that you must be born again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 8, 'Just as you can hear the wind but can''t tell where it comes from or where it is going, so you can''t explain how people are born of the Spirit."', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 9, '"What do you mean?" Nicodemus asked.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 10, 'Jesus replied, "You are a respected Jewish teacher, and yet you don''t understand these things?', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 11, 'I assure you, I am telling you what we know and have seen, and yet you won''t believe us.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 12, 'But if you don''t even believe me when I tell you about things that happen here on earth, how can you possibly believe if I tell you what is going on in heaven?', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 13, 'For only I, the Son of Man, have come to earth and will return to heaven again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 14, 'And as Moses lifted up the bronze snake on a pole in the wilderness, so I, the Son of Man, must be lifted up on a pole,', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 15, 'so that everyone who believes in me will have eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 16, '"For God so loved the world that he gave his only Son, so that everyone who believes in him will not perish but have eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 17, 'God did not send his Son into the world to condemn it, but to save it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 18, '"There is no judgment awaiting those who trust him. But those who do not trust him have already been judged for not believing in the only Son of God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 19, 'Their judgment is based on this fact: The light from heaven came into the world, but they loved the darkness more than the light, for their actions were evil.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 20, 'They hate the light because they want to sin in the darkness. They stay away from the light for fear their sins will be exposed and they will be punished.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 21, 'But those who do what is right come to the light gladly, so everyone can see that they are doing what God wants."', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 22, 'Afterward Jesus and his disciples left Jerusalem, but they stayed in Judea for a while and baptized there.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 23, 'At this time John the Baptist was baptizing at Aenon, near Salim, because there was plenty of water there and people kept coming to him for baptism.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 24, 'This was before John was put into prison.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 25, 'At that time a certain Jew began an argument with John''s disciples over ceremonial cleansing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 26, 'John''s disciples came to him and said, "Teacher, the man you met on the other side of the Jordan River, the one you said was the Messiah, is also baptizing people. And everybody is going over there instead of coming here to us."', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 27, 'John replied, "God in heaven appoints each person''s work.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 28, 'You yourselves know how plainly I told you that I am not the Messiah. I am here to prepare the way for him--that is all.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 29, 'The bride will go where the bridegroom is. A bridegroom''s friend rejoices with him. I am the bridegroom''s friend, and I am filled with joy at his success.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 30, 'He must become greater and greater, and I must become less and less.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 31, '"He has come from above and is greater than anyone else. I am of the earth, and my understanding is limited to the things of earth, but he has come from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 32, 'He tells what he has seen and heard, but how few believe what he tells them!', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 33, 'Those who believe him discover that God is true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 34, 'For he is sent by God. He speaks God''s words, for God''s Spirit is upon him without measure or limit.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 35, 'The Father loves his Son, and he has given him authority over everything.', 'NLT'),
(6, 3, 36, 'And all who believe in God''s Son have eternal life. Those who don''t obey the Son will never experience eternal life, but the wrath of God remains upon them."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 1, 'Jesus learned that the Pharisees had heard, "Jesus is baptizing and making more disciples than John"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 2, '(though Jesus himself didn''t baptize them--his disciples did).', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 3, 'So he left Judea to return to Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 4, 'He had to go through Samaria on the way.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 5, 'Eventually he came to the Samaritan village of Sychar, near the parcel of ground that Jacob gave to his son Joseph.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 6, 'Jacob''s well was there; and Jesus, tired from the long walk, sat wearily beside the well about noontime.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 7, 'Soon a Samaritan woman came to draw water, and Jesus said to her, "Please give me a drink."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 8, 'He was alone at the time because his disciples had gone into the village to buy some food.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 9, 'The woman was surprised, for Jews refuse to have anything to do with Samaritans. She said to Jesus, "You are a Jew, and I am a Samaritan woman. Why are you asking me for a drink?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 10, 'Jesus replied, "If you only knew the gift God has for you and who I am, you would ask me, and I would give you living water."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 11, '"But sir, you don''t have a rope or a bucket," she said, "and this is a very deep well. Where would you get this living water?', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 12, 'And besides, are you greater than our ancestor Jacob who gave us this well? How can you offer better water than he and his sons and his cattle enjoyed?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 13, 'Jesus replied, "People soon become thirsty again after drinking this water.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 14, 'But the water I give them takes away thirst altogether. It becomes a perpetual spring within them, giving them eternal life."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 15, '"Please, sir," the woman said, "give me some of that water! Then I''ll never be thirsty again, and I won''t have to come here to haul water."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 16, '"Go and get your husband," Jesus told her.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 17, '"I don''t have a husband," the woman replied. Jesus said, "You''re right! You don''t have a husband--', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 18, 'for you have had five husbands, and you aren''t even married to the man you''re living with now."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 19, '"Sir," the woman said, "you must be a prophet.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 20, 'So tell me, why is it that you Jews insist that Jerusalem is the only place of worship, while we Samaritans claim it is here at Mount Gerizim, where our ancestors worshiped?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 21, 'Jesus replied, "Believe me, the time is coming when it will no longer matter whether you worship the Father here or in Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 22, 'You Samaritans know so little about the one you worship, while we Jews know all about him, for salvation comes through the Jews.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 23, 'But the time is coming and is already here when true worshipers will worship the Father in spirit and in truth. The Father is looking for anyone who will worship him that way.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 24, 'For God is Spirit, so those who worship him must worship in spirit and in truth."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 25, 'The woman said, "I know the Messiah will come--the one who is called Christ. When he comes, he will explain everything to us."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 26, 'Then Jesus told her, "I am the Messiah!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 27, 'Just then his disciples arrived. They were astonished to find him talking to a woman, but none of them asked him why he was doing it or what they had been discussing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 28, 'The woman left her water jar beside the well and went back to the village and told everyone,', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 29, '"Come and meet a man who told me everything I ever did! Can this be the Messiah?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 30, 'So the people came streaming from the village to see him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 31, 'Meanwhile, the disciples were urging Jesus to eat.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 32, '"No," he said, "I have food you don''t know about."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 33, '"Who brought it to him?" the disciples asked each other.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 34, 'Then Jesus explained: "My nourishment comes from doing the will of God, who sent me, and from finishing his work.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 35, 'Do you think the work of harvesting will not begin until the summer ends four months from now? Look around you! Vast fields are ripening all around us and are ready now for the harvest.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 36, 'The harvesters are paid good wages, and the fruit they harvest is people brought to eternal life. What joy awaits both the planter and the harvester alike!', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 37, 'You know the saying, ''One person plants and someone else harvests.'' And it''s true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 38, 'I sent you to harvest where you didn''t plant; others had already done the work, and you will gather the harvest."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 39, 'Many Samaritans from the village believed in Jesus because the woman had said, "He told me everything I ever did!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 40, 'When they came out to see him, they begged him to stay at their village. So he stayed for two days,', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 41, 'long enough for many of them to hear his message and believe.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 42, 'Then they said to the woman, "Now we believe because we have heard him ourselves, not just because of what you told us. He is indeed the Savior of the world."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 43, 'At the end of the two days'' stay, Jesus went on into Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 44, 'He had previously said, "A prophet is honored everywhere except in his own country."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 45, 'The Galileans welcomed him, for they had been in Jerusalem at the Passover celebration and had seen all his miraculous signs.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 46, 'In the course of his journey through Galilee, he arrived at the town of Cana, where he had turned the water into wine. There was a government official in the city of Capernaum whose son was very sick.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 47, 'When he heard that Jesus had come from Judea and was traveling in Galilee, he went over to Cana. He found Jesus and begged him to come to Capernaum with him to heal his son, who was about to die.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 48, 'Jesus asked, "Must I do miraculous signs and wonders before you people will believe in me?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 49, 'The official pleaded, "Lord, please come now before my little boy dies."', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 50, 'Then Jesus told him, "Go back home. Your son will live!" And the man believed Jesus'' word and started home.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 51, 'While he was on his way, some of his servants met him with the news that his son was alive and well.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 52, 'He asked them when the boy had begun to feel better, and they replied, "Yesterday afternoon at one o''clock his fever suddenly disappeared!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 53, 'Then the father realized it was the same time that Jesus had told him, "Your son will live." And the officer and his entire household believed in Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 4, 54, 'This was Jesus'' second miraculous sign in Galilee after coming from Judea.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 1, 'Afterward Jesus returned to Jerusalem for one of the Jewish holy days.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 2, 'Inside the city, near the Sheep Gate, was the pool of Bethesda, with five covered porches.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 3, 'Crowds of sick people--blind, lame, or paralyzed--lay on the porches.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 4, 'See Footnote', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 5, 'One of the men lying there had been sick for thirty-eight years.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 6, 'When Jesus saw him and knew how long he had been ill, he asked him, "Would you like to get well?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 7, '"I can''t, sir," the sick man said, "for I have no one to help me into the pool when the water is stirred up. While I am trying to get there, someone else always gets in ahead of me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 8, 'Jesus told him, "Stand up, pick up your sleeping mat, and walk!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 9, 'Instantly, the man was healed! He rolled up the mat and began walking! But this miracle happened on the Sabbath day.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 10, 'So the Jewish leaders objected. They said to the man who was cured, "You can''t work on the Sabbath! It''s illegal to carry that sleeping mat!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 11, 'He replied, "The man who healed me said to me, ''Pick up your sleeping mat and walk.''"', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 12, '"Who said such a thing as that?" they demanded.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 13, 'The man didn''t know, for Jesus had disappeared into the crowd.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 14, 'But afterward Jesus found him in the Temple and told him, "Now you are well; so stop sinning, or something even worse may happen to you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 15, 'Then the man went to find the Jewish leaders and told them it was Jesus who had healed him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 16, 'So the Jewish leaders began harassing Jesus for breaking the Sabbath rules.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 17, 'But Jesus replied, "My Father never stops working, so why should I?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 18, 'So the Jewish leaders tried all the more to kill him. In addition to disobeying the Sabbath rules, he had spoken of God as his Father, thereby making himself equal with God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 19, 'Jesus replied, "I assure you, the Son can do nothing by himself. He does only what he sees the Father doing. Whatever the Father does, the Son also does.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 20, 'For the Father loves the Son and tells him everything he is doing, and the Son will do far greater things than healing this man. You will be astonished at what he does.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 21, 'He will even raise from the dead anyone he wants to, just as the Father does.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 22, 'And the Father leaves all judgment to his Son,', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 23, 'so that everyone will honor the Son, just as they honor the Father. But if you refuse to honor the Son, then you are certainly not honoring the Father who sent him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 24, '"I assure you, those who listen to my message and believe in God who sent me have eternal life. They will never be condemned for their sins, but they have already passed from death into life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 25, '"And I assure you that the time is coming, in fact it is here, when the dead will hear my voice--the voice of the Son of God. And those who listen will live.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 26, 'The Father has life in himself, and he has granted his Son to have life in himself.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 27, 'And he has given him authority to judge all mankind because he is the Son of Man.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 28, 'Don''t be so surprised! Indeed, the time is coming when all the dead in their graves will hear the voice of God''s Son,', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 29, 'and they will rise again. Those who have done good will rise to eternal life, and those who have continued in evil will rise to judgment.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 30, 'But I do nothing without consulting the Father. I judge as I am told. And my judgment is absolutely just, because it is according to the will of God who sent me; it is not merely my own.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 31, '"If I were to testify on my own behalf, my testimony would not be valid.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 32, 'But someone else is also testifying about me, and I can assure you that everything he says about me is true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 33, 'In fact, you sent messengers to listen to John the Baptist, and he preached the truth.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 34, 'But the best testimony about me is not from a man, though I have reminded you about John''s testimony so you might be saved.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 35, 'John shone brightly for a while, and you benefited and rejoiced.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 36, 'But I have a greater witness than John--my teachings and my miracles. They have been assigned to me by the Father, and they testify that the Father has sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 37, 'And the Father himself has also testified about me. You have never heard his voice or seen him face to face,', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 38, 'and you do not have his message in your hearts, because you do not believe me--the one he sent to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 39, '"You search the Scriptures because you believe they give you eternal life. But the Scriptures point to me!', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 40, 'Yet you refuse to come to me so that I can give you this eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 41, '"Your approval or disapproval means nothing to me,', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 42, 'because I know you don''t have God''s love within you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 43, 'For I have come to you representing my Father, and you refuse to welcome me, even though you readily accept others who represent only themselves.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 44, 'No wonder you can''t believe! For you gladly honor each other, but you don''t care about the honor that comes from God alone.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 45, '"Yet it is not I who will accuse you of this before the Father. Moses will accuse you! Yes, Moses, on whom you set your hopes.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 46, 'But if you had believed Moses, you would have believed me because he wrote about me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 5, 47, 'And since you don''t believe what he wrote, how will you believe what I say?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 1, 'After this, Jesus crossed over the Sea of Galilee, also known as the Sea of Tiberias.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 2, 'And a huge crowd kept following him wherever he went, because they saw his miracles as he healed the sick.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 3, 'Then Jesus went up into the hills and sat down with his disciples around him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 4, '(It was nearly time for the annual Passover celebration.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 5, 'Jesus soon saw a great crowd of people climbing the hill, looking for him. Turning to Philip, he asked, "Philip, where can we buy bread to feed all these people?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 6, 'He was testing Philip, for he already knew what he was going to do.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 7, 'Philip replied, "It would take a small fortune to feed them!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 8, 'Then Andrew, Simon Peter''s brother, spoke up.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 9, '"There''s a young boy here with five barley loaves and two fish. But what good is that with this huge crowd?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 10, '"Tell everyone to sit down," Jesus ordered. So all of them--the men alone numbered five thousand--sat down on the grassy slopes.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 11, 'Then Jesus took the loaves, gave thanks to God, and passed them out to the people. Afterward he did the same with the fish. And they all ate until they were full.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 12, '"Now gather the leftovers," Jesus told his disciples, "so that nothing is wasted."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 13, 'There were only five barley loaves to start with, but twelve baskets were filled with the pieces of bread the people did not eat!', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 14, 'When the people saw this miraculous sign, they exclaimed, "Surely, he is the Prophet we have been expecting!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 15, 'Jesus saw that they were ready to take him by force and make him king, so he went higher into the hills alone.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 16, 'That evening his disciples went down to the shore to wait for him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 17, 'But as darkness fell and Jesus still hadn''t come back, they got into the boat and headed out across the lake toward Capernaum.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 18, 'Soon a gale swept down upon them as they rowed, and the sea grew very rough.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 19, 'They were three or four miles out when suddenly they saw Jesus walking on the water toward the boat. They were terrified,', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 20, 'but he called out to them, "I am here! Don''t be afraid."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 21, 'Then they were eager to let him in, and immediately the boat arrived at their destination!', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 22, 'The next morning, back across the lake, crowds began gathering on the shore, waiting to see Jesus. For they knew that he and his disciples had come over together and that the disciples had gone off in their boat, leaving him behind.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 23, 'Several boats from Tiberias landed near the place where the Lord had blessed the bread and the people had eaten.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 24, 'When the crowd saw that Jesus wasn''t there, nor his disciples, they got into the boats and went across to Capernaum to look for him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 25, 'When they arrived and found him, they asked, "Teacher, how did you get here?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 26, 'Jesus replied, "The truth is, you want to be with me because I fed you, not because you saw the miraculous sign.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 27, 'But you shouldn''t be so concerned about perishable things like food. Spend your energy seeking the eternal life that I, the Son of Man, can give you. For God the Father has sent me for that very purpose."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 28, 'They replied, "What does God want us to do?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 29, 'Jesus told them, "This is what God wants you to do: Believe in the one he has sent."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 30, 'They replied, "You must show us a miraculous sign if you want us to believe in you. What will you do for us?', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 31, 'After all, our ancestors ate manna while they journeyed through the wilderness! As the Scriptures say, ''Moses gave them bread from heaven to eat.''"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 32, 'Jesus said, "I assure you, Moses didn''t give them bread from heaven. My Father did. And now he offers you the true bread from heaven.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 33, 'The true bread of God is the one who comes down from heaven and gives life to the world."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 34, '"Sir," they said, "give us that bread every day of our lives."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 35, 'Jesus replied, "I am the bread of life. No one who comes to me will ever be hungry again. Those who believe in me will never thirst.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 36, 'But you haven''t believed in me even though you have seen me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 37, 'However, those the Father has given me will come to me, and I will never reject them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 38, 'For I have come down from heaven to do the will of God who sent me, not to do what I want.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 39, 'And this is the will of God, that I should not lose even one of all those he has given me, but that I should raise them to eternal life at the last day.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 40, 'For it is my Father''s will that all who see his Son and believe in him should have eternal life--that I should raise them at the last day."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 41, 'Then the people began to murmur in disagreement because he had said, "I am the bread from heaven."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 42, 'They said, "This is Jesus, the son of Joseph. We know his father and mother. How can he say, ''I came down from heaven''?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 43, 'But Jesus replied, "Don''t complain about what I said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 44, 'For people can''t come to me unless the Father who sent me draws them to me, and at the last day I will raise them from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 45, 'As it is written in the Scriptures, ''They will all be taught by God.'' Everyone who hears and learns from the Father comes to me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 46, '(Not that anyone has ever seen the Father; only I, who was sent from God, have seen him.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 47, '"I assure you, anyone who believes in me already has eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 48, 'Yes, I am the bread of life!', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 49, 'Your ancestors ate manna in the wilderness, but they all died.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 50, 'However, the bread from heaven gives eternal life to everyone who eats it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 51, 'I am the living bread that came down out of heaven. Anyone who eats this bread will live forever; this bread is my flesh, offered so the world may live."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 52, 'Then the people began arguing with each other about what he meant. "How can this man give us his flesh to eat?" they asked.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 53, 'So Jesus said again, "I assure you, unless you eat the flesh of the Son of Man and drink his blood, you cannot have eternal life within you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 54, 'But those who eat my flesh and drink my blood have eternal life, and I will raise them at the last day.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 55, 'For my flesh is the true food, and my blood is the true drink.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 56, 'All who eat my flesh and drink my blood remain in me, and I in them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 57, 'I live by the power of the living Father who sent me; in the same way, those who partake of me will live because of me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 58, 'I am the true bread from heaven. Anyone who eats this bread will live forever and not die as your ancestors did, even though they ate the manna."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 59, 'He said these things while he was teaching in the synagogue in Capernaum.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 60, 'Even his disciples said, "This is very hard to understand. How can anyone accept it?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 61, 'Jesus knew within himself that his disciples were complaining, so he said to them, "Does this offend you?', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 62, 'Then what will you think if you see me, the Son of Man, return to heaven again?', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 63, 'It is the Spirit who gives eternal life. Human effort accomplishes nothing. And the very words I have spoken to you are spirit and life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 64, 'But some of you don''t believe me." (For Jesus knew from the beginning who didn''t believe, and he knew who would betray him.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 65, 'Then he said, "That is what I meant when I said that people can''t come to me unless the Father brings them to me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 66, 'At this point many of his disciples turned away and deserted him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 67, 'Then Jesus turned to the Twelve and asked, "Are you going to leave, too?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 68, 'Simon Peter replied, "Lord, to whom would we go? You alone have the words that give eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 69, 'We believe them, and we know you are the Holy One of God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 70, 'Then Jesus said, "I chose the twelve of you, but one is a devil."', 'NLT'),
(6, 6, 71, 'He was speaking of Judas, son of Simon Iscariot, one of the Twelve, who would betray him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 1, 'After this, Jesus stayed in Galilee, going from village to village. He wanted to stay out of Judea where the Jewish leaders were plotting his death.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 2, 'But soon it was time for the Festival of Shelters,', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 3, 'and Jesus'' brothers urged him to go to Judea for the celebration. "Go where your followers can see your miracles!" they scoffed.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 4, '"You can''t become a public figure if you hide like this! If you can do such wonderful things, prove it to the world!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 5, 'For even his brothers didn''t believe in him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 6, 'Jesus replied, "Now is not the right time for me to go. But you can go anytime, and it will make no difference.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 7, 'The world can''t hate you, but it does hate me because I accuse it of sin and evil.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 8, 'You go on. I am not yet ready to go to this festival, because my time has not yet come."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 9, 'So Jesus remained in Galilee.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 10, 'But after his brothers had left for the festival, Jesus also went, though secretly, staying out of public view.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 11, 'The Jewish leaders tried to find him at the festival and kept asking if anyone had seen him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 12, 'There was a lot of discussion about him among the crowds. Some said, "He''s a wonderful man," while others said, "He''s nothing but a fraud, deceiving the people."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 13, 'But no one had the courage to speak favorably about him in public, for they were afraid of getting in trouble with the Jewish leaders.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 14, 'Then, midway through the festival, Jesus went up to the Temple and began to teach.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 15, 'The Jewish leaders were surprised when they heard him. "How does he know so much when he hasn''t studied everything we''ve studied?" they asked.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 16, 'So Jesus told them, "I''m not teaching my own ideas, but those of God who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 17, 'Anyone who wants to do the will of God will know whether my teaching is from God or is merely my own.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 18, 'Those who present their own ideas are looking for praise for themselves, but those who seek to honor the one who sent them are good and genuine.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 19, 'None of you obeys the law of Moses! In fact, you are trying to kill me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 20, 'The crowd replied, "You''re demon possessed! Who''s trying to kill you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 21, 'Jesus replied, "I worked on the Sabbath by healing a man, and you were offended.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 22, 'But you work on the Sabbath, too, when you obey Moses'' law of circumcision. (Actually, this tradition of circumcision is older than the law of Moses; it goes back to Abraham.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 23, 'For if the correct time for circumcising your son falls on the Sabbath, you go ahead and do it, so as not to break the law of Moses. So why should I be condemned for making a man completely well on the Sabbath?', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 24, 'Think this through and you will see that I am right."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 25, 'Some of the people who lived there in Jerusalem said among themselves, "Isn''t this the man they are trying to kill?', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 26, 'But here he is, speaking in public, and they say nothing to him. Can it be that our leaders know that he really is the Messiah?', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 27, 'But how could he be? For we know where this man comes from. When the Messiah comes, he will simply appear; no one will know where he comes from."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 28, 'While Jesus was teaching in the Temple, he called out, "Yes, you know me, and you know where I come from. But I represent one you don''t know, and he is true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 29, 'I know him because I have come from him, and he sent me to you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 30, 'Then the leaders tried to arrest him; but no one laid a hand on him, because his time had not yet come.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 31, 'Many among the crowds at the Temple believed in him. "After all," they said, "would you expect the Messiah to do more miraculous signs than this man has done?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 32, 'When the Pharisees heard that the crowds were murmuring such things, they and the leading priests sent Temple guards to arrest Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 33, 'But Jesus told them, "I will be here a little longer. Then I will return to the one who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 34, 'You will search for me but not find me. And you won''t be able to come where I am."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 35, 'The Jewish leaders were puzzled by this statement. "Where is he planning to go?" they asked. "Maybe he is thinking of leaving the country and going to the Jews in other lands, or maybe even to the Gentiles!', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 36, 'What does he mean when he says, ''You will search for me but not find me,'' and ''You won''t be able to come where I am''?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 37, 'On the last day, the climax of the festival, Jesus stood and shouted to the crowds, "If you are thirsty, come to me!', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 38, 'If you believe in me, come and drink! For the Scriptures declare that rivers of living water will flow out from within."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 39, '(When he said "living water," he was speaking of the Spirit, who would be given to everyone believing in him. But the Spirit had not yet been given, because Jesus had not yet entered into his glory.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 40, 'When the crowds heard him say this, some of them declared, "This man surely is the Prophet."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 41, 'Others said, "He is the Messiah." Still others said, "But he can''t be! Will the Messiah come from Galilee?', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 42, 'For the Scriptures clearly state that the Messiah will be born of the royal line of David, in Bethlehem, the village where King David was born."', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 43, 'So the crowd was divided in their opinion about him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 44, 'And some wanted him arrested, but no one touched him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 45, 'The Temple guards who had been sent to arrest him returned to the leading priests and Pharisees. "Why didn''t you bring him in?" they demanded.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 46, '"We have never heard anyone talk like this!" the guards responded.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 47, '"Have you been led astray, too?" the Pharisees mocked.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 48, '"Is there a single one of us rulers or Pharisees who believes in him?', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 49, 'These ignorant crowds do, but what do they know about it? A curse on them anyway!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 50, 'Nicodemus, the leader who had met with Jesus earlier, then spoke up.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 51, '"Is it legal to convict a man before he is given a hearing?" he asked.', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 52, 'They replied, "Are you from Galilee, too? Search the Scriptures and see for yourself--no prophet ever comes from Galilee!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 7, 53, 'Then the meeting broke up and everybody went home.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 1, 'Jesus returned to the Mount of Olives,', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 2, 'but early the next morning he was back again at the Temple. A crowd soon gathered, and he sat down and taught them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 3, 'As he was speaking, the teachers of religious law and Pharisees brought a woman they had caught in the act of adultery. They put her in front of the crowd.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 4, '"Teacher," they said to Jesus, "this woman was caught in the very act of adultery.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 5, 'The law of Moses says to stone her. What do you say?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 6, 'They were trying to trap him into saying something they could use against him, but Jesus stooped down and wrote in the dust with his finger.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 7, 'They kept demanding an answer, so he stood up again and said, "All right, stone her. But let those who have never sinned throw the first stones!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 8, 'Then he stooped down again and wrote in the dust.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 9, 'When the accusers heard this, they slipped away one by one, beginning with the oldest, until only Jesus was left in the middle of the crowd with the woman.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 10, 'Then Jesus stood up again and said to her, "Where are your accusers? Didn''t even one of them condemn you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 11, '"No, Lord," she said. And Jesus said, "Neither do I. Go and sin no more."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 12, 'Jesus said to the people, "I am the light of the world. If you follow me, you won''t be stumbling through the darkness, because you will have the light that leads to life."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 13, 'The Pharisees replied, "You are making false claims about yourself!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 14, 'Jesus told them, "These claims are valid even though I make them about myself. For I know where I came from and where I am going, but you don''t know this about me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 15, 'You judge me with all your human limitations, but I am not judging anyone.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 16, 'And if I did, my judgment would be correct in every respect because I am not alone--I have with me the Father who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 17, 'Your own law says that if two people agree about something, their witness is accepted as fact.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 18, 'I am one witness, and my Father who sent me is the other."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 19, '"Where is your father?" they asked. Jesus answered, "Since you don''t know who I am, you don''t know who my Father is. If you knew me, then you would know my Father, too."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 20, 'Jesus made these statements while he was teaching in the section of the Temple known as the Treasury. But he was not arrested, because his time had not yet come.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 21, 'Later Jesus said to them again, "I am going away. You will search for me and die in your sin. You cannot come where I am going."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 22, 'The Jewish leaders asked, "Is he planning to commit suicide? What does he mean, ''You cannot come where I am going''?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 23, 'Then he said to them, "You are from below; I am from above. You are of this world; I am not.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 24, 'That is why I said that you will die in your sins; for unless you believe that I am who I say I am, you will die in your sins."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 25, '"Tell us who you are," they demanded. Jesus replied, "I am the one I have always claimed to be.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 26, 'I have much to say about you and much to condemn, but I won''t. For I say only what I have heard from the one who sent me, and he is true."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 27, 'But they still didn''t understand that he was talking to them about his Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 28, 'So Jesus said, "When you have lifted up the Son of Man on the cross, then you will realize that I am he and that I do nothing on my own, but I speak what the Father taught me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 29, 'And the one who sent me is with me--he has not deserted me. For I always do those things that are pleasing to him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 30, 'Then many who heard him say these things believed in him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 31, 'Jesus said to the people who believed in him, "You are truly my disciples if you keep obeying my teachings.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 32, 'And you will know the truth, and the truth will set you free."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 33, '"But we are descendants of Abraham," they said. "We have never been slaves to anyone on earth. What do you mean, ''set free''?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 34, 'Jesus replied, "I assure you that everyone who sins is a slave of sin.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 35, 'A slave is not a permanent member of the family, but a son is part of the family forever.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 36, 'So if the Son sets you free, you will indeed be free.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 37, 'Yes, I realize that you are descendants of Abraham. And yet some of you are trying to kill me because my message does not find a place in your hearts.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 38, 'I am telling you what I saw when I was with my Father. But you are following the advice of your father."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 39, '"Our father is Abraham," they declared. "No," Jesus replied, "for if you were children of Abraham, you would follow his good example.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 40, 'I told you the truth I heard from God, but you are trying to kill me. Abraham wouldn''t do a thing like that.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 41, 'No, you are obeying your real father when you act that way." They replied, "We were not born out of wedlock! Our true Father is God himself."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 42, 'Jesus told them, "If God were your Father, you would love me, because I have come to you from God. I am not here on my own, but he sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 43, 'Why can''t you understand what I am saying? It is because you are unable to do so!', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 44, 'For you are the children of your father the Devil, and you love to do the evil things he does. He was a murderer from the beginning and has always hated the truth. There is no truth in him. When he lies, it is consistent with his character; for he is a liar and the father of lies.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 45, 'So when I tell the truth, you just naturally don''t believe me!', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 46, 'Which of you can truthfully accuse me of sin? And since I am telling you the truth, why don''t you believe me?', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 47, 'Anyone whose Father is God listens gladly to the words of God. Since you don''t, it proves you aren''t God''s children."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 48, 'The people retorted, "You Samaritan devil! Didn''t we say all along that you were possessed by a demon?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 49, '"No," Jesus said, "I have no demon in me. For I honor my Father--and you dishonor me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 50, 'And though I have no wish to glorify myself, God wants to glorify me. Let him be the judge.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 51, 'I assure you, anyone who obeys my teaching will never die!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 52, 'The people said, "Now we know you are possessed by a demon. Even Abraham and the prophets died, but you say that those who obey your teaching will never die!', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 53, 'Are you greater than our father Abraham, who died? Are you greater than the prophets, who died? Who do you think you are?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 54, 'Jesus answered, "If I am merely boasting about myself, it doesn''t count. But it is my Father who says these glorious things about me. You say, ''He is our God,''', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 55, 'but you do not even know him. I know him. If I said otherwise, I would be as great a liar as you! But it is true--I know him and obey him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 56, 'Your ancestor Abraham rejoiced as he looked forward to my coming. He saw it and was glad."', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 57, 'The people said, "You aren''t even fifty years old. How can you say you have seen Abraham? "', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 58, 'Jesus answered, "The truth is, I existed before Abraham was even born!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 8, 59, 'At that point they picked up stones to kill him. But Jesus hid himself from them and left the Temple.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 1, 'As Jesus was walking along, he saw a man who had been blind from birth.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 2, '"Teacher," his disciples asked him, "why was this man born blind? Was it a result of his own sins or those of his parents?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 3, '"It was not because of his sins or his parents'' sins," Jesus answered. "He was born blind so the power of God could be seen in him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 4, 'All of us must quickly carry out the tasks assigned us by the one who sent me, because there is little time left before the night falls and all work comes to an end.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 5, 'But while I am still here in the world, I am the light of the world."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 6, 'Then he spit on the ground, made mud with the saliva, and smoothed the mud over the blind man''s eyes.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 7, 'He told him, "Go and wash in the pool of Siloam" (Siloam means Sent). So the man went and washed, and came back seeing!', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 8, 'His neighbors and others who knew him as a blind beggar asked each other, "Is this the same man--that beggar?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 9, 'Some said he was, and others said, "No, but he surely looks like him!" And the beggar kept saying, "I am the same man!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 10, 'They asked, "Who healed you? What happened?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 11, 'He told them, "The man they call Jesus made mud and smoothed it over my eyes and told me, ''Go to the pool of Siloam and wash off the mud.'' I went and washed, and now I can see!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 12, '"Where is he now?" they asked. "I don''t know," he replied.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 13, 'Then they took the man to the Pharisees.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 14, 'Now as it happened, Jesus had healed the man on a Sabbath.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 15, 'The Pharisees asked the man all about it. So he told them, "He smoothed the mud over my eyes, and when it was washed away, I could see!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 16, 'Some of the Pharisees said, "This man Jesus is not from God, for he is working on the Sabbath." Others said, "But how could an ordinary sinner do such miraculous signs?" So there was a deep division of opinion among them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 17, 'Then the Pharisees once again questioned the man who had been blind and demanded, "This man who opened your eyes--who do you say he is?" The man replied, "I think he must be a prophet."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 18, 'The Jewish leaders wouldn''t believe he had been blind, so they called in his parents.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 19, 'They asked them, "Is this your son? Was he born blind? If so, how can he see?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 20, 'His parents replied, "We know this is our son and that he was born blind,', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 21, 'but we don''t know how he can see or who healed him. He is old enough to speak for himself. Ask him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 22, 'They said this because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders, who had announced that anyone saying Jesus was the Messiah would be expelled from the synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 23, 'That''s why they said, "He is old enough to speak for himself. Ask him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 24, 'So for the second time they called in the man who had been blind and told him, "Give glory to God by telling the truth, because we know Jesus is a sinner."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 25, '"I don''t know whether he is a sinner," the man replied. "But I know this: I was blind, and now I can see!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 26, '"But what did he do?" they asked. "How did he heal you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 27, '"Look!" the man exclaimed. "I told you once. Didn''t you listen? Why do you want to hear it again? Do you want to become his disciples, too?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 28, 'Then they cursed him and said, "You are his disciple, but we are disciples of Moses.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 29, 'We know God spoke to Moses, but as for this man, we don''t know anything about him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 30, '"Why, that''s very strange!" the man replied. "He healed my eyes, and yet you don''t know anything about him!', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 31, 'Well, God doesn''t listen to sinners, but he is ready to hear those who worship him and do his will.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 32, 'Never since the world began has anyone been able to open the eyes of someone born blind.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 33, 'If this man were not from God, he couldn''t do it."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 34, '"You were born in sin!" they answered. "Are you trying to teach us?" And they threw him out of the synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 35, 'When Jesus heard what had happened, he found the man and said, "Do you believe in the Son of Man?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 36, 'The man answered, "Who is he, sir, because I would like to."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 37, '"You have seen him," Jesus said, "and he is speaking to you!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 38, '"Yes, Lord," the man said, "I believe!" And he worshiped Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 39, 'Then Jesus told him, "I have come to judge the world. I have come to give sight to the blind and to show those who think they see that they are blind."', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 40, 'The Pharisees who were standing there heard him and asked, "Are you saying we are blind?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 9, 41, '"If you were blind, you wouldn''t be guilty," Jesus replied. "But you remain guilty because you claim you can see.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 1, '"I assure you, anyone who sneaks over the wall of a sheepfold, rather than going through the gate, must surely be a thief and a robber!', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 2, 'For a shepherd enters through the gate.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 3, 'The gatekeeper opens the gate for him, and the sheep hear his voice and come to him. He calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 4, 'After he has gathered his own flock, he walks ahead of them, and they follow him because they recognize his voice.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 5, 'They won''t follow a stranger; they will run from him because they don''t recognize his voice."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 6, 'Those who heard Jesus use this illustration didn''t understand what he meant,', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 7, 'so he explained it to them. "I assure you, I am the gate for the sheep," he said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 8, '"All others who came before me were thieves and robbers. But the true sheep did not listen to them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 9, 'Yes, I am the gate. Those who come in through me will be saved. Wherever they go, they will find green pastures.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 10, 'The thief''s purpose is to steal and kill and destroy. My purpose is to give life in all its fullness.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 11, '"I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 12, 'A hired hand will run when he sees a wolf coming. He will leave the sheep because they aren''t his and he isn''t their shepherd. And so the wolf attacks them and scatters the flock.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 13, 'The hired hand runs away because he is merely hired and has no real concern for the sheep.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 14, '"I am the good shepherd; I know my own sheep, and they know me,', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 15, 'just as my Father knows me and I know the Father. And I lay down my life for the sheep.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 16, 'I have other sheep, too, that are not in this sheepfold. I must bring them also, and they will listen to my voice; and there will be one flock with one shepherd.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 17, '"The Father loves me because I lay down my life that I may have it back again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 18, 'No one can take my life from me. I lay down my life voluntarily. For I have the right to lay it down when I want to and also the power to take it again. For my Father has given me this command."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 19, 'When he said these things, the people were again divided in their opinions about him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 20, 'Some of them said, "He has a demon, or he''s crazy. Why listen to a man like that?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 21, 'Others said, "This doesn''t sound like a man possessed by a demon! Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 22, 'It was now winter, and Jesus was in Jerusalem at the time of Hanukkah.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 23, 'He was at the Temple, walking through the section known as Solomon''s Colonnade.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 24, 'The Jewish leaders surrounded him and asked, "How long are you going to keep us in suspense? If you are the Messiah, tell us plainly."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 25, 'Jesus replied, "I have already told you, and you don''t believe me. The proof is what I do in the name of my Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 26, 'But you don''t believe me because you are not part of my flock.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 27, 'My sheep recognize my voice; I know them, and they follow me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 28, 'I give them eternal life, and they will never perish. No one will snatch them away from me,', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 29, 'for my Father has given them to me, and he is more powerful than anyone else. So no one can take them from me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 30, 'The Father and I are one."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 31, 'Once again the Jewish leaders picked up stones to kill him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 32, 'Jesus said, "At my Father''s direction I have done many things to help the people. For which one of these good deeds are you killing me?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 33, 'They replied, "Not for any good work, but for blasphemy, because you, a mere man, have made yourself God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 34, 'Jesus replied, "It is written in your own law that God said to certain leaders of the people, ''I say, you are gods!''', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 35, 'And you know that the Scriptures cannot be altered. So if those people, who received God''s message, were called ''gods,''', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 36, 'why do you call it blasphemy when the Holy One who was sent into the world by the Father says, ''I am the Son of God''?', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 37, 'Don''t believe me unless I carry out my Father''s work.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 38, 'But if I do his work, believe in what I have done, even if you don''t believe me. Then you will realize that the Father is in me, and I am in the Father."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 39, 'Once again they tried to arrest him, but he got away and left them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 40, 'He went beyond the Jordan River to stay near the place where John was first baptizing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 41, 'And many followed him. "John didn''t do miracles," they remarked to one another, "but all his predictions about this man have come true."', 'NLT'),
(6, 10, 42, 'And many believed in him there.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 1, 'A man named Lazarus was sick. He lived in Bethany with his sisters, Mary and Martha.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 2, 'This is the Mary who poured the expensive perfume on the Lord''s feet and wiped them with her hair. Her brother, Lazarus, was sick.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 3, 'So the two sisters sent a message to Jesus telling him, "Lord, the one you love is very sick."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 4, 'But when Jesus heard about it he said, "Lazarus''s sickness will not end in death. No, it is for the glory of God. I, the Son of God, will receive glory from this."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 5, 'Although Jesus loved Martha, Mary, and Lazarus,', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 6, 'he stayed where he was for the next two days and did not go to them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 7, 'Finally after two days, he said to his disciples, "Let''s go to Judea again."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 8, 'But his disciples objected. "Teacher," they said, "only a few days ago the Jewish leaders in Judea were trying to kill you. Are you going there again?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 9, 'Jesus replied, "There are twelve hours of daylight every day. As long as it is light, people can walk safely. They can see because they have the light of this world.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 10, 'Only at night is there danger of stumbling because there is no light."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 11, 'Then he said, "Our friend Lazarus has fallen asleep, but now I will go and wake him up."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 12, 'The disciples said, "Lord, if he is sleeping, that means he is getting better!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 13, 'They thought Jesus meant Lazarus was having a good night''s rest, but Jesus meant Lazarus had died.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 14, 'Then he told them plainly, "Lazarus is dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 15, 'And for your sake, I am glad I wasn''t there, because this will give you another opportunity to believe in me. Come, let''s go see him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 16, 'Thomas, nicknamed the Twin, said to his fellow disciples, "Let''s go, too--and die with Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 17, 'When Jesus arrived at Bethany, he was told that Lazarus had already been in his grave for four days.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 18, 'Bethany was only a few miles down the road from Jerusalem,', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 19, 'and many of the people had come to pay their respects and console Martha and Mary on their loss.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 20, 'When Martha got word that Jesus was coming, she went to meet him. But Mary stayed at home.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 21, 'Martha said to Jesus, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 22, 'But even now I know that God will give you whatever you ask."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 23, 'Jesus told her, "Your brother will rise again."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 24, '"Yes," Martha said, "when everyone else rises, on resurrection day."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 25, 'Jesus told her, "I am the resurrection and the life. Those who believe in me, even though they die like everyone else, will live again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 26, 'They are given eternal life for believing in me and will never perish. Do you believe this, Martha?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 27, '"Yes, Lord," she told him. "I have always believed you are the Messiah, the Son of God, the one who has come into the world from God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 28, 'Then she left him and returned to Mary. She called Mary aside from the mourners and told her, "The Teacher is here and wants to see you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 29, 'So Mary immediately went to him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 30, 'Now Jesus had stayed outside the village, at the place where Martha met him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 31, 'When the people who were at the house trying to console Mary saw her leave so hastily, they assumed she was going to Lazarus''s grave to weep. So they followed her there.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 32, 'When Mary arrived and saw Jesus, she fell down at his feet and said, "Lord, if you had been here, my brother would not have died."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 33, 'When Jesus saw her weeping and saw the other people wailing with her, he was moved with indignation and was deeply troubled.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 34, '"Where have you put him?" he asked them. They told him, "Lord, come and see."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 35, 'Then Jesus wept.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 36, 'The people who were standing nearby said, "See how much he loved him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 37, 'But some said, "This man healed a blind man. Why couldn''t he keep Lazarus from dying?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 38, 'And again Jesus was deeply troubled. Then they came to the grave. It was a cave with a stone rolled across its entrance.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 39, '"Roll the stone aside," Jesus told them. But Martha, the dead man''s sister, said, "Lord, by now the smell will be terrible because he has been dead for four days."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 40, 'Jesus responded, "Didn''t I tell you that you will see God''s glory if you believe?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 41, 'So they rolled the stone aside. Then Jesus looked up to heaven and said, "Father, thank you for hearing me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 42, 'You always hear me, but I said it out loud for the sake of all these people standing here, so they will believe you sent me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 43, 'Then Jesus shouted, "Lazarus, come out!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 44, 'And Lazarus came out, bound in graveclothes, his face wrapped in a headcloth. Jesus told them, "Unwrap him and let him go!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 45, 'Many of the people who were with Mary believed in Jesus when they saw this happen.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 46, 'But some went to the Pharisees and told them what Jesus had done.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 47, 'Then the leading priests and Pharisees called the high council together to discuss the situation. "What are we going to do?" they asked each other. "This man certainly performs many miraculous signs.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 48, 'If we leave him alone, the whole nation will follow him, and then the Roman army will come and destroy both our Temple and our nation."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 49, 'And one of them, Caiaphas, who was high priest that year, said, "How can you be so stupid?', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 50, 'Why should the whole nation be destroyed? Let this one man die for the people."', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 51, 'This prophecy that Jesus should die for the entire nation came from Caiaphas in his position as high priest. He didn''t think of it himself; he was inspired to say it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 52, 'It was a prediction that Jesus'' death would be not for Israel only, but for the gathering together of all the children of God scattered around the world.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 53, 'So from that time on the Jewish leaders began to plot Jesus'' death.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 54, 'As a result, Jesus stopped his public ministry among the people and left Jerusalem. He went to a place near the wilderness, to the village of Ephraim, and stayed there with his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 55, 'It was now almost time for the celebration of Passover, and many people from the country arrived in Jerusalem several days early so they could go through the cleansing ceremony before the Passover began.', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 56, 'They wanted to see Jesus, and as they talked in the Temple, they asked each other, "What do you think? Will he come for the Passover?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 11, 57, 'Meanwhile, the leading priests and Pharisees had publicly announced that anyone seeing Jesus must report him immediately so they could arrest him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 1, 'Six days before the Passover ceremonies began, Jesus arrived in Bethany, the home of Lazarus--the man he had raised from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 2, 'A dinner was prepared in Jesus'' honor. Martha served, and Lazarus sat at the table with him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 3, 'Then Mary took a twelve-ounce jar of expensive perfume made from essence of nard, and she anointed Jesus'' feet with it and wiped his feet with her hair. And the house was filled with fragrance.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 4, 'But Judas Iscariot, one of his disciples--the one who would betray him--said,', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 5, '"That perfume was worth a small fortune. It should have been sold and the money given to the poor."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 6, 'Not that he cared for the poor--he was a thief who was in charge of the disciples'' funds, and he often took some for his own use.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 7, 'Jesus replied, "Leave her alone. She did it in preparation for my burial.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 8, 'You will always have the poor among you, but I will not be here with you much longer."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 9, 'When all the people heard of Jesus'' arrival, they flocked to see him and also to see Lazarus, the man Jesus had raised from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 10, 'Then the leading priests decided to kill Lazarus, too,', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 11, 'for it was because of him that many of the people had deserted them and believed in Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 12, 'The next day, the news that Jesus was on the way to Jerusalem swept through the city. A huge crowd of Passover visitors', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 13, 'took palm branches and went down the road to meet him. They shouted, "Praise God! Bless the one who comes in the name of the Lord! Hail to the King of Israel!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 14, 'Jesus found a young donkey and sat on it, fulfilling the prophecy that said:', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 15, '"Don''t be afraid, people of Israel. Look, your King is coming, sitting on a donkey''s colt."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 16, 'His disciples didn''t realize at the time that this was a fulfillment of prophecy. But after Jesus entered into his glory, they remembered that these Scriptures had come true before their eyes.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 17, 'Those in the crowd who had seen Jesus call Lazarus back to life were telling others all about it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 18, 'That was the main reason so many went out to meet him--because they had heard about this mighty miracle.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 19, 'Then the Pharisees said to each other, "We''ve lost. Look, the whole world has gone after him!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 20, 'Some Greeks who had come to Jerusalem to attend the Passover', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 21, 'paid a visit to Philip, who was from Bethsaida in Galilee. They said, "Sir, we want to meet Jesus."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 22, 'Philip told Andrew about it, and they went together to ask Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 23, 'Jesus replied, "The time has come for the Son of Man to enter into his glory.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 24, 'The truth is, a kernel of wheat must be planted in the soil. Unless it dies it will be alone--a single seed. But its death will produce many new kernels--a plentiful harvest of new lives.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 25, 'Those who love their life in this world will lose it. Those who despise their life in this world will keep it for eternal life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 26, 'All those who want to be my disciples must come and follow me, because my servants must be where I am. And if they follow me, the Father will honor them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 27, 'Now my soul is deeply troubled. Should I pray, ''Father, save me from what lies ahead''? But that is the very reason why I came!', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 28, 'Father, bring glory to your name." Then a voice spoke from heaven, saying, "I have already brought it glory, and I will do it again."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 29, 'When the crowd heard the voice, some thought it was thunder, while others declared an angel had spoken to him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 30, 'Then Jesus told them, "The voice was for your benefit, not mine.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 31, 'The time of judgment for the world has come, when the prince of this world will be cast out.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 32, 'And when I am lifted up on the cross, I will draw everyone to myself."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 33, 'He said this to indicate how he was going to die.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 34, '"Die?" asked the crowd. "We understood from Scripture that the Messiah would live forever. Why are you saying the Son of Man will die? Who is this Son of Man you are talking about?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 35, 'Jesus replied, "My light will shine out for you just a little while longer. Walk in it while you can, so you will not stumble when the darkness falls. If you walk in the darkness, you cannot see where you are going.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 36, 'Believe in the light while there is still time; then you will become children of the light." After saying these things, Jesus went away and was hidden from them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 37, 'But despite all the miraculous signs he had done, most of the people did not believe in him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 38, 'This is exactly what Isaiah the prophet had predicted: "Lord, who has believed our message? To whom will the Lord reveal his saving power?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 39, 'But the people couldn''t believe, for as Isaiah also said,', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 40, '"The Lord has blinded their eyes and hardened their hearts--so their eyes cannot see, and their hearts cannot understand, and they cannot turn to me and let me heal them."', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 41, 'Isaiah was referring to Jesus when he made this prediction, because he was given a vision of the Messiah''s glory.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 42, 'Many people, including some of the Jewish leaders, believed in him. But they wouldn''t admit it to anyone because of their fear that the Pharisees would expel them from the synagogue.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 43, 'For they loved human praise more than the praise of God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 44, 'Jesus shouted to the crowds, "If you trust me, you are really trusting God who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 45, 'For when you see me, you are seeing the one who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 46, 'I have come as a light to shine in this dark world, so that all who put their trust in me will no longer remain in the darkness.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 47, 'If anyone hears me and doesn''t obey me, I am not his judge--for I have come to save the world and not to judge it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 48, 'But all who reject me and my message will be judged at the day of judgment by the truth I have spoken.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 49, 'I don''t speak on my own authority. The Father who sent me gave me his own instructions as to what I should say.', 'NLT'),
(6, 12, 50, 'And I know his instructions lead to eternal life; so I say whatever the Father tells me to say!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 1, 'Before the Passover celebration, Jesus knew that his hour had come to leave this world and return to his Father. He now showed the disciples the full extent of his love.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 2, 'It was time for supper, and the Devil had already enticed Judas, son of Simon Iscariot, to carry out his plan to betray Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 3, 'Jesus knew that the Father had given him authority over everything and that he had come from God and would return to God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 4, 'So he got up from the table, took off his robe, wrapped a towel around his waist,', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 5, 'and poured water into a basin. Then he began to wash the disciples'' feet and to wipe them with the towel he had around him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 6, 'When he came to Simon Peter, Peter said to him, "Lord, why are you going to wash my feet?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 7, 'Jesus replied, "You don''t understand now why I am doing it; someday you will."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 8, '"No," Peter protested, "you will never wash my feet!" Jesus replied, "But if I don''t wash you, you won''t belong to me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 9, 'Simon Peter exclaimed, "Then wash my hands and head as well, Lord, not just my feet!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 10, 'Jesus replied, "A person who has bathed all over does not need to wash, except for the feet, to be entirely clean. And you are clean, but that isn''t true of everyone here."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 11, 'For Jesus knew who would betray him. That is what he meant when he said, "Not all of you are clean."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 12, 'After washing their feet, he put on his robe again and sat down and asked, "Do you understand what I was doing?', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 13, 'You call me ''Teacher'' and ''Lord,'' and you are right, because it is true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 14, 'And since I, the Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you ought to wash each other''s feet.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 15, 'I have given you an example to follow. Do as I have done to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 16, 'How true it is that a servant is not greater than the master. Nor are messengers more important than the one who sends them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 17, 'You know these things--now do them! That is the path of blessing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 18, '"I am not saying these things to all of you; I know so well each one of you I chose. The Scriptures declare, ''The one who shares my food has turned against me,'' and this will soon come true.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 19, 'I tell you this now, so that when it happens you will believe I am the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 20, 'Truly, anyone who welcomes my messenger is welcoming me, and anyone who welcomes me is welcoming the Father who sent me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 21, 'Now Jesus was in great anguish of spirit, and he exclaimed, "The truth is, one of you will betray me!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 22, 'The disciples looked at each other, wondering whom he could mean.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 23, 'One of Jesus'' disciples, the one Jesus loved, was sitting next to Jesus at the table.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 24, 'Simon Peter motioned to him to ask who would do this terrible thing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 25, 'Leaning toward Jesus, he asked, "Lord, who is it?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 26, 'Jesus said, "It is the one to whom I give the bread dipped in the sauce." And when he had dipped it, he gave it to Judas, son of Simon Iscariot.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 27, 'As soon as Judas had eaten the bread, Satan entered into him. Then Jesus told him, "Hurry. Do it now."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 28, 'None of the others at the table knew what Jesus meant.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 29, 'Since Judas was their treasurer, some thought Jesus was telling him to go and pay for the food or to give some money to the poor.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 30, 'So Judas left at once, going out into the night.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 31, 'As soon as Judas left the room, Jesus said, "The time has come for me, the Son of Man, to enter into my glory, and God will receive glory because of all that happens to me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 32, 'And God will bring me into my glory very soon.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 33, 'Dear children, how brief are these moments before I must go away and leave you! Then, though you search for me, you cannot come to me--just as I told the Jewish leaders.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 34, 'So now I am giving you a new commandment: Love each other. Just as I have loved you, you should love each other.', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 35, 'Your love for one another will prove to the world that you are my disciples."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 36, 'Simon Peter said, "Lord, where are you going?" And Jesus replied, "You can''t go with me now, but you will follow me later."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 37, '"But why can''t I come now, Lord?" he asked. "I am ready to die for you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 13, 38, 'Jesus answered, "Die for me? No, before the rooster crows tomorrow morning, you will deny three times that you even know me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 1, '"Don''t be troubled. You trust God, now trust in me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 2, 'There are many rooms in my Father''s home, and I am going to prepare a place for you. If this were not so, I would tell you plainly.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 3, 'When everything is ready, I will come and get you, so that you will always be with me where I am.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 4, 'And you know where I am going and how to get there."', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 5, '"No, we don''t know, Lord," Thomas said. "We haven''t any idea where you are going, so how can we know the way?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 6, 'Jesus told him, "I am the way, the truth, and the life. No one can come to the Father except through me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 7, 'If you had known who I am, then you would have known who my Father is. From now on you know him and have seen him!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 8, 'Philip said, "Lord, show us the Father and we will be satisfied."', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 9, 'Jesus replied, "Philip, don''t you even yet know who I am, even after all the time I have been with you? Anyone who has seen me has seen the Father! So why are you asking to see him?', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 10, 'Don''t you believe that I am in the Father and the Father is in me? The words I say are not my own, but my Father who lives in me does his work through me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 11, 'Just believe that I am in the Father and the Father is in me. Or at least believe because of what you have seen me do.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 12, '"The truth is, anyone who believes in me will do the same works I have done, and even greater works, because I am going to be with the Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 13, 'You can ask for anything in my name, and I will do it, because the work of the Son brings glory to the Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 14, 'Yes, ask anything in my name, and I will do it!', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 15, '"If you love me, obey my commandments.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 16, 'And I will ask the Father, and he will give you another Counselor, who will never leave you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 17, 'He is the Holy Spirit, who leads into all truth. The world at large cannot receive him, because it isn''t looking for him and doesn''t recognize him. But you do, because he lives with you now and later will be in you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 18, 'No, I will not abandon you as orphans--I will come to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 19, 'In just a little while the world will not see me again, but you will. For I will live again, and you will, too.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 20, 'When I am raised to life again, you will know that I am in my Father, and you are in me, and I am in you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 21, 'Those who obey my commandments are the ones who love me. And because they love me, my Father will love them, and I will love them. And I will reveal myself to each one of them."', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 22, 'Judas (not Judas Iscariot, but the other disciple with that name) said to him, "Lord, why are you going to reveal yourself only to us and not to the world at large?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 23, 'Jesus replied, "All those who love me will do what I say. My Father will love them, and we will come to them and live with them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 24, 'Anyone who doesn''t love me will not do what I say. And remember, my words are not my own. This message is from the Father who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 25, 'I am telling you these things now while I am still with you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 26, 'But when the Father sends the Counselor as my representative--and by the Counselor I mean the Holy Spirit--he will teach you everything and will remind you of everything I myself have told you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 27, '"I am leaving you with a gift--peace of mind and heart. And the peace I give isn''t like the peace the world gives. So don''t be troubled or afraid.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 28, 'Remember what I told you: I am going away, but I will come back to you again. If you really love me, you will be very happy for me, because now I can go to the Father, who is greater than I am.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 29, 'I have told you these things before they happen so that you will believe when they do happen.', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 30, '"I don''t have much more time to talk to you, because the prince of this world approaches. He has no power over me,', 'NLT'),
(6, 14, 31, 'but I will do what the Father requires of me, so that the world will know that I love the Father. Come, let''s be going.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 1, '"I am the true vine, and my Father is the gardener.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 2, 'He cuts off every branch that doesn''t produce fruit, and he prunes the branches that do bear fruit so they will produce even more.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 3, 'You have already been pruned for greater fruitfulness by the message I have given you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 4, 'Remain in me, and I will remain in you. For a branch cannot produce fruit if it is severed from the vine, and you cannot be fruitful apart from me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 5, '"Yes, I am the vine; you are the branches. Those who remain in me, and I in them, will produce much fruit. For apart from me you can do nothing.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 6, 'Anyone who parts from me is thrown away like a useless branch and withers. Such branches are gathered into a pile to be burned.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 7, 'But if you stay joined to me and my words remain in you, you may ask any request you like, and it will be granted!', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 8, 'My true disciples produce much fruit. This brings great glory to my Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 9, '"I have loved you even as the Father has loved me. Remain in my love.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 10, 'When you obey me, you remain in my love, just as I obey my Father and remain in his love.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 11, 'I have told you this so that you will be filled with my joy. Yes, your joy will overflow!', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 12, 'I command you to love each other in the same way that I love you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 13, 'And here is how to measure it--the greatest love is shown when people lay down their lives for their friends.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 14, 'You are my friends if you obey me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 15, 'I no longer call you servants, because a master doesn''t confide in his servants. Now you are my friends, since I have told you everything the Father told me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 16, 'You didn''t choose me. I chose you. I appointed you to go and produce fruit that will last, so that the Father will give you whatever you ask for, using my name.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 17, 'I command you to love each other.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 18, '"When the world hates you, remember it hated me before it hated you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 19, 'The world would love you if you belonged to it, but you don''t. I chose you to come out of the world, and so it hates you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 20, 'Do you remember what I told you? ''A servant is not greater than the master.'' Since they persecuted me, naturally they will persecute you. And if they had listened to me, they would listen to you!', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 21, 'The people of the world will hate you because you belong to me, for they don''t know God who sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 22, 'They would not be guilty if I had not come and spoken to them. But now they have no excuse for their sin.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 23, 'Anyone who hates me hates my Father, too.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 24, 'If I hadn''t done such miraculous signs among them that no one else could do, they would not be counted guilty. But as it is, they saw all that I did and yet hated both of us--me and my Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 25, 'This has fulfilled what the Scriptures said: ''They hated me without cause.''', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 26, '"But I will send you the Counselor--the Spirit of truth. He will come to you from the Father and will tell you all about me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 15, 27, 'And you must also tell others about me because you have been with me from the beginning.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 1, '"I have told you these things so that you won''t fall away.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 2, 'For you will be expelled from the synagogues, and the time is coming when those who kill you will think they are doing God a service.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 3, 'This is because they have never known the Father or me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 4, 'Yes, I''m telling you these things now, so that when they happen, you will remember I warned you. I didn''t tell you earlier because I was going to be with you for a while longer.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 5, '"But now I am going away to the one who sent me, and none of you has asked me where I am going.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 6, 'Instead, you are very sad.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 7, 'But it is actually best for you that I go away, because if I don''t, the Counselor won''t come. If I do go away, he will come because I will send him to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 8, 'And when he comes, he will convince the world of its sin, and of God''s righteousness, and of the coming judgment.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 9, 'The world''s sin is unbelief in me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 10, 'Righteousness is available because I go to the Father, and you will see me no more.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 11, 'Judgment will come because the prince of this world has already been judged.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 12, '"Oh, there is so much more I want to tell you, but you can''t bear it now.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 13, 'When the Spirit of truth comes, he will guide you into all truth. He will not be presenting his own ideas; he will be telling you what he has heard. He will tell you about the future.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 14, 'He will bring me glory by revealing to you whatever he receives from me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 15, 'All that the Father has is mine; this is what I mean when I say that the Spirit will reveal to you whatever he receives from me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 16, '"In just a little while I will be gone, and you won''t see me anymore. Then, just a little while after that, you will see me again."', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 17, 'The disciples asked each other, "What does he mean when he says, ''You won''t see me, and then you will see me''? And what does he mean when he says, ''I am going to the Father''?', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 18, 'And what does he mean by ''a little while''? We don''t understand."', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 19, 'Jesus realized they wanted to ask him, so he said, "Are you asking yourselves what I meant? I said in just a little while I will be gone, and you won''t see me anymore. Then, just a little while after that, you will see me again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 20, 'Truly, you will weep and mourn over what is going to happen to me, but the world will rejoice. You will grieve, but your grief will suddenly turn to wonderful joy when you see me again.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 21, 'It will be like a woman experiencing the pains of labor. When her child is born, her anguish gives place to joy because she has brought a new person into the world.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 22, 'You have sorrow now, but I will see you again; then you will rejoice, and no one can rob you of that joy.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 23, 'At that time you won''t need to ask me for anything. The truth is, you can go directly to the Father and ask him, and he will grant your request because you use my name.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 24, 'You haven''t done this before. Ask, using my name, and you will receive, and you will have abundant joy.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 25, '"I have spoken of these matters in parables, but the time will come when this will not be necessary, and I will tell you plainly all about the Father.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 26, 'Then you will ask in my name. I''m not saying I will ask the Father on your behalf,', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 27, 'for the Father himself loves you dearly because you love me and believe that I came from God.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 28, 'Yes, I came from the Father into the world, and I will leave the world and return to the Father."', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 29, 'Then his disciples said, "At last you are speaking plainly and not in parables.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 30, 'Now we understand that you know everything and don''t need anyone to tell you anything. From this we believe that you came from God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 31, 'Jesus asked, "Do you finally believe?', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 32, 'But the time is coming--in fact, it is already here--when you will be scattered, each one going his own way, leaving me alone. Yet I am not alone because the Father is with me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 16, 33, 'I have told you all this so that you may have peace in me. Here on earth you will have many trials and sorrows. But take heart, because I have overcome the world."', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 1, 'When Jesus had finished saying all these things, he looked up to heaven and said, "Father, the time has come. Glorify your Son so he can give glory back to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 2, 'For you have given him authority over everyone in all the earth. He gives eternal life to each one you have given him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 3, 'And this is the way to have eternal life--to know you, the only true God, and Jesus Christ, the one you sent to earth.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 4, 'I brought glory to you here on earth by doing everything you told me to do.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 5, 'And now, Father, bring me into the glory we shared before the world began.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 6, '"I have told these men about you. They were in the world, but then you gave them to me. Actually, they were always yours, and you gave them to me; and they have kept your word.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 7, 'Now they know that everything I have is a gift from you,', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 8, 'for I have passed on to them the words you gave me; and they accepted them and know that I came from you, and they believe you sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 9, '"My prayer is not for the world, but for those you have given me, because they belong to you.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 10, 'And all of them, since they are mine, belong to you; and you have given them back to me, so they are my glory!', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 11, 'Now I am departing the world; I am leaving them behind and coming to you. Holy Father, keep them and care for them--all those you have given me--so that they will be united just as we are.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 12, 'During my time here, I have kept them safe. I guarded them so that not one was lost, except the one headed for destruction, as the Scriptures foretold.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 13, '"And now I am coming to you. I have told them many things while I was with them so they would be filled with my joy.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 14, 'I have given them your word. And the world hates them because they do not belong to the world, just as I do not.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 15, 'I''m not asking you to take them out of the world, but to keep them safe from the evil one.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 16, 'They are not part of this world any more than I am.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 17, 'Make them pure and holy by teaching them your words of truth.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 18, 'As you sent me into the world, I am sending them into the world.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 19, 'And I give myself entirely to you so they also might be entirely yours.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 20, '"I am praying not only for these disciples but also for all who will ever believe in me because of their testimony.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 21, 'My prayer for all of them is that they will be one, just as you and I are one, Father--that just as you are in me and I am in you, so they will be in us, and the world will believe you sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 22, '"I have given them the glory you gave me, so that they may be one, as we are--', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 23, 'I in them and you in me, all being perfected into one. Then the world will know that you sent me and will understand that you love them as much as you love me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 24, 'Father, I want these whom you''ve given me to be with me, so they can see my glory. You gave me the glory because you loved me even before the world began!', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 25, '"O righteous Father, the world doesn''t know you, but I do; and these disciples know you sent me.', 'NLT'),
(6, 17, 26, 'And I have revealed you to them and will keep on revealing you. I will do this so that your love for me may be in them and I in them."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 1, 'After saying these things, Jesus crossed the Kidron Valley with his disciples and entered a grove of olive trees.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 2, 'Judas, the betrayer, knew this place, because Jesus had gone there many times with his disciples.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 3, 'The leading priests and Pharisees had given Judas a battalion of Roman soldiers and Temple guards to accompany him. Now with blazing torches, lanterns, and weapons, they arrived at the olive grove.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 4, 'Jesus fully realized all that was going to happen to him. Stepping forward to meet them, he asked, "Whom are you looking for?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 5, '"Jesus of Nazareth," they replied. "I am he," Jesus said. Judas was standing there with them when Jesus identified himself.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 6, 'And as he said, "I am he," they all fell backward to the ground!', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 7, 'Once more he asked them, "Whom are you searching for?" And again they replied, "Jesus of Nazareth."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 8, '"I told you that I am he," Jesus said. "And since I am the one you want, let these others go."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 9, 'He did this to fulfill his own statement: "I have not lost a single one of those you gave me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 10, 'Then Simon Peter drew a sword and slashed off the right ear of Malchus, the high priest''s servant.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 11, 'But Jesus said to Peter, "Put your sword back into its sheath. Shall I not drink from the cup the Father has given me?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 12, 'So the soldiers, their commanding officer, and the Temple guards arrested Jesus and tied him up.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 13, 'First they took him to Annas, the father-in-law of Caiaphas, the high priest that year.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 14, 'Caiaphas was the one who had told the other Jewish leaders, "Better that one should die for all."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 15, 'Simon Peter followed along behind, as did another of the disciples. That other disciple was acquainted with the high priest, so he was allowed to enter the courtyard with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 16, 'Peter stood outside the gate. Then the other disciple spoke to the woman watching at the gate, and she let Peter in.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 17, 'The woman asked Peter, "Aren''t you one of Jesus'' disciples?No," he said, "I am not."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 18, 'The guards and the household servants were standing around a charcoal fire they had made because it was cold. And Peter stood there with them, warming himself.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 19, 'Inside, the high priest began asking Jesus about his followers and what he had been teaching them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 20, 'Jesus replied, "What I teach is widely known, because I have preached regularly in the synagogues and the Temple. I have been heard by people everywhere, and I teach nothing in private that I have not said in public.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 21, 'Why are you asking me this question? Ask those who heard me. They know what I said."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 22, 'One of the Temple guards standing there struck Jesus on the face. "Is that the way to answer the high priest?" he demanded.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 23, 'Jesus replied, "If I said anything wrong, you must give evidence for it. Should you hit a man for telling the truth?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 24, 'Then Annas bound Jesus and sent him to Caiaphas, the high priest.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 25, 'Meanwhile, as Simon Peter was standing by the fire, they asked him again, "Aren''t you one of his disciples?I am not," he said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 26, 'But one of the household servants of the high priest, a relative of the man whose ear Peter had cut off, asked, "Didn''t I see you out there in the olive grove with Jesus?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 27, 'Again Peter denied it. And immediately a rooster crowed.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 28, 'Jesus'' trial before Caiaphas ended in the early hours of the morning. Then he was taken to the headquarters of the Roman governor. His accusers didn''t go in themselves because it would defile them, and they wouldn''t be allowed to celebrate the Passover feast.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 29, 'So Pilate, the governor, went out to them and asked, "What is your charge against this man?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 30, '"We wouldn''t have handed him over to you if he weren''t a criminal!" they retorted.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 31, '"Then take him away and judge him by your own laws," Pilate told them. "Only the Romans are permitted to execute someone," the Jewish leaders replied.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 32, 'This fulfilled Jesus'' prediction about the way he would die.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 33, 'Then Pilate went back inside and called for Jesus to be brought to him. "Are you the King of the Jews?" he asked him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 34, 'Jesus replied, "Is this your own question, or did others tell you about me?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 35, '"Am I a Jew?" Pilate asked. "Your own people and their leading priests brought you here. Why? What have you done?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 36, 'Then Jesus answered, "I am not an earthly king. If I were, my followers would have fought when I was arrested by the Jewish leaders. But my Kingdom is not of this world."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 37, 'Pilate replied, "You are a king then?You say that I am a king, and you are right," Jesus said. "I was born for that purpose. And I came to bring truth to the world. All who love the truth recognize that what I say is true."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 38, '"What is truth?" Pilate asked. Then he went out again to the people and told them, "He is not guilty of any crime.', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 39, 'But you have a custom of asking me to release someone from prison each year at Passover. So if you want me to, I''ll release the King of the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(6, 18, 40, 'But they shouted back, "No! Not this man, but Barabbas!" (Barabbas was a criminal.)', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 1, 'Then Pilate had Jesus flogged with a lead-tipped whip.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 2, 'The soldiers made a crown of long, sharp thorns and put it on his head, and they put a royal purple robe on him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 3, '"Hail! King of the Jews!" they mocked, and they hit him with their fists.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 4, 'Pilate went outside again and said to the people, "I am going to bring him out to you now, but understand clearly that I find him not guilty."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 5, 'Then Jesus came out wearing the crown of thorns and the purple robe. And Pilate said, "Here is the man!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 6, 'When they saw him, the leading priests and Temple guards began shouting, "Crucify! Crucify!You crucify him," Pilate said. "I find him not guilty."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 7, 'The Jewish leaders replied, "By our laws he ought to die because he called himself the Son of God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 8, 'When Pilate heard this, he was more frightened than ever.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 9, 'He took Jesus back into the headquarters again and asked him, "Where are you from?" But Jesus gave no answer.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 10, '"You won''t talk to me?" Pilate demanded. "Don''t you realize that I have the power to release you or to crucify you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 11, 'Then Jesus said, "You would have no power over me at all unless it were given to you from above. So the one who brought me to you has the greater sin."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 12, 'Then Pilate tried to release him, but the Jewish leaders told him, "If you release this man, you are not a friend of Caesar. Anyone who declares himself a king is a rebel against Caesar."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 13, 'When they said this, Pilate brought Jesus out to them again. Then Pilate sat down on the judgment seat on the platform that is called the Stone Pavement (in Hebrew, Gabbatha).', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 14, 'It was now about noon of the day of preparation for the Passover. And Pilate said to the people, "Here is your king!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 15, '"Away with him," they yelled. "Away with him--crucify him!What? Crucify your king?" Pilate asked. "We have no king but Caesar," the leading priests shouted back.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 16, 'Then Pilate gave Jesus to them to be crucified. So they took Jesus and led him away.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 17, 'Carrying the cross by himself, Jesus went to the place called Skull Hill (in Hebrew, Golgotha).', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 18, 'There they crucified him. There were two others crucified with him, one on either side, with Jesus between them.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 19, 'And Pilate posted a sign over him that read, "Jesus of Nazareth, the King of the Jews."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 20, 'The place where Jesus was crucified was near the city; and the sign was written in Hebrew, Latin, and Greek, so that many people could read it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 21, 'Then the leading priests said to Pilate, "Change it from ''The King of the Jews'' to ''He said, I am King of the Jews.''"', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 22, 'Pilate replied, "What I have written, I have written. It stays exactly as it is."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 23, 'When the soldiers had crucified Jesus, they divided his clothes among the four of them. They also took his robe, but it was seamless, woven in one piece from the top.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 24, 'So they said, "Let''s not tear it but throw dice to see who gets it." This fulfilled the Scripture that says, "They divided my clothes among themselves and threw dice for my robe." So that is what they did.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 25, 'Standing near the cross were Jesus'' mother, and his mother''s sister, Mary (the wife of Clopas), and Mary Magdalene.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 26, 'When Jesus saw his mother standing there beside the disciple he loved, he said to her, "Woman, he is your son."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 27, 'And he said to this disciple, "She is your mother." And from then on this disciple took her into his home.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 28, 'Jesus knew that everything was now finished, and to fulfill the Scriptures he said, "I am thirsty."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 29, 'A jar of sour wine was sitting there, so they soaked a sponge in it, put it on a hyssop branch, and held it up to his lips.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 30, 'When Jesus had tasted it, he said, "It is finished!" Then he bowed his head and gave up his spirit.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 31, 'The Jewish leaders didn''t want the victims hanging there the next day, which was the Sabbath (and a very special Sabbath at that, because it was the Passover), so they asked Pilate to hasten their deaths by ordering that their legs be broken. Then their bodies could be taken down.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 32, 'So the soldiers came and broke the legs of the two men crucified with Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 33, 'But when they came to Jesus, they saw that he was dead already, so they didn''t break his legs.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 34, 'One of the soldiers, however, pierced his side with a spear, and blood and water flowed out.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 35, 'This report is from an eyewitness giving an accurate account; it is presented so that you also can believe.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 36, 'These things happened in fulfillment of the Scriptures that say, "Not one of his bones will be broken,"', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 37, 'and "They will look on him whom they pierced."', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 38, 'Afterward Joseph of Arimathea, who had been a secret disciple of Jesus (because he feared the Jewish leaders), asked Pilate for permission to take Jesus'' body down. When Pilate gave him permission, he came and took the body away.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 39, 'Nicodemus, the man who had come to Jesus at night, also came, bringing about seventy-five pounds of embalming ointment made from myrrh and aloes.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 40, 'Together they wrapped Jesus'' body in a long linen cloth with the spices, as is the Jewish custom of burial.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 41, 'The place of crucifixion was near a garden, where there was a new tomb, never used before.', 'NLT'),
(6, 19, 42, 'And so, because it was the day of preparation before the Passover and since the tomb was close at hand, they laid Jesus there.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 1, 'Early Sunday morning, while it was still dark, Mary Magdalene came to the tomb and found that the stone had been rolled away from the entrance.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 2, 'She ran and found Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom Jesus loved. She said, "They have taken the Lord''s body out of the tomb, and I don''t know where they have put him!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 3, 'Peter and the other disciple ran to the tomb to see.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 4, 'The other disciple outran Peter and got there first.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 5, 'He stooped and looked in and saw the linen cloth lying there, but he didn''t go in.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 6, 'Then Simon Peter arrived and went inside. He also noticed the linen wrappings lying there,', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 7, 'while the cloth that had covered Jesus'' head was folded up and lying to the side.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 8, 'Then the other disciple also went in, and he saw and believed--', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 9, 'for until then they hadn''t realized that the Scriptures said he would rise from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 10, 'Then they went home.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 11, 'Mary was standing outside the tomb crying, and as she wept, she stooped and looked in.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 12, 'She saw two white-robed angels sitting at the head and foot of the place where the body of Jesus had been lying.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 13, '"Why are you crying?" the angels asked her. "Because they have taken away my Lord," she replied, "and I don''t know where they have put him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 14, 'She glanced over her shoulder and saw someone standing behind her. It was Jesus, but she didn''t recognize him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 15, '"Why are you crying?" Jesus asked her. "Who are you looking for?" She thought he was the gardener. "Sir," she said, "if you have taken him away, tell me where you have put him, and I will go and get him."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 16, '"Mary!" Jesus said. She turned toward him and exclaimed, "Teacher!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 17, '"Don''t cling to me," Jesus said, "for I haven''t yet ascended to the Father. But go find my brothers and tell them that I am ascending to my Father and your Father, my God and your God."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 18, 'Mary Magdalene found the disciples and told them, "I have seen the Lord!" Then she gave them his message.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 19, 'That evening, on the first day of the week, the disciples were meeting behind locked doors because they were afraid of the Jewish leaders. Suddenly, Jesus was standing there among them! "Peace be with you," he said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 20, 'As he spoke, he held out his hands for them to see, and he showed them his side. They were filled with joy when they saw their Lord!', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 21, 'He spoke to them again and said, "Peace be with you. As the Father has sent me, so I send you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 22, 'Then he breathed on them and said to them, "Receive the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 23, 'If you forgive anyone''s sins, they are forgiven. If you refuse to forgive them, they are unforgiven."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 24, 'One of the disciples, Thomas (nicknamed the Twin ), was not with the others when Jesus came.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 25, 'They told him, "We have seen the Lord!" But he replied, "I won''t believe it unless I see the nail wounds in his hands, put my fingers into them, and place my hand into the wound in his side."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 26, 'Eight days later the disciples were together again, and this time Thomas was with them. The doors were locked; but suddenly, as before, Jesus was standing among them. He said, "Peace be with you."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 27, 'Then he said to Thomas, "Put your finger here and see my hands. Put your hand into the wound in my side. Don''t be faithless any longer. Believe!"', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 28, '"My Lord and my God!" Thomas exclaimed.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 29, 'Then Jesus told him, "You believe because you have seen me. Blessed are those who haven''t seen me and believe anyway."', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 30, 'Jesus'' disciples saw him do many other miraculous signs besides the ones recorded in this book.', 'NLT'),
(6, 20, 31, 'But these are written so that you may believe that Jesus is the Messiah, the Son of God, and that by believing in him you will have life.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 1, 'Later Jesus appeared again to the disciples beside the Sea of Galilee. This is how it happened.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 2, 'Several of the disciples were there--Simon Peter, Thomas (nicknamed the Twin ), Nathanael from Cana in Galilee, the sons of Zebedee, and two other disciples.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 3, 'Simon Peter said, "I''m going fishing.We''ll come, too," they all said. So they went out in the boat, but they caught nothing all night.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 4, 'At dawn the disciples saw Jesus standing on the beach, but they couldn''t see who he was.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 5, 'He called out, "Friends, have you caught any fish?No," they replied.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 6, 'Then he said, "Throw out your net on the right-hand side of the boat, and you''ll get plenty of fish!" So they did, and they couldn''t draw in the net because there were so many fish in it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 7, 'Then the disciple whom Jesus loved said to Peter, "It is the Lord!" When Simon Peter heard that it was the Lord, he put on his tunic (for he had stripped for work), jumped into the water, and swam ashore.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 8, 'The others stayed with the boat and pulled the loaded net to the shore, for they were only out about three hundred feet.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 9, 'When they got there, they saw that a charcoal fire was burning and fish were frying over it, and there was bread.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 10, '"Bring some of the fish you''ve just caught," Jesus said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 11, 'So Simon Peter went aboard and dragged the net to the shore. There were 153 large fish, and yet the net hadn''t torn.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 12, '"Now come and have some breakfast!" Jesus said. And no one dared ask him if he really was the Lord because they were sure of it.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 13, 'Then Jesus served them the bread and the fish.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 14, 'This was the third time Jesus had appeared to his disciples since he had been raised from the dead.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 15, 'After breakfast Jesus said to Simon Peter, "Simon son of John, do you love me more than these?Yes, Lord," Peter replied, "you know I love you.Then feed my lambs," Jesus told him.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 16, 'Jesus repeated the question: "Simon son of John, do you love me?Yes, Lord," Peter said, "you know I love you.Then take care of my sheep," Jesus said.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 17, 'Once more he asked him, "Simon son of John, do you love me?" Peter was grieved that Jesus asked the question a third time. He said, "Lord, you know everything. You know I love you." Jesus said, "Then feed my sheep.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 18, 'The truth is, when you were young, you were able to do as you liked and go wherever you wanted to. But when you are old, you will stretch out your hands, and others will direct you and take you where you don''t want to go."', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 19, 'Jesus said this to let him know what kind of death he would die to glorify God. Then Jesus told him, "Follow me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 20, 'Peter turned around and saw the disciple Jesus loved following them--the one who had leaned over to Jesus during supper and asked, "Lord, who among us will betray you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 21, 'Peter asked Jesus, "What about him, Lord?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 22, 'Jesus replied, "If I want him to remain alive until I return, what is that to you? You follow me."', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 23, 'So the rumor spread among the community of believers that that disciple wouldn''t die. But that isn''t what Jesus said at all. He only said, "If I want him to remain alive until I return, what is that to you?"', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 24, 'This is that disciple who saw these events and recorded them here. And we all know that his account of these things is accurate.', 'NLT'),
(6, 21, 25, 'And I suppose that if all the other things Jesus did were written down, the whole world could not contain the books.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 1, 'Dear Theophilus: In my first book I told you about everything Jesus began to do and teach', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 2, 'until the day he ascended to heaven after giving his chosen apostles further instructions from the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 3, 'During the forty days after his crucifixion, he appeared to the apostles from time to time and proved to them in many ways that he was actually alive. On these occasions he talked to them about the Kingdom of God.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 4, 'In one of these meetings as he was eating a meal with them, he told them, "Do not leave Jerusalem until the Father sends you what he promised. Remember, I have told you about this before.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 5, 'John baptized with water, but in just a few days you will be baptized with the Holy Spirit."', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 6, 'When the apostles were with Jesus, they kept asking him, "Lord, are you going to free Israel now and restore our kingdom?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 7, '"The Father sets those dates," he replied, "and they are not for you to know.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 8, 'But when the Holy Spirit has come upon you, you will receive power and will tell people about me everywhere--in Jerusalem, throughout Judea, in Samaria, and to the ends of the earth."', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 9, 'It was not long after he said this that he was taken up into the sky while they were watching, and he disappeared into a cloud.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 10, 'As they were straining their eyes to see him, two white-robed men suddenly stood there among them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 11, 'They said, "Men of Galilee, why are you standing here staring at the sky? Jesus has been taken away from you into heaven. And someday, just as you saw him go, he will return!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 12, 'The apostles were at the Mount of Olives when this happened, so they walked the half mile back to Jerusalem.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 13, 'Then they went to the upstairs room of the house where they were staying. Here is the list of those who were present: Peter, John, James, Andrew, Philip, Thomas, Bartholomew, Matthew, James (son of Alphaeus), Simon (the Zealot), and Judas (son of James).', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 14, 'They all met together continually for prayer, along with Mary the mother of Jesus, several other women, and the brothers of Jesus.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 15, 'During this time, on a day when about 120 believers were present, Peter stood up and addressed them as follows:', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 16, '"Brothers, it was necessary for the Scriptures to be fulfilled concerning Judas, who guided the Temple police to arrest Jesus. This was predicted long ago by the Holy Spirit, speaking through King David.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 17, 'Judas was one of us, chosen to share in the ministry with us."', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 18, '(Judas bought a field with the money he received for his treachery, and falling there, he burst open, spilling out his intestines.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 19, 'The news of his death spread rapidly among all the people of Jerusalem, and they gave the place the Aramaic name Akeldama, which means "Field of Blood.")', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 20, 'Peter continued, "This was predicted in the book of Psalms, where it says, ''Let his home become desolate, with no one living in it.'' And again, ''Let his position be given to someone else.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 21, '"So now we must choose another man to take Judas''s place. It must be someone who has been with us all the time that we were with the Lord Jesus--', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 22, 'from the time he was baptized by John until the day he was taken from us into heaven. Whoever is chosen will join us as a witness of Jesus'' resurrection."', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 23, 'So they nominated two men: Joseph called Barsabbas (also known as Justus) and Matthias.', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 24, 'Then they all prayed for the right man to be chosen. "O Lord," they said, "you know every heart. Show us which of these men you have chosen', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 25, 'as an apostle to replace Judas the traitor in this ministry, for he has deserted us and gone where he belongs."', 'NLT'),
(7, 1, 26, 'Then they cast lots, and in this way Matthias was chosen and became an apostle with the other eleven.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 1, 'On the day of Pentecost, seven weeks after Jesus'' resurrection, the believers were meeting together in one place.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 2, 'Suddenly, there was a sound from heaven like the roaring of a mighty windstorm in the skies above them, and it filled the house where they were meeting.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 3, 'Then, what looked like flames or tongues of fire appeared and settled on each of them.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 4, 'And everyone present was filled with the Holy Spirit and began speaking in other languages, as the Holy Spirit gave them this ability.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 5, 'Godly Jews from many nations were living in Jerusalem at that time.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 6, 'When they heard this sound, they came running to see what it was all about, and they were bewildered to hear their own languages being spoken by the believers.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 7, 'They were beside themselves with wonder. "How can this be?" they exclaimed. "These people are all from Galilee,', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 8, 'and yet we hear them speaking the languages of the lands where we were born!', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 9, 'Here we are--Parthians, Medes, Elamites, people from Mesopotamia, Judea, Cappadocia, Pontus, the province of Asia,', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 10, 'Phrygia, Pamphylia, Egypt, and the areas of Libya toward Cyrene, visitors from Rome (both Jews and converts to Judaism),', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 11, 'Cretans, and Arabians. And we all hear these people speaking in our own languages about the wonderful things God has done!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 12, 'They stood there amazed and perplexed. "What can this mean?" they asked each other.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 13, 'But others in the crowd were mocking. "They''re drunk, that''s all!" they said.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 14, 'Then Peter stepped forward with the eleven other apostles and shouted to the crowd, "Listen carefully, all of you, fellow Jews and residents of Jerusalem! Make no mistake about this.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 15, 'Some of you are saying these people are drunk. It isn''t true! It''s much too early for that. People don''t get drunk by nine o''clock in the morning.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 16, 'No, what you see this morning was predicted centuries ago by the prophet Joel:', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 17, '''In the last days, God said, I will pour out my Spirit upon all people. Your sons and daughters will prophesy, your young men will see visions, and your old men will dream dreams.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 18, 'In those days I will pour out my Spirit upon all my servants, men and women alike, and they will prophesy.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 19, 'And I will cause wonders in the heavens above and signs on the earth below--blood and fire and clouds of smoke.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 20, 'The sun will be turned into darkness, and the moon will turn bloodred, before that great and glorious day of the Lord arrives.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 21, 'And anyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 22, '"People of Israel, listen! God publicly endorsed Jesus of Nazareth by doing wonderful miracles, wonders, and signs through him, as you well know.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 23, 'But you followed God''s prearranged plan. With the help of lawless Gentiles, you nailed him to the cross and murdered him.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 24, 'However, God released him from the horrors of death and raised him back to life again, for death could not keep him in its grip.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 25, 'King David said this about him: ''I know the Lord is always with me. I will not be shaken, for he is right beside me.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 26, 'No wonder my heart is filled with joy, and my mouth shouts his praises! My body rests in hope.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 27, 'For you will not leave my soul among the dead or allow your Holy One to rot in the grave.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 28, 'You have shown me the way of life, and you will give me wonderful joy in your presence.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 29, '"Dear brothers, think about this! David wasn''t referring to himself when he spoke these words I have quoted, for he died and was buried, and his tomb is still here among us.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 30, 'But he was a prophet, and he knew God had promised with an oath that one of David''s own descendants would sit on David''s throne as the Messiah.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 31, 'David was looking into the future and predicting the Messiah''s resurrection. He was saying that the Messiah would not be left among the dead and that his body would not rot in the grave.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 32, '"This prophecy was speaking of Jesus, whom God raised from the dead, and we all are witnesses of this.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 33, 'Now he sits on the throne of highest honor in heaven, at God''s right hand. And the Father, as he had promised, gave him the Holy Spirit to pour out upon us, just as you see and hear today.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 34, 'For David himself never ascended into heaven, yet he said, ''The LORD said to my Lord, Sit in honor at my right hand', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 35, 'until I humble your enemies, making them a footstool under your feet.''', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 36, 'So let it be clearly known by everyone in Israel that God has made this Jesus whom you crucified to be both Lord and Messiah!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 37, 'Peter''s words convicted them deeply, and they said to him and to the other apostles, "Brothers, what should we do?"', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 38, 'Peter replied, "Each of you must turn from your sins and turn to God, and be baptized in the name of Jesus Christ for the forgiveness of your sins. Then you will receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 39, 'This promise is to you and to your children, and even to the Gentiles--all who have been called by the Lord our God."', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 40, 'Then Peter continued preaching for a long time, strongly urging all his listeners, "Save yourselves from this generation that has gone astray!"', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 41, 'Those who believed what Peter said were baptized and added to the church--about three thousand in all.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 42, 'They joined with the other believers and devoted themselves to the apostles'' teaching and fellowship, sharing in the Lord''s Supper and in prayer.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 43, 'A deep sense of awe came over them all, and the apostles performed many miraculous signs and wonders.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 44, 'And all the believers met together constantly and shared everything they had.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 45, 'They sold their possessions and shared the proceeds with those in need.', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 46, 'They worshiped together at the Temple each day, met in homes for the Lord''s Supper, and shared their meals with great joy and generosity--', 'NLT'),
(7, 2, 47, 'all the while praising God and enjoying the goodwill of all the people. And each day the Lord added to their group those who were being saved.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 1, 'Peter and John went to the Temple one afternoon to take part in the three o''clock prayer service.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 2, 'As they approached the Temple, a man lame from birth was being carried in. Each day he was put beside the Temple gate, the one called the Beautiful Gate, so he could beg from the people going into the Temple.', 'NLT'),
(7, 3, 3, 'When he saw Peter and John about to enter, he asked them for some money.', 'NLT');
